59 struct FormalParametersBase {
60  explicit FormalParametersBase(DeclarationScope* scope) : scope(scope) {}
61 
62  int num_parameters() const {
63  // Don't include the rest parameter into the function's formal parameter
64  // count (esp. the SharedFunctionInfo::internal_formal_parameter_count,
65  // which says whether we need to create an inlined arguments frame).
66  return arity - has_rest;
67  }
68 
69  void UpdateArityAndFunctionLength(bool is_optional, bool is_rest) {
70  if (!is_optional && !is_rest && function_length == arity) {
71  ++function_length;
72  }
73  ++arity;
74  }
75 
76  DeclarationScope* scope;
77  bool has_rest = false;
78  bool is_simple = true;
79  int function_length = 0;
80  int arity = 0;
81 };

83 // Stack-allocated scope to collect source ranges from the parser.
84 class V8_NODISCARD SourceRangeScope final {
85  public:
86  SourceRangeScope(const Scanner* scanner, SourceRange* range)
87  : scanner_(scanner), range_(range) {
88  range_->start = scanner->peek_location().beg_pos;
89  DCHECK_NE(range_->start, kNoSourcePosition);
90  DCHECK_EQ(range_->end, kNoSourcePosition);
91  }
92 
93  ~SourceRangeScope() {
94  DCHECK_EQ(kNoSourcePosition, range_->end);
95  range_->end = scanner_->location().end_pos;
96  DCHECK_NE(range_->end, kNoSourcePosition);
97  }
98 
99  private:
100  const Scanner* scanner_;
101  SourceRange* range_;
102 
103  DISALLOW_IMPLICIT_CONSTRUCTORS(SourceRangeScope);
104 };

106 // ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
107 // The RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR macro is a convenient macro to enforce error
108 // handling for functions that may fail (by returning if there was an parser
109 // error).
110 //
111 // Usage:
112 // foo = ParseFoo(); // may fail
113 // RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR
114 //
115 // SAFE_USE(foo);
116 
117 #define RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR \
118  if (has_error()) return impl()->NullStatement();
119 
120 // Common base class template shared between parser and pre-parser.
121 // The Impl parameter is the actual class of the parser/pre-parser,
122 // following the Curiously Recurring Template Pattern (CRTP).
123 // The structure of the parser objects is roughly the following:
124 //
125 // // A structure template containing type definitions, needed to
126 // // avoid a cyclic dependency.
127 // template <typename Impl>
128 // struct ParserTypes;
129 //
130 // // The parser base object, which should just implement pure
131 // // parser behavior. The Impl parameter is the actual derived
132 // // class (according to CRTP), which implements impure parser
133 // // behavior.
134 // template <typename Impl>
135 // class ParserBase { ... };
136 //
137 // // And then, for each parser variant (e.g., parser, preparser, etc):
138 // class Parser;
139 //
140 // template <>
141 // class ParserTypes<Parser> { ... };
142 //
143 // class Parser : public ParserBase<Parser> { ... };
144 //
145 // The parser base object implements pure parsing, according to the
146 // language grammar. Different parser implementations may exhibit
147 // different parser-driven behavior that is not considered as pure
148 // parsing, e.g., early error detection and reporting, AST generation, etc.
149 
150 // The ParserTypes structure encapsulates the differences in the
151 // types used in parsing methods. E.g., Parser methods use Expression*
152 // and PreParser methods use PreParserExpression. For any given parser
153 // implementation class Impl, it is expected to contain the following typedefs:
154 //
155 // template <>
156 // struct ParserTypes<Impl> {
157 // // Synonyms for ParserBase<Impl> and Impl, respectively.
158 // typedef Base;
159 // typedef Impl;
160 // // Return types for traversing functions.
161 // typedef Identifier;
162 // typedef Expression;
163 // typedef FunctionLiteral;
164 // typedef ObjectLiteralProperty;
165 // typedef ClassLiteralProperty;
166 // typedef ExpressionList;
167 // typedef ObjectPropertyList;
168 // typedef ClassPropertyList;
169 // typedef FormalParameters;
170 // typedef Statement;
171 // typedef StatementList;
172 // typedef Block;
173 // typedef BreakableStatement;
174 // typedef ForStatement;
175 // typedef IterationStatement;
176 // // For constructing objects returned by the traversing functions.
177 // typedef Factory;
178 // // For other implementation-specific tasks.
179 // typedef Target;
180 // typedef TargetScope;
181 // };
182 
183 template <typename Impl>
184 struct ParserTypes;
185

187  kAutoAccessorClassField,
188  kAccessorGetter,
189  kAccessorSetter,
190  kValue,

193  kMethod,
194  kClassField,
195  kShorthandOrClassField,
196  kSpread,
197  kNotSet
198 };

200 template <typename Impl>
201 class ParserBase {
202  public:
203  // Shorten type names defined by ParserTypes<Impl>.
204  using Types = ParserTypes<Impl>;
205  using ExpressionScope = typename v8::internal::ExpressionScope<Types>;
206  using ExpressionParsingScope =
207  typename v8::internal::ExpressionParsingScope<Types>;
208  using AccumulationScope = typename v8::internal::AccumulationScope<Types>;
209  using ArrowHeadParsingScope =
210  typename v8::internal::ArrowHeadParsingScope<Types>;
211  using VariableDeclarationParsingScope =
212  typename v8::internal::VariableDeclarationParsingScope<Types>;
213  using ParameterDeclarationParsingScope =
214  typename v8::internal::ParameterDeclarationParsingScope<Types>;
215 
216  // Return types for traversing functions.
217  using BlockT = typename Types::Block;
218  using BreakableStatementT = typename Types::BreakableStatement;
219  using ClassLiteralPropertyT = typename Types::ClassLiteralProperty;
220  using ClassPropertyListT = typename Types::ClassPropertyList;
221  using ClassStaticElementListT = typename Types::ClassStaticElementList;
222  using ExpressionT = typename Types::Expression;
223  using ExpressionListT = typename Types::ExpressionList;
224  using FormalParametersT = typename Types::FormalParameters;
225  using ForStatementT = typename Types::ForStatement;
226  using FunctionLiteralT = typename Types::FunctionLiteral;
227  using IdentifierT = typename Types::Identifier;
228  using IterationStatementT = typename Types::IterationStatement;
229  using ObjectLiteralPropertyT = typename Types::ObjectLiteralProperty;
230  using ObjectPropertyListT = typename Types::ObjectPropertyList;
231  using StatementT = typename Types::Statement;
232  using StatementListT = typename Types::StatementList;
233  using SuspendExpressionT = typename Types::Suspend;
234  // For constructing objects returned by the traversing functions.
235  using FactoryT = typename Types::Factory;
236  // Other implementation-specific tasks.
237  using FuncNameInferrer = typename Types::FuncNameInferrer;
238  using FuncNameInferrerState = typename Types::FuncNameInferrer::State;
239  using SourceRange = typename Types::SourceRange;
240  using SourceRangeScope = typename Types::SourceRangeScope;
241 
242  // All implementation-specific methods must be called through this.
243  Impl* impl() { return static_cast<Impl*>(this); }
244  const Impl* impl() const { return static_cast<const Impl*>(this); }
245

261  parsing_on_main_thread_(parsing_on_main_thread),
262  stack_limit_(stack_limit),
263  pending_error_handler_(pending_error_handler),
264  zone_(zone),
265  expression_scope_(nullptr),
266  scanner_(scanner),
267  flags_(flags),
268  info_id_(0),
269  has_module_in_scope_chain_(flags_.is_module()),
270  default_eager_compile_hint_(FunctionLiteral::kShouldLazyCompile),
271  compile_hints_magic_enabled_(compile_hints_magic_enabled),
272  compile_hints_per_function_magic_enabled_(
273  compile_hints_per_function_magic_enabled) {
274  pointer_buffer_.reserve(32);
275  variable_buffer_.reserve(32);
276  }

336  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
337  // BlockState and FunctionState implement the parser's scope stack.
338  // The parser's current scope is in scope_. BlockState and FunctionState
339  // constructors push on the scope stack and the destructors pop. They are also
340  // used to hold the parser's per-funcion state.
341  class BlockState {
342  public:
343  BlockState(Scope** scope_stack, Scope* scope)
344  : scope_stack_(scope_stack), outer_scope_(*scope_stack) {
345  *scope_stack_ = scope;
346  }
347 
348  BlockState(Zone* zone, Scope** scope_stack)
349  : BlockState(scope_stack,
350  zone->New<Scope>(zone, *scope_stack, BLOCK_SCOPE)) {}
351 
352  ~BlockState() { *scope_stack_ = outer_scope_; }
353 
354  private:
355  Scope** const scope_stack_;
356  Scope* const outer_scope_;
357  };
358 
359  // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
360  // Target is a support class to facilitate manipulation of the
361  // Parser's target_stack_ (the stack of potential 'break' and
362  // 'continue' statement targets). Upon construction, a new target is
363  // added; it is removed upon destruction.
364 
365  // |labels| is a list of all labels that can be used as a target for break.
366  // |own_labels| is a list of all labels that an iteration statement is
367  // directly prefixed with, i.e. all the labels that a continue statement in
368  // the body can use to continue this iteration statement. This is always a
369  // subset of |labels|.
370  //
371  // Example: "l1: { l2: if (b) l3: l4: for (;;) s }"
372  // labels() of the Block will be l1.
373  // labels() of the ForStatement will be l2, l3, l4.
374  // own_labels() of the ForStatement will be l3, l4.
375  class Target {
376  public:
377  enum TargetType { TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS, TARGET_FOR_NAMED_ONLY };
378 
379  Target(ParserBase* parser, BreakableStatementT statement,
380  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
381  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels, TargetType target_type)
382  : stack_(parser->function_state_->target_stack_address()),
383  statement_(statement),
384  labels_(labels),
385  own_labels_(own_labels),
386  target_type_(target_type),
387  previous_(*stack_) {
388  DCHECK_IMPLIES(Impl::IsIterationStatement(statement_),
389  target_type == Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
390  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!Impl::IsIterationStatement(statement_),
391  own_labels == nullptr);
392  *stack_ = this;
393  }
394 
395  ~Target() { *stack_ = previous_; }
396 
397  const Target* previous() const { return previous_; }
398  const BreakableStatementT statement() const { return statement_; }
399  const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels() const { return labels_; }
400  const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels() const {
401  return own_labels_;
402  }
403  bool is_iteration() const { return Impl::IsIterationStatement(statement_); }
404  bool is_target_for_anonymous() const {
405  return target_type_ == TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS;
406  }
407 
408  private:
409  Target** const stack_;
410  const BreakableStatementT statement_;
411  const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* const labels_;
412  const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* const own_labels_;
413  const TargetType target_type_;
414  Target* const previous_;
415  };
416 
417  Target* target_stack() { return *function_state_->target_stack_address(); }
418 
419  BreakableStatementT LookupBreakTarget(IdentifierT label) {
420  bool anonymous = impl()->IsNull(label);
421  for (const Target* t = target_stack(); t != nullptr; t = t->previous()) {
422  if ((anonymous && t->is_target_for_anonymous()) ||
423  (!anonymous &&
424  ContainsLabel(t->labels(),
425  impl()->GetRawNameFromIdentifier(label)))) {
426  return t->statement();
427  }
428  }
429  return impl()->NullStatement();
430  }
431 
432  IterationStatementT LookupContinueTarget(IdentifierT label) {
433  bool anonymous = impl()->IsNull(label);
434  for (const Target* t = target_stack(); t != nullptr; t = t->previous()) {
435  if (!t->is_iteration()) continue;
436 
437  DCHECK(t->is_target_for_anonymous());
438  if (anonymous || ContainsLabel(t->own_labels(),
439  impl()->GetRawNameFromIdentifier(label))) {
440  return impl()->AsIterationStatement(t->statement());
441  }
442  }
443  return impl()->NullStatement();
444  }

485  class V8_NODISCARD FunctionOrEvalRecordingScope {
486  public:
487  explicit FunctionOrEvalRecordingScope(FunctionState* state)
488  : state_and_prev_value_(state, state->contains_function_or_eval_) {
489  state->contains_function_or_eval_ = false;
490  }
491  ~FunctionOrEvalRecordingScope() {
492  bool found = state_and_prev_value_->contains_function_or_eval_;
493  if (!found) {
494  state_and_prev_value_->contains_function_or_eval_ =
495  state_and_prev_value_.GetPayload();
496  }
497  }
498 
499  private:
500  base::PointerWithPayload<FunctionState, bool, 1> state_and_prev_value_;
501  };

503  class V8_NODISCARD LoopScope final {
504  public:
505  explicit LoopScope(FunctionState* function_state)
506  : function_state_(function_state) {
507  function_state_->loop_nesting_depth_++;
508  }
509 
510  ~LoopScope() { function_state_->loop_nesting_depth_--; }
511 
512  private:
513  FunctionState* function_state_;
514  };
515 
516  int loop_nesting_depth() const { return loop_nesting_depth_; }
517 
518  Target** target_stack_address() { return &target_stack_; }
519 
520  private:
521  // Properties count estimation.
522  int expected_property_count_;
523 
524  // How many suspends are needed for this function.
525  int suspend_count_;
526 
527  // How deeply nested we currently are in this function.
528  int loop_nesting_depth_ = 0;
529 
530  FunctionState** function_state_stack_;
531  FunctionState* outer_function_state_;
532  DeclarationScope* scope_;
533  Target* target_stack_ = nullptr; // for break, continue statements
534 
535  // A reason, if any, why this function should not be optimized.
536  BailoutReason dont_optimize_reason_;
537 
538  // Record whether the next (=== immediately following) function literal is
539  // preceded by a parenthesis / exclamation mark. Also record the previous
540  // state.
541  // These are managed by the FunctionState constructor; the caller may only
542  // call set_next_function_is_likely_called.
543  bool next_function_is_likely_called_;
544  bool previous_function_was_likely_called_;
545 
546  // Track if a function or eval occurs within this FunctionState
547  bool contains_function_or_eval_;
548 
549  friend Impl;
550  };

605  struct ClassInfo {
606  public:
607  explicit ClassInfo(ParserBase* parser)
608  : extends(parser->impl()->NullExpression()),
609  public_members(parser->impl()->NewClassPropertyList(4)),
610  private_members(parser->impl()->NewClassPropertyList(4)),
611  static_elements(parser->impl()->NewClassStaticElementList(4)),
612  instance_fields(parser->impl()->NewClassPropertyList(4)),
613  constructor(parser->impl()->NullExpression()) {}
614  ExpressionT extends;
615  ClassPropertyListT public_members;
616  ClassPropertyListT private_members;
617  ClassStaticElementListT static_elements;
618  ClassPropertyListT instance_fields;
619  FunctionLiteralT constructor;
620 
621  bool has_static_elements() const {
622  return static_elements_scope != nullptr;
623  }
624  bool has_instance_members() const {
625  return instance_members_scope != nullptr;
626  }
627 
628  DeclarationScope* EnsureStaticElementsScope(ParserBase* parser, int beg_pos,
629  int info_id) {
630  if (!has_static_elements()) {
631  static_elements_scope = parser->NewFunctionScope(
632  FunctionKind::kClassStaticInitializerFunction);
633  static_elements_scope->SetLanguageMode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
634  static_elements_scope->set_start_position(beg_pos);
635  static_elements_function_id = info_id;
636  // Actually consume the id. The id that was passed in might be an
637  // earlier id in case of computed property names.
638  parser->GetNextInfoId();
639  }
640  return static_elements_scope;
641  }
642 
643  DeclarationScope* EnsureInstanceMembersScope(ParserBase* parser,
644  int beg_pos, int info_id) {
645  if (!has_instance_members()) {
646  instance_members_scope = parser->NewFunctionScope(
647  FunctionKind::kClassMembersInitializerFunction);
648  instance_members_scope->SetLanguageMode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
649  instance_members_scope->set_start_position(beg_pos);
650  instance_members_function_id = info_id;
651  // Actually consume the id. The id that was passed in might be an
652  // earlier id in case of computed property names.
653  parser->GetNextInfoId();
654  }
655  return instance_members_scope;
656  }
657 
658  DeclarationScope* static_elements_scope = nullptr;
659  DeclarationScope* instance_members_scope = nullptr;
660  Variable* home_object_variable = nullptr;
661  Variable* static_home_object_variable = nullptr;
662  int autoaccessor_count = 0;
663  int static_elements_function_id = -1;
664  int instance_members_function_id = -1;
665  int computed_field_count = 0;
666  bool has_seen_constructor = false;
667  bool has_static_computed_names : 1 = false;
668  bool has_static_private_methods_or_accessors : 1 = false;
669  bool has_static_blocks : 1 = false;
670  bool requires_brand : 1 = false;
671  bool is_anonymous : 1 = false;
672  };

674  enum class PropertyPosition { kObjectLiteral, kClassLiteral };
675  struct ParsePropertyInfo {
676  public:
677  explicit ParsePropertyInfo(ParserBase* parser,
678  AccumulationScope* accumulation_scope = nullptr)
679  : accumulation_scope(accumulation_scope),
680  name(parser->impl()->NullIdentifier()),
681  position(PropertyPosition::kClassLiteral),
682  function_flags(ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal),
683  kind(ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet),
684  is_computed_name(false),
685  is_private(false),
686  is_static(false),
687  is_rest(false) {}
688 
689  bool ParsePropertyKindFromToken(Token::Value token) {
690  // This returns true, setting the property kind, iff the given token is
691  // one which must occur after a property name, indicating that the
692  // previous token was in fact a name and not a modifier (like the "get" in
693  // "get x").
694  switch (token) {
695  case Token::kColon:
696  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kValue;
697  return true;
698  case Token::kComma:
699  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kShorthand;
700  return true;
701  case Token::kRightBrace:
702  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kShorthandOrClassField;
703  return true;
704  case Token::kAssign:
705  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kAssign;
706  return true;
707  case Token::kLeftParen:
708  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kMethod;
709  return true;
710  case Token::kMul:
711  case Token::kSemicolon:
712  kind = ParsePropertyKind::kClassField;
713  return true;
714  default:
715  break;
716  }
717  return false;
718  }
719 
720  AccumulationScope* accumulation_scope;
721  IdentifierT name;
722  PropertyPosition position;
723  ParseFunctionFlags function_flags;
724  ParsePropertyKind kind;
725  bool is_computed_name;
726  bool is_private;
727  bool is_static;
728  bool is_rest;
729  };
730 
731  void DeclareLabel(ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>** labels,
732  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>** own_labels,
733  const AstRawString* label) {
734  if (ContainsLabel(*labels, label) || TargetStackContainsLabel(label)) {
735  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kLabelRedeclaration, label);
736  return;
737  }
738 
739  // Add {label} to both {labels} and {own_labels}.
740  if (*labels == nullptr) {
741  DCHECK_NULL(*own_labels);
742  *labels =
743  zone()->template New<ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>>(1, zone());
744  *own_labels =
745  zone()->template New<ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>>(1, zone());
746  } else {
747  if (*own_labels == nullptr) {
748  *own_labels =
749  zone()->template New<ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>>(1, zone());
750  }
751  }
752  (*labels)->Add(label, zone());
753  (*own_labels)->Add(label, zone());
754  }
755 
756  bool ContainsLabel(const ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
757  const AstRawString* label) {
758  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(label);
759  if (labels != nullptr) {
760  for (int i = labels->length(); i-- > 0;) {
761  if (labels->at(i) == label) return true;
762  }
763  }
764  return false;
765  }
766 
767  bool TargetStackContainsLabel(const AstRawString* label) {
768  for (const Target* t = target_stack(); t != nullptr; t = t->previous()) {
769  if (ContainsLabel(t->labels(), label)) return true;
770  }
771  return false;
772  }
773 
774  ClassLiteralProperty::Kind ClassPropertyKindFor(ParsePropertyKind kind) {
775  switch (kind) {
776  case ParsePropertyKind::kAutoAccessorClassField:
777  return ClassLiteralProperty::AUTO_ACCESSOR;
778  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter:
779  return ClassLiteralProperty::GETTER;
780  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorSetter:
781  return ClassLiteralProperty::SETTER;
782  case ParsePropertyKind::kMethod:
783  return ClassLiteralProperty::METHOD;
784  case ParsePropertyKind::kClassField:
785  return ClassLiteralProperty::FIELD;
786  default:
787  // Only returns for deterministic kinds
788  UNREACHABLE();
789  }
790  }
791 
792  VariableMode GetVariableMode(ClassLiteralProperty::Kind kind) {
793  switch (kind) {
794  case ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::FIELD:
795  return VariableMode::kConst;
796  case ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::METHOD:
797  return VariableMode::kPrivateMethod;
798  case ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::GETTER:
799  return VariableMode::kPrivateGetterOnly;
800  case ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::SETTER:
801  return VariableMode::kPrivateSetterOnly;
802  case ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::AUTO_ACCESSOR:
803  return VariableMode::kPrivateGetterAndSetter;
804  }
805  }

850  // This constructor should only be used when absolutely necessary. Most scopes
851  // should automatically use scope() as parent, and be fine with
852  // NewScope(ScopeType) above.
853  Scope* NewScopeWithParent(Scope* parent, ScopeType scope_type) const {
854  // Must always use the specific constructors for the blocklisted scope
855  // types.
856  DCHECK_NE(FUNCTION_SCOPE, scope_type);
857  DCHECK_NE(SCRIPT_SCOPE, scope_type);
858  DCHECK_NE(REPL_MODE_SCOPE, scope_type);
859  DCHECK_NE(MODULE_SCOPE, scope_type);
860  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(parent);
861  return zone()->template New<Scope>(zone(), parent, scope_type);
862  }

864  // Creates a function scope that always allocates in zone(). The function
865  // scope itself is either allocated in zone() or in target_zone if one is
866  // passed in.
867  DeclarationScope* NewFunctionScope(FunctionKind kind,
868  Zone* parse_zone = nullptr) const {
869  DCHECK(ast_value_factory());
870  if (parse_zone == nullptr) parse_zone = zone();
871  DeclarationScope* result = zone()->template New<DeclarationScope>(
872  parse_zone, scope(), FUNCTION_SCOPE, kind);
873 
874  // Record presence of an inner function scope
875  function_state_->RecordFunctionOrEvalCall();
876 
877  // TODO(verwaest): Move into the DeclarationScope constructor.
878  if (!IsArrowFunction(kind)) {
879  result->DeclareDefaultFunctionVariables(ast_value_factory());
880  }
881  return result;
882  }

928  // position past the end of the current token otherwise.

941  V8_INLINE void Consume(Token::Value token) {
942  Token::Value next = scanner()->Next();
943  USE(next);
944  USE(token);
945  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(), next == token);
946  }
947 
948  V8_INLINE bool Check(Token::Value token) {
949  Token::Value next = scanner()->peek();
950  if (next == token) {
951  Consume(next);
952  return true;
953  }
954  return false;
955  }
956 
957  void Expect(Token::Value token) {
958  Token::Value next = Next();
959  if (V8_UNLIKELY(next != token)) {
960  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
961  }
962  }
963 
964  void ExpectSemicolon() {
965  // Check for automatic semicolon insertion according to
966  // the rules given in ECMA-262, section 7.9, page 21.
967  Token::Value tok = peek();
968  if (V8_LIKELY(tok == Token::kSemicolon)) {
969  Next();
970  return;
971  }
972  if (V8_LIKELY(scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() ||
973  Token::IsAutoSemicolon(tok))) {
974  return;
975  }
976 
977  if (scanner()->current_token() == Token::kAwait && !is_async_function()) {
978  if (flags().parsing_while_debugging() == ParsingWhileDebugging::kYes) {
979  ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
980  MessageTemplate::kAwaitNotInDebugEvaluate);
981  } else {
982  ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
983  MessageTemplate::kAwaitNotInAsyncContext);
984  }
985  return;
986  }
987 
988  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
989  }

991  bool peek_any_identifier() { return Token::IsAnyIdentifier(peek()); }
992 
993  bool PeekContextualKeyword(const AstRawString* name) {
994  return peek() == Token::kIdentifier &&
995  !scanner()->next_literal_contains_escapes() &&
996  scanner()->NextSymbol(ast_value_factory()) == name;
997  }
998 
999  bool PeekContextualKeyword(Token::Value token) {
1000  return peek() == token && !scanner()->next_literal_contains_escapes();
1001  }
1002 
1003  bool CheckContextualKeyword(const AstRawString* name) {
1004  if (PeekContextualKeyword(name)) {
1005  Consume(Token::kIdentifier);
1006  return true;
1007  }
1008  return false;
1009  }
1010 
1011  bool CheckContextualKeyword(Token::Value token) {
1012  if (PeekContextualKeyword(token)) {
1013  Consume(token);
1014  return true;
1015  }
1016  return false;
1017  }
1018 
1019  void ExpectContextualKeyword(const AstRawString* name,
1020  const char* fullname = nullptr, int pos = -1) {
1021  Expect(Token::kIdentifier);
1022  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->CurrentSymbol(ast_value_factory()) != name)) {
1023  ReportUnexpectedToken(scanner()->current_token());
1024  }
1025  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
1026  const char* full = fullname == nullptr
1027  ? reinterpret_cast<const char*>(name->raw_data())
1028  : fullname;
1029  int start = pos == -1 ? position() : pos;
1030  impl()->ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(start, end_position()),
1031  MessageTemplate::kInvalidEscapedMetaProperty,
1032  full);
1033  }
1034  }
1035 
1036  void ExpectContextualKeyword(Token::Value token) {
1037  // Token Should be in range of Token::kIdentifier + 1 to Token::kAsync
1038  DCHECK(base::IsInRange(token, Token::kGet, Token::kAsync));
1039  Token::Value next = Next();
1040  if (V8_UNLIKELY(next != token)) {
1041  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
1042  }
1043  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
1044  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
1045  }
1046  }

1048  bool CheckInOrOf(ForEachStatement::VisitMode* visit_mode) {
1049  if (Check(Token::kIn)) {
1050  *visit_mode = ForEachStatement::ENUMERATE;
1051  return true;
1052  } else if (CheckContextualKeyword(Token::kOf)) {
1053  *visit_mode = ForEachStatement::ITERATE;
1054  return true;
1055  }
1056  return false;
1057  }
1058 
1059  bool PeekInOrOf() {
1060  return peek() == Token::kIn || PeekContextualKeyword(Token::kOf);
1061  }

1063  // Checks whether an octal literal was last seen between beg_pos and end_pos.
1064  // Only called for strict mode strings.
1065  void CheckStrictOctalLiteral(int beg_pos, int end_pos) {
1066  Scanner::Location octal = scanner()->octal_position();
1067  if (octal.IsValid() && beg_pos <= octal.beg_pos &&
1068  octal.end_pos <= end_pos) {
1069  MessageTemplate message = scanner()->octal_message();
1070  DCHECK_NE(message, MessageTemplate::kNone);
1071  impl()->ReportMessageAt(octal, message);
1072  scanner()->clear_octal_position();
1073  if (message == MessageTemplate::kStrictDecimalWithLeadingZero) {
1074  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kDecimalWithLeadingZeroInStrictMode);
1075  }
1076  }
1077  }
1078 
1079  // Checks if an octal literal or an invalid hex or unicode escape sequence
1080  // appears in the current template literal token. In the presence of such,
1081  // either returns false or reports an error, depending on should_throw.
1082  // Otherwise returns true.
1083  inline bool CheckTemplateEscapes(bool should_throw) {
1084  DCHECK(Token::IsTemplate(scanner()->current_token()));
1085  if (!scanner()->has_invalid_template_escape()) return true;
1086 
1087  // Handle error case(s)
1088  if (should_throw) {
1089  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->invalid_template_escape_location(),
1090  scanner()->invalid_template_escape_message());
1091  }
1092  scanner()->clear_invalid_template_escape_message();
1093  return should_throw;
1094  }

1101  // Checking the name of a function literal. This has to be done after parsing
1102  // the function, since the function can declare itself strict.
1103  void CheckFunctionName(LanguageMode language_mode, IdentifierT function_name,
1104  FunctionNameValidity function_name_validity,
1105  const Scanner::Location& function_name_loc) {
1106  if (impl()->IsNull(function_name)) return;
1107  if (function_name_validity == kSkipFunctionNameCheck) return;
1108  // The function name needs to be checked in strict mode.
1109  if (is_sloppy(language_mode)) return;
1110 
1111  if (impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(function_name)) {
1112  impl()->ReportMessageAt(function_name_loc,
1113  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
1114  return;
1115  }
1116  if (function_name_validity == kFunctionNameIsStrictReserved) {
1117  impl()->ReportMessageAt(function_name_loc,
1118  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedStrictReserved);
1119  return;
1120  }
1121  }

1133  bool is_generator() const {
1134  return IsGeneratorFunction(function_state_->kind());
1135  }
1136  bool is_async_function() const {
1137  return IsAsyncFunction(function_state_->kind());
1138  }
1139  bool is_async_generator() const {
1140  return IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_state_->kind());
1141  }
1142  bool is_resumable() const {
1143  return IsResumableFunction(function_state_->kind());
1144  }
1145  bool is_await_allowed() const {
1146  return is_async_function() || IsModule(function_state_->kind());
1147  }
1148  bool is_await_as_identifier_disallowed() const {
1149  return flags().is_module() ||
1150  IsAwaitAsIdentifierDisallowed(function_state_->kind());
1151  }
1152  bool IsAwaitAsIdentifierDisallowed(FunctionKind kind) const {
1153  // 'await' is always disallowed as an identifier in module contexts. Callers
1154  // should short-circuit the module case instead of calling this.
1155  //
1156  // There is one special case: direct eval inside a module. In that case,
1157  // even though the eval script itself is parsed as a Script (not a Module,
1158  // i.e. flags().is_module() is false), thus allowing await as an identifier
1159  // by default, the immediate outer scope is a module scope.
1160  DCHECK(!IsModule(kind) ||
1161  (flags().is_eval() && function_state_->scope() == original_scope_ &&
1162  IsModule(function_state_->kind())));
1163  return IsAsyncFunction(kind) ||
1164  kind == FunctionKind::kClassStaticInitializerFunction;
1165  }
1166  bool is_using_allowed() const {
1167  // UsingDeclaration and AwaitUsingDeclaration are Syntax Errors if the goal
1168  // symbol is Script. UsingDeclaration and AwaitUsingDeclaration are Syntax
1169  // Errors if they are not contained, either directly or indirectly, within a
1170  // Block, ForStatement, ForInOfStatement, FunctionBody, GeneratorBody,
1171  // AsyncGeneratorBody, AsyncFunctionBody, ClassStaticBlockBody, or
1172  // ClassBody. They are disallowed in 'bare' switch cases.
1173  // Unless the current scope's ScopeType is ScriptScope, the
1174  // current position is directly or indirectly within one of the productions
1175  // listed above since they open a new scope.
1176  return (((scope()->scope_type() != SCRIPT_SCOPE &&
1177  scope()->scope_type() != EVAL_SCOPE) ||
1178  scope()->scope_type() == REPL_MODE_SCOPE) &&
1179  !scope()->is_nonlinear());
1180  }
1181  bool IsNextUsingKeyword(bool is_await_using) {
1182  // using and await using declarations in for-of statements must be followed
1183  // by a non-pattern ForBinding.
1184  //
1185  // `of`: for ( [lookahead ≠ using of] ForDeclaration[?Yield, ?Await, +Using]
1186  // of AssignmentExpression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await] )
1187  //
1188  // If `using` is not considered a keyword, it is parsed as an identifier.
1189  Token::Value token_after_using =
1190  is_await_using ? PeekAheadAhead() : PeekAhead();
1191  if (v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management) {
1192  switch (token_after_using) {
1193  case Token::kIdentifier:
1194  case Token::kStatic:
1195  case Token::kLet:
1196  case Token::kYield:
1197  case Token::kAwait:
1198  case Token::kGet:
1199  case Token::kSet:
1200  case Token::kUsing:
1201  case Token::kAccessor:
1202  case Token::kAsync:
1203  return true;
1204  case Token::kOf:
1205  if (is_await_using) {
1206  return true;
1207  } else {
1208  // In the case of synchronous `using`, `of` is disallowed as well
1209  // with a negative lookahead for for-of loops. But, cursedly,
1210  // `using of` is allowed as the initializer of C-style for loops,
1211  // e.g. `for (using of = null;;)` parses.
1212  Token::Value token_after_of = PeekAheadAhead();
1213  return token_after_of == Token::kAssign;
1214  }
1215  case Token::kFutureStrictReservedWord:
1216  case Token::kEscapedStrictReservedWord:
1217  return is_sloppy(language_mode());
1218  default:
1219  return false;
1220  }
1221  } else {
1222  return false;
1223  }
1224  }
1225  bool IfStartsWithUsingOrAwaitUsingKeyword() {
1226  // ForDeclaration[Yield, Await, Using] : ...
1227  // [+Using] using [no LineTerminator here] ForBinding[?Yield, ?Await,
1228  // ~Pattern]
1229  // [+Using, +Await] await [no LineTerminator here] using [no
1230  // LineTerminator here] ForBinding[?Yield, +Await, ~Pattern]
1231  return ((peek() == Token::kUsing &&
1232  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext() &&
1233  IsNextUsingKeyword(/* is_await_using */ false)) ||
1234  (is_await_allowed() && peek() == Token::kAwait &&
1235  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext() &&
1236  PeekAhead() == Token::kUsing &&
1237  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNextNext() &&
1238  IsNextUsingKeyword(/* is_await_using */ true)));
1239  }

1241  return pending_error_handler_;
1242  }
1243  PendingCompilationErrorHandler* pending_error_handler() {
1244  return pending_error_handler_;
1245  }

1270  void ValidateFormalParameters(LanguageMode language_mode,
1271  const FormalParametersT& parameters,
1272  bool allow_duplicates) {

1277  // Needs to be called if the reference needs to be available from the current
1278  // point. It causes the receiver to be context allocated if necessary.
1279  // Returns the receiver variable that we're referencing.
1280  V8_INLINE void UseThis() {
1281  Scope* scope = this->scope();
1282  DeclarationScope* closure_scope = scope->GetClosureScope();
1283  if (closure_scope->is_reparsed()) return;
1284  DeclarationScope* receiver_scope = closure_scope->GetReceiverScope();
1285  Variable* var = receiver_scope->receiver();
1286  var->set_is_used();
1287  if (closure_scope == receiver_scope) {
1288  // It's possible that we're parsing the head of an arrow function, in
1289  // which case we haven't realized yet that closure_scope !=
1290  // receiver_scope. Mark through the ExpressionScope for now.
1291  expression_scope()->RecordThisUse();
1292  } else {
1293  closure_scope->set_has_this_reference();
1294  var->ForceContextAllocation();
1295  }
1296  }

1463  // Check if the scope has conflicting var/let declarations from different
1464  // scopes. This covers for example
1465  //
1466  // function f() { { { var x; } let x; } }
1467  // function g() { { var x; let x; } }
1468  //
1469  // The var declarations are hoisted to the function scope, but originate from
1470  // a scope where the name has also been let bound or the var declaration is
1471  // hoisted over such a scope.
1472  void CheckConflictingVarDeclarations(DeclarationScope* scope) {
1473  bool allowed_catch_binding_var_redeclaration = false;
1474  Declaration* decl = scope->CheckConflictingVarDeclarations(
1475  &allowed_catch_binding_var_redeclaration);
1476  if (allowed_catch_binding_var_redeclaration) {
1477  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kVarRedeclaredCatchBinding);
1478  }
1479  if (decl != nullptr) {
1480  // In ES6, conflicting variable bindings are early errors.
1481  const AstRawString* name = decl->var()->raw_name();
1482  int position = decl->position();
1483  Scanner::Location location =
1484  position == kNoSourcePosition
1485  ? Scanner::Location::invalid()
1486  : Scanner::Location(position, position + 1);
1487  impl()->ReportMessageAt(location, MessageTemplate::kVarRedeclaration,
1488  name);
1489  }
1490  }

1585  bool IsAssignableIdentifier(ExpressionT expression) {
1586  if (!impl()->IsIdentifier(expression)) return false;
1587  if (is_strict(language_mode()) &&

1594  enum SubFunctionKind { kFunction, kNonStaticMethod, kStaticMethod };
1595 
1596  FunctionKind FunctionKindForImpl(SubFunctionKind sub_function_kind,
1597  ParseFunctionFlags flags) {
1598  static const FunctionKind kFunctionKinds[][2][2] = {
1599  {
1600  // SubFunctionKind::kNormalFunction
1601  {// is_generator=false
1602  FunctionKind::kNormalFunction, FunctionKind::kAsyncFunction},
1603  {// is_generator=true
1604  FunctionKind::kGeneratorFunction,
1605  FunctionKind::kAsyncGeneratorFunction},
1606  },
1607  {
1608  // SubFunctionKind::kNonStaticMethod
1609  {// is_generator=false
1610  FunctionKind::kConciseMethod, FunctionKind::kAsyncConciseMethod},
1611  {// is_generator=true
1612  FunctionKind::kConciseGeneratorMethod,
1613  FunctionKind::kAsyncConciseGeneratorMethod},
1614  },
1615  {
1616  // SubFunctionKind::kStaticMethod
1617  {// is_generator=false
1618  FunctionKind::kStaticConciseMethod,
1619  FunctionKind::kStaticAsyncConciseMethod},
1620  {// is_generator=true
1621  FunctionKind::kStaticConciseGeneratorMethod,
1622  FunctionKind::kStaticAsyncConciseGeneratorMethod},
1623  }};
1624  return kFunctionKinds[sub_function_kind]
1625  [(flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator) != 0]
1626  [(flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync) != 0];
1627  }
1628 
1629  inline FunctionKind FunctionKindFor(ParseFunctionFlags flags) {
1630  return FunctionKindForImpl(SubFunctionKind::kFunction, flags);
1631  }
1632 
1633  inline FunctionKind MethodKindFor(bool is_static, ParseFunctionFlags flags) {
1634  return FunctionKindForImpl(is_static ? SubFunctionKind::kStaticMethod
1635  : SubFunctionKind::kNonStaticMethod,
1636  flags);
1637  }

1639  // Keep track of eval() calls since they disable all local variable
1640  // optimizations. This checks if expression is an eval call, and if yes,
1641  // forwards the information to scope.
1642  bool CheckPossibleEvalCall(ExpressionT expression, bool is_optional_call,
1643  Scope* scope) {
1644  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(expression) &&
1645  impl()->IsEval(impl()->AsIdentifier(expression)) && !is_optional_call) {
1646  function_state_->RecordFunctionOrEvalCall();
1647  scope->RecordEvalCall();
1648  return true;
1649  }
1650  return false;
1651  }
1652 
1653  // Convenience method which determines the type of return statement to emit
1654  // depending on the current function type.
1655  inline StatementT BuildReturnStatement(
1656  ExpressionT expr, int pos,
1657  int end_pos = ReturnStatement::kFunctionLiteralReturnPosition) {
1658  if (impl()->IsNull(expr)) {
1659  expr = factory()->NewUndefinedLiteral(kNoSourcePosition);
1660  } else if (is_async_generator()) {
1661  // In async generators, if there is an explicit operand to the return
1662  // statement, await the operand.
1663  expr = factory()->NewAwait(expr, kNoSourcePosition);
1664  function_state_->AddSuspend();
1665  }
1666  if (is_async_function()) {
1667  return factory()->NewAsyncReturnStatement(expr, pos, end_pos);
1668  }
1669  return factory()->NewReturnStatement(expr, pos, end_pos);
1670  }

1773  // This struct is used to move information about the next arrow function from
1774  // the place where the arrow head was parsed to where the body will be parsed.
1775  // Nothing can be parsed between the head and the body, so it will be consumed
1776  // immediately after it's produced.
1777  // Preallocating the struct as part of the parser minimizes the cost of
1778  // supporting arrow functions on non-arrow expressions.
1779  struct NextArrowFunctionInfo {
1780  Scanner::Location strict_parameter_error_location =
1781  Scanner::Location::invalid();
1782  MessageTemplate strict_parameter_error_message = MessageTemplate::kNone;
1783  DeclarationScope* scope = nullptr;
1784  int function_literal_id = -1;
1785  bool could_be_immediately_invoked = false;
1786 
1787  bool HasInitialState() const { return scope == nullptr; }
1788 
1789  void Reset() {
1790  scope = nullptr;
1791  function_literal_id = -1;
1792  ClearStrictParameterError();
1793  could_be_immediately_invoked = false;
1794  DCHECK(HasInitialState());
1795  }
1796 
1797  // Tracks strict-mode parameter violations of sloppy-mode arrow heads in
1798  // case the function ends up becoming strict mode. Only one global place to
1799  // track this is necessary since arrow functions with none-simple parameters
1800  // cannot become strict-mode later on.
1801  void ClearStrictParameterError() {
1802  strict_parameter_error_location = Scanner::Location::invalid();
1803  strict_parameter_error_message = MessageTemplate::kNone;
1804  }
1805  };
1806 
1807  FormalParametersT* parameters_;
1808  NextArrowFunctionInfo next_arrow_function_info_;
1809 
1810  // The position of the token following the start parenthesis in the production
1811  // PrimaryExpression :: '(' Expression ')'
1812  int position_after_last_primary_expression_open_parenthesis_ = -1;
1813 
1814  bool accept_IN_ = true;
1815  bool allow_eval_cache_ = true;
1816 };

1819 ParserBase<Impl>::FunctionState::FunctionState(
1820  FunctionState** function_state_stack, Scope** scope_stack,
1821  DeclarationScope* scope)
1822  : BlockState(scope_stack, scope),
1823  expected_property_count_(0),
1824  suspend_count_(0),
1825  function_state_stack_(function_state_stack),
1826  outer_function_state_(*function_state_stack),
1827  scope_(scope),
1828  dont_optimize_reason_(BailoutReason::kNoReason),
1829  next_function_is_likely_called_(false),
1830  previous_function_was_likely_called_(false),
1831  contains_function_or_eval_(false) {
1832  *function_state_stack = this;
1833  if (outer_function_state_) {
1834  outer_function_state_->previous_function_was_likely_called_ =
1835  outer_function_state_->next_function_is_likely_called_;
1836  outer_function_state_->next_function_is_likely_called_ = false;
1837  }
1838 }

1845 template <typename Impl>
1846 void ParserBase<Impl>::ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::Value token) {
1847  return impl()->ReportUnexpectedTokenAt(scanner_->location(), token);
1848 }
1849 
1850 template <typename Impl>
1851 bool ParserBase<Impl>::ClassifyPropertyIdentifier(
1852  Token::Value next, ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info) {
1853  // Updates made here must be reflected on ParseAndClassifyIdentifier.
1854  if (V8_LIKELY(base::IsInRange(next, Token::kIdentifier, Token::kAsync))) {
1855  if (V8_UNLIKELY(impl()->IsArguments(prop_info->name) &&
1856  scope()->ShouldBanArguments())) {
1857  ReportMessage(
1858  MessageTemplate::kArgumentsDisallowedInInitializerAndStaticBlock);
1859  return false;
1860  }
1861  return true;
1862  }
1863 
1864  if (!Token::IsValidIdentifier(next, language_mode(), is_generator(),
1865  is_await_as_identifier_disallowed())) {
1866  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
1867  return false;
1868  }
1869 
1870  DCHECK(!prop_info->is_computed_name);
1871 
1872  if (next == Token::kAwait) {
1873  DCHECK(!is_async_function());
1874  expression_scope()->RecordAsyncArrowParametersError(
1875  scanner()->peek_location(), MessageTemplate::kAwaitBindingIdentifier);
1876  }
1877  return true;
1878 }
1879 
1880 template <typename Impl>
1881 typename ParserBase<Impl>::IdentifierT
1882 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(Token::Value next) {
1883  // Updates made here must be reflected on ClassifyPropertyIdentifier.
1884  DCHECK_EQ(scanner()->current_token(), next);
1885  if (V8_LIKELY(base::IsInRange(next, Token::kIdentifier, Token::kAsync))) {
1886  IdentifierT name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
1887  if (V8_UNLIKELY(impl()->IsArguments(name) &&
1888  scope()->ShouldBanArguments())) {
1889  ReportMessage(
1890  MessageTemplate::kArgumentsDisallowedInInitializerAndStaticBlock);
1891  return impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
1892  }
1893  return name;
1894  }
1895 
1896  if (!Token::IsValidIdentifier(next, language_mode(), is_generator(),
1897  is_await_as_identifier_disallowed())) {
1898  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
1899  return impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
1900  }
1901 
1902  if (next == Token::kAwait) {
1903  expression_scope()->RecordAsyncArrowParametersError(
1904  scanner()->location(), MessageTemplate::kAwaitBindingIdentifier);
1905  return impl()->GetIdentifier();
1906  }
1907 
1908  DCHECK(Token::IsStrictReservedWord(next));
1909  expression_scope()->RecordStrictModeParameterError(
1910  scanner()->location(), MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedStrictReserved);
1911  return impl()->GetIdentifier();
1912 }
1913 
1914 template <class Impl>
1915 typename ParserBase<Impl>::IdentifierT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseIdentifier(
1916  FunctionKind function_kind) {
1917  Token::Value next = Next();
1918 
1919  if (!Token::IsValidIdentifier(
1920  next, language_mode(), IsGeneratorFunction(function_kind),
1921  flags().is_module() ||
1922  IsAwaitAsIdentifierDisallowed(function_kind))) {
1923  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
1924  return impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
1925  }
1926 
1927  return impl()->GetIdentifier();
1928 }
1929 
1930 template <typename Impl>
1931 typename ParserBase<Impl>::IdentifierT
1932 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseNonRestrictedIdentifier() {
1933  IdentifierT result = ParseIdentifier();
1934 
1935  if (is_strict(language_mode()) &&
1936  V8_UNLIKELY(impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(result))) {
1937  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
1938  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
1939  }
1940 
1941  return result;
1942 }

1944 template <typename Impl>
1945 typename ParserBase<Impl>::IdentifierT ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePropertyName() {
1946  Token::Value next = Next();
1947  if (V8_LIKELY(Token::IsPropertyName(next))) {
1948  if (peek() == Token::kColon) return impl()->GetSymbol();
1949  return impl()->GetIdentifier();
1950  }
1951 
1952  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
1953  return impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
1954 }
1955 
1956 template <typename Impl>
1957 bool ParserBase<Impl>::IsExtraordinaryPrivateNameAccessAllowed() const {
1958  if (flags().parsing_while_debugging() != ParsingWhileDebugging::kYes &&
1959  !flags().is_repl_mode()) {
1960  return false;
1961  }
1962  Scope* current_scope = scope();
1963  while (current_scope != nullptr) {
1964  switch (current_scope->scope_type()) {
1965  case CLASS_SCOPE:
1966  case CATCH_SCOPE:
1967  case BLOCK_SCOPE:
1968  case WITH_SCOPE:
1969  case SHADOW_REALM_SCOPE:
1970  return false;
1971  // Top-level scopes.
1972  case REPL_MODE_SCOPE:
1973  case SCRIPT_SCOPE:
1974  case MODULE_SCOPE:
1975  return true;
1976  // Top-level wrapper function scopes.
1977  case FUNCTION_SCOPE:
1978  return info_id_ == kFunctionLiteralIdTopLevel;
1979  // Used by debug-evaluate. If the outer scope is top-level,
1980  // extraordinary private name access is allowed.
1981  case EVAL_SCOPE:
1982  current_scope = current_scope->outer_scope();
1983  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_scope);
1984  break;
1985  }
1986  }
1987  UNREACHABLE();
1988 }
1989 
1990 template <typename Impl>
1991 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
1992 ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePropertyOrPrivatePropertyName() {
1993  int pos = position();
1994  IdentifierT name;
1995  ExpressionT key;
1996  Token::Value next = Next();
1997  if (V8_LIKELY(Token::IsPropertyName(next))) {
1998  name = impl()->GetSymbol();
1999  key = factory()->NewStringLiteral(name, pos);
2000  } else if (next == Token::kPrivateName) {
2001  // In the case of a top level function, we completely skip
2002  // analysing it's scope, meaning, we don't have a chance to
2003  // resolve private names and find that they are not enclosed in a
2004  // class body.
2005  //
2006  // Here, we check if this is a new private name reference in a top
2007  // level function and throw an error if so.
2008  PrivateNameScopeIterator private_name_scope_iter(scope());
2009  // Parse the identifier so that we can display it in the error message
2010  name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2011  // In debug-evaluate, we relax the private name resolution to enable
2012  // evaluation of obj.#member outside the class bodies in top-level scopes.
2013  if (private_name_scope_iter.Done() &&
2014  !IsExtraordinaryPrivateNameAccessAllowed()) {
2015  impl()->ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(pos, pos + 1),
2016  MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateFieldResolution,
2017  impl()->GetRawNameFromIdentifier(name));
2018  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2019  }
2020  key =
2021  impl()->ExpressionFromPrivateName(&private_name_scope_iter, name, pos);
2022  } else {
2023  ReportUnexpectedToken(next);
2024  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2025  }
2026  impl()->PushLiteralName(name);
2027  return key;
2028 }
2029 
2030 template <typename Impl>
2031 bool ParserBase<Impl>::ValidateRegExpFlags(RegExpFlags flags) {
2032  return RegExp::VerifyFlags(flags);
2033 }
2034 
2035 template <typename Impl>
2036 bool ParserBase<Impl>::ValidateRegExpLiteral(const AstRawString* pattern,
2037  RegExpFlags flags,
2038  RegExpError* regexp_error) {
2039  // TODO(jgruber): If already validated in the preparser, skip validation in
2040  // the parser.
2041  DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2042  ZoneScope zone_scope(zone()); // Free regexp parser memory after use.
2043  const unsigned char* d = pattern->raw_data();
2044  if (pattern->is_one_byte()) {
2045  return RegExp::VerifySyntax(zone(), stack_limit(),
2046  static_cast<const uint8_t*>(d),
2047  pattern->length(), flags, regexp_error, no_gc);
2048  } else {
2049  return RegExp::VerifySyntax(zone(), stack_limit(),
2050  reinterpret_cast<const uint16_t*>(d),
2051  pattern->length(), flags, regexp_error, no_gc);
2052  }
2053 }
2054 
2055 template <typename Impl>
2056 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseRegExpLiteral() {
2057  int pos = peek_position();
2058  if (!scanner()->ScanRegExpPattern()) {
2059  Next();
2060  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kUnterminatedRegExp);
2061  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2062  }
2063 
2064  const AstRawString* pattern = GetNextSymbolForRegExpLiteral();
2065  std::optional<RegExpFlags> flags = scanner()->ScanRegExpFlags();
2066  const AstRawString* flags_as_ast_raw_string = GetNextSymbolForRegExpLiteral();
2067  if (!flags.has_value() || !ValidateRegExpFlags(flags.value())) {
2068  Next();
2069  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kMalformedRegExpFlags);
2070  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2071  }
2072  Next();
2073  RegExpError regexp_error;
2074  if (!ValidateRegExpLiteral(pattern, flags.value(), &regexp_error)) {
2075  if (RegExpErrorIsStackOverflow(regexp_error)) set_stack_overflow();
2076  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kMalformedRegExp, pattern,
2077  flags_as_ast_raw_string, RegExpErrorString(regexp_error));
2078  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2079  }
2080  return factory()->NewRegExpLiteral(pattern, flags.value(), pos);
2081 }
2082 
2083 template <typename Impl>
2084 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBindingPattern() {
2085  // Pattern ::
2086  // Identifier
2087  // ArrayLiteral
2088  // ObjectLiteral
2089 
2090  int beg_pos = peek_position();
2091  Token::Value token = peek();
2092  ExpressionT result;
2093 
2094  if (Token::IsAnyIdentifier(token)) {
2095  IdentifierT name = ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(Next());
2096  if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_strict(language_mode()) &&
2097  impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(name))) {
2098  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
2099  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
2100  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2101  }
2102  return impl()->ExpressionFromIdentifier(name, beg_pos);
2103  }
2104 
2105  CheckStackOverflow();
2106 
2107  if (token == Token::kLeftBracket) {
2108  result = ParseArrayLiteral();
2109  } else if (token == Token::kLeftBrace) {
2110  result = ParseObjectLiteral();
2111  } else {
2112  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
2113  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2114  }
2115 
2116  return result;
2117 }
2118 
2119 template <typename Impl>
2120 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
2121 ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePrimaryExpression() {
2122  CheckStackOverflow();
2123 
2124  // PrimaryExpression ::
2125  // 'this'
2126  // 'null'
2127  // 'true'
2128  // 'false'
2129  // Identifier
2130  // Number
2131  // String
2132  // ArrayLiteral
2133  // ObjectLiteral
2134  // RegExpLiteral
2135  // ClassLiteral
2136  // '(' Expression ')'
2137  // TemplateLiteral
2138  // do Block
2139  // AsyncFunctionLiteral
2140 
2141  int beg_pos = peek_position();
2142  Token::Value token = peek();
2143 
2144  if (Token::IsAnyIdentifier(token)) {
2145  Consume(token);
2146 
2147  FunctionKind kind = FunctionKind::kArrowFunction;
2148 
2149  if (V8_UNLIKELY(token == Token::kAsync &&
2150  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() &&
2151  !scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
2152  // async function ...
2153  if (peek() == Token::kFunction) return ParseAsyncFunctionLiteral();
2154 
2155  // async Identifier => ...
2156  if (peek_any_identifier() && PeekAhead() == Token::kArrow) {
2157  token = Next();
2158  beg_pos = position();
2159  kind = FunctionKind::kAsyncArrowFunction;
2160  }
2161  }
2162 
2163  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kArrow)) {
2164  ArrowHeadParsingScope parsing_scope(impl(), kind, PeekNextInfoId());
2165  IdentifierT name = ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(token);
2166  ClassifyParameter(name, beg_pos, end_position());
2167  ExpressionT result =
2168  impl()->ExpressionFromIdentifier(name, beg_pos, InferName::kNo);
2169  parsing_scope.SetInitializers(0, peek_position());
2170  next_arrow_function_info_.scope = parsing_scope.ValidateAndCreateScope();
2171  next_arrow_function_info_.function_literal_id =
2172  parsing_scope.function_literal_id();
2173  next_arrow_function_info_.could_be_immediately_invoked =
2174  position_after_last_primary_expression_open_parenthesis_ == beg_pos;
2175  return result;
2176  }
2177 
2178  IdentifierT name = ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(token);
2179  return impl()->ExpressionFromIdentifier(name, beg_pos);
2180  }
2181 
2182  if (Token::IsLiteral(token)) {
2183  return impl()->ExpressionFromLiteral(Next(), beg_pos);
2184  }
2185 
2186  switch (token) {
2187  case Token::kNew:
2188  return ParseMemberWithPresentNewPrefixesExpression();
2189 
2190  case Token::kThis: {
2191  Consume(Token::kThis);
2192  // Not necessary for this.x, this.x(), this?.x and this?.x() to
2193  // store the source position for ThisExpression.
2194  if (peek() == Token::kPeriod || peek() == Token::kQuestionPeriod) {
2195  return impl()->ThisExpression();
2196  }
2197  return impl()->NewThisExpression(beg_pos);
2198  }
2199 
2200  case Token::kAssignDiv:
2201  case Token::kDiv:
2202  return ParseRegExpLiteral();
2203 
2204  case Token::kFunction:
2205  return ParseFunctionExpression();
2206 
2207  case Token::kSuper: {
2208  return ParseSuperExpression();
2209  }
2210  case Token::kImport:
2211  return ParseImportExpressions();
2212 
2213  case Token::kLeftBracket:
2214  return ParseArrayLiteral();
2215 
2216  case Token::kLeftBrace:
2217  return ParseObjectLiteral();
2218 
2219  case Token::kLeftParen: {
2220  Consume(Token::kLeftParen);
2221 
2222  if (Check(Token::kRightParen)) {
2223  // clear last next_arrow_function_info tracked strict parameters error.
2224  next_arrow_function_info_.ClearStrictParameterError();
2225 
2226  // ()=>x. The continuation that consumes the => is in
2227  // ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar.
2228  if (peek() != Token::kArrow) ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kRightParen);
2229  next_arrow_function_info_.scope =
2230  NewFunctionScope(FunctionKind::kArrowFunction);
2231  next_arrow_function_info_.function_literal_id = PeekNextInfoId();
2232  next_arrow_function_info_.could_be_immediately_invoked =
2233  position_after_last_primary_expression_open_parenthesis_ == beg_pos;
2234  return factory()->NewEmptyParentheses(beg_pos);
2235  }
2236  Scope::Snapshot scope_snapshot(scope());
2237  bool could_be_immediately_invoked_arrow_function =
2238  position_after_last_primary_expression_open_parenthesis_ == beg_pos;
2239  ArrowHeadParsingScope maybe_arrow(impl(), FunctionKind::kArrowFunction,
2240  PeekNextInfoId());
2241  position_after_last_primary_expression_open_parenthesis_ =
2242  peek_position();
2243  // Heuristically try to detect immediately called functions before
2244  // seeing the call parentheses.
2245  if (peek() == Token::kFunction ||
2246  (peek() == Token::kAsync && PeekAhead() == Token::kFunction)) {
2247  function_state_->set_next_function_is_likely_called();
2248  }
2249  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2250  ExpressionT expr = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
2251  expr->mark_parenthesized();
2252  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
2253 
2254  if (peek() == Token::kArrow) {
2255  next_arrow_function_info_.scope = maybe_arrow.ValidateAndCreateScope();
2256  next_arrow_function_info_.function_literal_id =
2257  maybe_arrow.function_literal_id();
2258  next_arrow_function_info_.could_be_immediately_invoked =
2259  could_be_immediately_invoked_arrow_function;
2260  scope_snapshot.Reparent(next_arrow_function_info_.scope);
2261  } else {
2262  maybe_arrow.ValidateExpression();
2263  }
2264 
2265  return expr;
2266  }
2267 
2268  case Token::kClass: {
2269  return ParseClassExpression(scope());
2270  }
2271 
2272  case Token::kTemplateSpan:
2273  case Token::kTemplateTail:
2274  return ParseTemplateLiteral(impl()->NullExpression(), beg_pos, false);
2275 
2276  case Token::kMod:
2277  if (flags().allow_natives_syntax() || impl()->ParsingExtension()) {
2278  return ParseV8Intrinsic();
2279  }
2280  break;
2281 
2282  default:
2283  break;
2284  }
2285 
2286  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
2287  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2288 }
2289 
2290 template <typename Impl>
2291 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseExpression() {
2292  ExpressionParsingScope expression_scope(impl());
2293  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2294  ExpressionT result = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
2295  expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
2296  return result;
2297 }

2299 template <typename Impl>
2300 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
2301 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseConditionalChainAssignmentExpression() {
2302  ExpressionParsingScope expression_scope(impl());
2303  ExpressionT result = ParseConditionalChainAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
2304  expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
2305  return result;
2306 }
