2308 template <typename Impl>
2309 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
2310 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAssignmentExpression() {
2311  ExpressionParsingScope expression_scope(impl());
2312  ExpressionT result = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
2313  expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
2314  return result;
2315 }
2316 
2317 template <typename Impl>
2318 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
2319 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseExpressionCoverGrammar() {
2320  // Expression ::
2321  // AssignmentExpression
2322  // Expression ',' AssignmentExpression
2323 
2324  ExpressionListT list(pointer_buffer());
2325  ExpressionT expression;
2326  AccumulationScope accumulation_scope(expression_scope());
2327  int variable_index = 0;
2328  while (true) {
2329  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kEllipsis)) {
2330  return ParseArrowParametersWithRest(&list, &accumulation_scope,
2331  variable_index);
2332  }
2333 
2334  int expr_pos = peek_position();
2335  expression = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
2336 
2337  ClassifyArrowParameter(&accumulation_scope, expr_pos, expression);
2338  list.Add(expression);
2339 
2340  variable_index =
2341  expression_scope()->SetInitializers(variable_index, peek_position());
2342 
2343  if (!Check(Token::kComma)) break;
2344 
2345  if (peek() == Token::kRightParen && PeekAhead() == Token::kArrow) {
2346  // a trailing comma is allowed at the end of an arrow parameter list
2347  break;
2348  }
2349 
2350  // Pass on the 'set_next_function_is_likely_called' flag if we have
2351  // several function literals separated by comma.
2352  if (peek() == Token::kFunction &&
2353  function_state_->previous_function_was_likely_called()) {
2354  function_state_->set_next_function_is_likely_called();
2355  }
2356  }
2357 
2358  // Return the single element if the list is empty. We need to do this because
2359  // callers of this function care about the type of the result if there was
2360  // only a single assignment expression. The preparser would lose this
2361  // information otherwise.
2362  if (list.length() == 1) return expression;
2363  return impl()->ExpressionListToExpression(list);
2364 }
2365 
2366 template <typename Impl>
2367 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
2368 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseArrowParametersWithRest(
2369  typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionListT* list,
2370  AccumulationScope* accumulation_scope, int seen_variables) {
2371  Consume(Token::kEllipsis);
2372 
2373  Scanner::Location ellipsis = scanner()->location();
2374  int pattern_pos = peek_position();
2375  ExpressionT pattern = ParseBindingPattern();
2376  ClassifyArrowParameter(accumulation_scope, pattern_pos, pattern);
2377 
2378  expression_scope()->RecordNonSimpleParameter();
2379 
2380  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kAssign)) {
2381  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kRestDefaultInitializer);
2382  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2383  }
2384 
2385  ExpressionT spread =
2386  factory()->NewSpread(pattern, ellipsis.beg_pos, pattern_pos);
2387  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kComma)) {
2388  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kParamAfterRest);
2389  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2390  }
2391 
2392  expression_scope()->SetInitializers(seen_variables, peek_position());
2393 
2394  // 'x, y, ...z' in CoverParenthesizedExpressionAndArrowParameterList only
2395  // as the formal parameters of'(x, y, ...z) => foo', and is not itself a
2396  // valid expression.
2397  if (peek() != Token::kRightParen || PeekAhead() != Token::kArrow) {
2398  impl()->ReportUnexpectedTokenAt(ellipsis, Token::kEllipsis);
2399  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2400  }
2401 
2402  list->Add(spread);
2403  return impl()->ExpressionListToExpression(*list);
2404 }
2405 
2406 template <typename Impl>
2407 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseArrayLiteral() {
2408  // ArrayLiteral ::
2409  // '[' Expression? (',' Expression?)* ']'
2410 
2411  int pos = peek_position();
2412  ExpressionListT values(pointer_buffer());
2413  int first_spread_index = -1;
2414  Consume(Token::kLeftBracket);
2415 
2416  AccumulationScope accumulation_scope(expression_scope());
2417 
2418  while (!Check(Token::kRightBracket)) {
2419  ExpressionT elem;
2420  if (peek() == Token::kComma) {
2421  elem = factory()->NewTheHoleLiteral();
2422  } else if (Check(Token::kEllipsis)) {
2423  int start_pos = position();
2424  int expr_pos = peek_position();
2425  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2426  ExpressionT argument =
2427  ParsePossibleDestructuringSubPattern(&accumulation_scope);
2428  elem = factory()->NewSpread(argument, start_pos, expr_pos);
2429 
2430  if (first_spread_index < 0) {
2431  first_spread_index = values.length();
2432  }
2433 
2434  if (argument->IsAssignment()) {
2435  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2436  Scanner::Location(start_pos, end_position()),
2437  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
2438  }
2439 
2440  if (peek() == Token::kComma) {
2441  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2442  Scanner::Location(start_pos, end_position()),
2443  MessageTemplate::kElementAfterRest);
2444  }
2445  } else {
2446  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2447  elem = ParsePossibleDestructuringSubPattern(&accumulation_scope);
2448  }
2449  values.Add(elem);
2450  if (peek() != Token::kRightBracket) {
2451  Expect(Token::kComma);
2452  if (elem->IsFailureExpression()) return elem;
2453  }
2454  }
2455 
2456  return factory()->NewArrayLiteral(values, first_spread_index, pos);
2457 }
2458 
2459 template <class Impl>
2460 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseProperty(
2461  ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info) {
2462  DCHECK_EQ(prop_info->kind, ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet);
2463  DCHECK_EQ(prop_info->function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
2464  DCHECK(!prop_info->is_computed_name);
2465 
2466  if (Check(Token::kAsync)) {
2467  Token::Value token = peek();
2468  if ((token != Token::kMul &&
2469  prop_info->ParsePropertyKindFromToken(token)) ||
2470  scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext()) {
2471  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2472  impl()->PushLiteralName(prop_info->name);
2473  return factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, position());
2474  }
2475  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
2476  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
2477  }
2478  prop_info->function_flags = ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync;
2479  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kMethod;
2480  }
2481 
2482  if (Check(Token::kMul)) {
2483  prop_info->function_flags |= ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator;
2484  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kMethod;
2485  }
2486 
2487  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet &&
2488  base::IsInRange(peek(), Token::kGet, Token::kSet)) {
2489  Token::Value token = Next();
2490  if (prop_info->ParsePropertyKindFromToken(peek())) {
2491  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2492  impl()->PushLiteralName(prop_info->name);
2493  return factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, position());
2494  }
2495  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
2496  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
2497  }
2498  if (token == Token::kGet) {
2499  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter;
2500  } else if (token == Token::kSet) {
2501  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorSetter;
2502  }
2503  }
2504 
2505  int pos = peek_position();
2506 
2507  // For non computed property names we normalize the name a bit:
2508  //
2509  // "12" -> 12
2510  // 12.3 -> "12.3"
2511  // 12.30 -> "12.3"
2512  // identifier -> "identifier"
2513  //
2514  // This is important because we use the property name as a key in a hash
2515  // table when we compute constant properties.
2516  bool is_array_index;
2517  uint32_t index;
2518  switch (peek()) {
2519  case Token::kPrivateName:
2520  prop_info->is_private = true;
2521  is_array_index = false;
2522  Consume(Token::kPrivateName);
2523  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet) {
2524  prop_info->ParsePropertyKindFromToken(peek());
2525  }
2526  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2527  if (V8_UNLIKELY(prop_info->position ==
2528  PropertyPosition::kObjectLiteral)) {
2529  ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kPrivateName);
2530  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet;
2531  return impl()->FailureExpression();
2532  }
2533  break;
2534 
2535  case Token::kString:
2536  Consume(Token::kString);
2537  prop_info->name = peek() == Token::kColon ? impl()->GetSymbol()
2538  : impl()->GetIdentifier();
2539  is_array_index = impl()->IsArrayIndex(prop_info->name, &index);
2540  break;
2541 
2542  case Token::kSmi:
2543  Consume(Token::kSmi);
2544  index = scanner()->smi_value();
2545  is_array_index = true;
2546  // Token::kSmi were scanned from their canonical representation.
2547  prop_info->name = impl()->GetSymbol();
2548  break;
2549 
2550  case Token::kNumber: {
2551  Consume(Token::kNumber);
2552  prop_info->name = impl()->GetNumberAsSymbol();
2553  is_array_index = impl()->IsArrayIndex(prop_info->name, &index);
2554  break;
2555  }
2556 
2557  case Token::kBigInt: {
2558  Consume(Token::kBigInt);
2559  prop_info->name = impl()->GetBigIntAsSymbol();
2560  is_array_index = impl()->IsArrayIndex(prop_info->name, &index);
2561  break;
2562  }
2563 
2564  case Token::kLeftBracket: {
2565  prop_info->name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
2566  prop_info->is_computed_name = true;
2567  Consume(Token::kLeftBracket);
2568  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2569  ExpressionT expression = ParseAssignmentExpression();
2570  Expect(Token::kRightBracket);
2571  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet) {
2572  prop_info->ParsePropertyKindFromToken(peek());
2573  }
2574  return expression;
2575  }
2576 
2577  case Token::kEllipsis:
2578  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet) {
2579  prop_info->name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
2580  Consume(Token::kEllipsis);
2581  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2582  int start_pos = peek_position();
2583  ExpressionT expression =
2584  ParsePossibleDestructuringSubPattern(prop_info->accumulation_scope);
2585  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kSpread;
2586 
2587  if (!IsValidReferenceExpression(expression)) {
2588  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
2589  Scanner::Location(start_pos, end_position()),
2590  MessageTemplate::kInvalidRestBindingPattern);
2591  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2592  Scanner::Location(start_pos, end_position()),
2593  MessageTemplate::kInvalidRestAssignmentPattern);
2594  }
2595 
2596  if (peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
2597  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2598  scanner()->location(), MessageTemplate::kElementAfterRest);
2599  }
2600  return expression;
2601  }
2602  [[fallthrough]];
2603 
2604  default:
2605  prop_info->name = ParsePropertyName();
2606  is_array_index = false;
2607  break;
2608  }
2609 
2610  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet) {
2611  prop_info->ParsePropertyKindFromToken(peek());
2612  }
2613  impl()->PushLiteralName(prop_info->name);
2614  return is_array_index ? factory()->NewNumberLiteral(index, pos)
2615  : factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, pos);
2616 }
2617 
2618 template <typename Impl>
2619 bool ParserBase<Impl>::VerifyCanHaveAutoAccessorOrThrow(
2620  ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info, ExpressionT name_expression,
2621  int name_token_position) {
2622  switch (prop_info->kind) {
2623  case ParsePropertyKind::kAssign:
2624  case ParsePropertyKind::kClassField:
2625  case ParsePropertyKind::kShorthandOrClassField:
2626  case ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet:
2627  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kAutoAccessorClassField;
2628  return true;
2629  default:
2630  impl()->ReportUnexpectedTokenAt(
2631  Scanner::Location(name_token_position, name_expression->position()),
2632  Token::kAccessor);
2633  return false;
2634  }
2635 }
2636 
2637 template <typename Impl>
2638 bool ParserBase<Impl>::ParseCurrentSymbolAsClassFieldOrMethod(
2639  ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info, ExpressionT* name_expression) {
2640  if (peek() == Token::kLeftParen) {
2641  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kMethod;
2642  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2643  *name_expression = factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, position());
2644  return true;
2645  }
2646  if (peek() == Token::kAssign || peek() == Token::kSemicolon ||
2647  peek() == Token::kRightBrace) {
2648  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2649  *name_expression = factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, position());
2650  return true;
2651  }
2652  return false;
2653 }
2654 
2655 template <typename Impl>
2656 bool ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAccessorPropertyOrAutoAccessors(
2657  ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info, ExpressionT* name_expression,
2658  int* name_token_position) {
2659  // accessor [no LineTerminator here] ClassElementName[?Yield, ?Await]
2660  // Initializer[~In, ?Yield, ?Await]opt ;
2661  Consume(Token::kAccessor);
2662  *name_token_position = scanner()->peek_location().beg_pos;
2663  // If there is a line terminator here, it cannot be an auto-accessor.
2664  if (scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext()) {
2665  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kClassField;
2666  prop_info->name = impl()->GetIdentifier();
2667  *name_expression = factory()->NewStringLiteral(prop_info->name, position());
2668  return true;
2669  }
2670  if (ParseCurrentSymbolAsClassFieldOrMethod(prop_info, name_expression)) {
2671  return true;
2672  }
2673  *name_expression = ParseProperty(prop_info);
2674  return VerifyCanHaveAutoAccessorOrThrow(prop_info, *name_expression,
2675  *name_token_position);
2676 }
2677 
2678 template <typename Impl>
2679 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ClassLiteralPropertyT
2680 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassPropertyDefinition(ClassInfo* class_info,
2681  ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info,
2682  bool has_extends) {
2683  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(class_info);
2684  DCHECK_EQ(prop_info->position, PropertyPosition::kClassLiteral);
2685 
2686  int next_info_id = PeekNextInfoId();
2687 
2688  Token::Value name_token = peek();
2689  int property_beg_pos = peek_position();
2690  int name_token_position = property_beg_pos;
2691  ExpressionT name_expression;
2692  if (name_token == Token::kStatic) {
2693  Consume(Token::kStatic);
2694  name_token_position = scanner()->peek_location().beg_pos;
2695  if (!ParseCurrentSymbolAsClassFieldOrMethod(prop_info, &name_expression)) {
2696  prop_info->is_static = true;
2697  if (v8_flags.js_decorators && peek() == Token::kAccessor) {
2698  if (!ParseAccessorPropertyOrAutoAccessors(prop_info, &name_expression,
2699  &name_token_position)) {
2700  return impl()->NullLiteralProperty();
2701  }
2702  } else {
2703  name_expression = ParseProperty(prop_info);
2704  }
2705  }
2706  } else if (v8_flags.js_decorators && name_token == Token::kAccessor) {
2707  if (!ParseAccessorPropertyOrAutoAccessors(prop_info, &name_expression,
2708  &name_token_position)) {
2709  return impl()->NullLiteralProperty();
2710  }
2711  } else {
2712  name_expression = ParseProperty(prop_info);
2713  }
2714 
2715  switch (prop_info->kind) {
2716  case ParsePropertyKind::kAssign:
2717  case ParsePropertyKind::kAutoAccessorClassField:
2718  case ParsePropertyKind::kClassField:
2719  case ParsePropertyKind::kShorthandOrClassField:
2720  case ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet: { // This case is a name followed by a
2721  // name or other property. Here we have
2722  // to assume that's an uninitialized
2723  // field followed by a linebreak
2724  // followed by a property, with ASI
2725  // adding the semicolon. If not, there
2726  // will be a syntax error after parsing
2727  // the first name as an uninitialized
2728  // field.
2729  DCHECK_IMPLIES(prop_info->is_computed_name, !prop_info->is_private);
2730 
2731  if (prop_info->is_computed_name) {
2732  if (!has_error() && next_info_id != PeekNextInfoId() &&
2733  !(prop_info->is_static ? class_info->has_static_elements()
2734  : class_info->has_instance_members())) {
2735  impl()->ReindexComputedMemberName(name_expression);
2736  }
2737  } else {
2738  CheckClassFieldName(prop_info->name, prop_info->is_static);
2739  }
2740 
2741  ExpressionT value = ParseMemberInitializer(
2742  class_info, property_beg_pos, next_info_id, prop_info->is_static);
2743  ExpectSemicolon();
2744 
2745  ClassLiteralPropertyT result;
2746  if (prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kAutoAccessorClassField) {
2747  // Declare the auto-accessor synthetic getter and setter here where we
2748  // have access to the property position in parsing and preparsing.
2749  result = impl()->NewClassLiteralPropertyWithAccessorInfo(
2750  scope()->AsClassScope(), class_info, prop_info->name,
2751  name_expression, value, prop_info->is_static,
2752  prop_info->is_computed_name, prop_info->is_private,
2753  property_beg_pos);
2754  } else {
2755  prop_info->kind = ParsePropertyKind::kClassField;
2756  result = factory()->NewClassLiteralProperty(
2757  name_expression, value, ClassLiteralProperty::FIELD,
2758  prop_info->is_static, prop_info->is_computed_name,
2759  prop_info->is_private);
2760  }
2761  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, prop_info->name);
2762 
2763  return result;
2764  }
2765  case ParsePropertyKind::kMethod: {
2766  // MethodDefinition
2767  // PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
2768  // '*' PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
2769  // async PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')'
2770  // '{' FunctionBody '}'
2771  // async '*' PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')'
2772  // '{' FunctionBody '}'
2773 
2774  if (!prop_info->is_computed_name) {
2775  CheckClassMethodName(prop_info->name, ParsePropertyKind::kMethod,
2776  prop_info->function_flags, prop_info->is_static,
2777  &class_info->has_seen_constructor);
2778  }
2779 
2780  FunctionKind kind =
2781  MethodKindFor(prop_info->is_static, prop_info->function_flags);
2782 
2783  if (!prop_info->is_static && impl()->IsConstructor(prop_info->name)) {
2784  class_info->has_seen_constructor = true;
2785  kind = has_extends ? FunctionKind::kDerivedConstructor
2786  : FunctionKind::kBaseConstructor;
2787  }
2788 
2789  ExpressionT value = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
2790  prop_info->name, scanner()->location(), kSkipFunctionNameCheck, kind,
2791  name_token_position, FunctionSyntaxKind::kAccessorOrMethod,
2792  language_mode(), nullptr);
2793 
2794  ClassLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewClassLiteralProperty(
2795  name_expression, value, ClassLiteralProperty::METHOD,
2796  prop_info->is_static, prop_info->is_computed_name,
2797  prop_info->is_private);
2798  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, prop_info->name);
2799  return result;
2800  }
2801 
2802  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter:
2803  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorSetter: {
2804  DCHECK_EQ(prop_info->function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
2805  bool is_get = prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter;
2806 
2807  if (!prop_info->is_computed_name) {
2808  CheckClassMethodName(prop_info->name, prop_info->kind,
2809  ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal, prop_info->is_static,
2810  &class_info->has_seen_constructor);
2811  // Make sure the name expression is a string since we need a Name for
2812  // Runtime_DefineAccessorPropertyUnchecked and since we can determine
2813  // this statically we can skip the extra runtime check.
2814  name_expression = factory()->NewStringLiteral(
2815  prop_info->name, name_expression->position());
2816  }
2817 
2818  FunctionKind kind;
2819  if (prop_info->is_static) {
2820  kind = is_get ? FunctionKind::kStaticGetterFunction
2821  : FunctionKind::kStaticSetterFunction;
2822  } else {
2823  kind = is_get ? FunctionKind::kGetterFunction
2824  : FunctionKind::kSetterFunction;
2825  }
2826 
2827  FunctionLiteralT value = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
2828  prop_info->name, scanner()->location(), kSkipFunctionNameCheck, kind,
2829  name_token_position, FunctionSyntaxKind::kAccessorOrMethod,
2830  language_mode(), nullptr);
2831 
2832  ClassLiteralProperty::Kind property_kind =
2833  is_get ? ClassLiteralProperty::GETTER : ClassLiteralProperty::SETTER;
2834  ClassLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewClassLiteralProperty(
2835  name_expression, value, property_kind, prop_info->is_static,
2836  prop_info->is_computed_name, prop_info->is_private);
2837  const AstRawString* prefix =
2838  is_get ? ast_value_factory()->get_space_string()
2839  : ast_value_factory()->set_space_string();
2840  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, prop_info->name, prefix);
2841  return result;
2842  }
2843  case ParsePropertyKind::kValue:
2844  case ParsePropertyKind::kShorthand:
2845  case ParsePropertyKind::kSpread:
2846  impl()->ReportUnexpectedTokenAt(
2847  Scanner::Location(name_token_position, name_expression->position()),
2848  name_token);
2849  return impl()->NullLiteralProperty();
2850  }
2851  UNREACHABLE();
2852 }
2853 
2854 template <typename Impl>
2855 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseMemberInitializer(
2856  ClassInfo* class_info, int beg_pos, int info_id, bool is_static) {
2857  FunctionParsingScope body_parsing_scope(impl());
2858  DeclarationScope* initializer_scope =
2859  is_static
2860  ? class_info->EnsureStaticElementsScope(this, beg_pos, info_id)
2861  : class_info->EnsureInstanceMembersScope(this, beg_pos, info_id);
2862 
2863  if (Check(Token::kAssign)) {
2864  FunctionState initializer_state(&function_state_, &scope_,
2865  initializer_scope);
2866 
2867  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2868  auto result = ParseAssignmentExpression();
2869  initializer_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
2870  return result;
2871  }
2872  initializer_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
2873  return factory()->NewUndefinedLiteral(kNoSourcePosition);
2874 }
2875 
2876 template <typename Impl>
2877 typename ParserBase<Impl>::BlockT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassStaticBlock(
2878  ClassInfo* class_info) {
2879  Consume(Token::kStatic);
2880 
2881  DeclarationScope* initializer_scope =
2882  class_info->EnsureStaticElementsScope(this, position(), PeekNextInfoId());
2883 
2884  FunctionState initializer_state(&function_state_, &scope_, initializer_scope);
2885  FunctionParsingScope body_parsing_scope(impl());
2886  AcceptINScope accept_in(this, true);
2887 
2888  // Each static block has its own var and lexical scope, so make a new var
2889  // block scope instead of using the synthetic members initializer function
2890  // scope.
2891  DeclarationScope* static_block_var_scope = NewVarblockScope();
2892  BlockT static_block = ParseBlock(nullptr, static_block_var_scope);
2893  CheckConflictingVarDeclarations(static_block_var_scope);
2894  initializer_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
2895  return static_block;
2896 }
2897 
2898 template <typename Impl>
2899 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ObjectLiteralPropertyT
2900 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseObjectPropertyDefinition(ParsePropertyInfo* prop_info,
2901  bool* has_seen_proto) {
2902  DCHECK_EQ(prop_info->position, PropertyPosition::kObjectLiteral);
2903  Token::Value name_token = peek();
2904  Scanner::Location next_loc = scanner()->peek_location();
2905 
2906  ExpressionT name_expression = ParseProperty(prop_info);
2907 
2908  DCHECK_IMPLIES(name_token == Token::kPrivateName, has_error());
2909 
2910  IdentifierT name = prop_info->name;
2911  ParseFunctionFlags function_flags = prop_info->function_flags;
2912 
2913  switch (prop_info->kind) {
2914  case ParsePropertyKind::kSpread:
2915  DCHECK_EQ(function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
2916  DCHECK(!prop_info->is_computed_name);
2917  DCHECK_EQ(Token::kEllipsis, name_token);
2918 
2919  prop_info->is_computed_name = true;
2920  prop_info->is_rest = true;
2921 
2922  return factory()->NewObjectLiteralProperty(
2923  factory()->NewTheHoleLiteral(), name_expression,
2924  ObjectLiteralProperty::SPREAD, true);
2925 
2926  case ParsePropertyKind::kValue: {
2927  DCHECK_EQ(function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
2928 
2929  if (!prop_info->is_computed_name &&
2930  scanner()->CurrentLiteralEquals("__proto__")) {
2931  if (*has_seen_proto) {
2932  expression_scope()->RecordExpressionError(
2933  scanner()->location(), MessageTemplate::kDuplicateProto);
2934  }
2935  *has_seen_proto = true;
2936  }
2937  Consume(Token::kColon);
2938  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2939  ExpressionT value =
2940  ParsePossibleDestructuringSubPattern(prop_info->accumulation_scope);
2941 
2942  ObjectLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewObjectLiteralProperty(
2943  name_expression, value, prop_info->is_computed_name);
2944  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, name);
2945  return result;
2946  }
2947 
2948  case ParsePropertyKind::kAssign:
2949  case ParsePropertyKind::kShorthandOrClassField:
2950  case ParsePropertyKind::kShorthand: {
2951  // PropertyDefinition
2952  // IdentifierReference
2953  // CoverInitializedName
2954  //
2955  // CoverInitializedName
2956  // IdentifierReference Initializer?
2957  DCHECK_EQ(function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
2958 
2959  if (!ClassifyPropertyIdentifier(name_token, prop_info)) {
2960  return impl()->NullLiteralProperty();
2961  }
2962 
2963  ExpressionT lhs =
2964  impl()->ExpressionFromIdentifier(name, next_loc.beg_pos);
2965  if (!IsAssignableIdentifier(lhs)) {
2966  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2967  next_loc, MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
2968  }
2969 
2970  ExpressionT value;
2971  if (peek() == Token::kAssign) {
2972  Consume(Token::kAssign);
2973  {
2974  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
2975  ExpressionT rhs = ParseAssignmentExpression();
2976  value = factory()->NewAssignment(Token::kAssign, lhs, rhs,
2977  kNoSourcePosition);
2978  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromIdentifierRef(rhs, lhs);
2979  }
2980  expression_scope()->RecordExpressionError(
2981  Scanner::Location(next_loc.beg_pos, end_position()),
2982  MessageTemplate::kInvalidCoverInitializedName);
2983  } else {
2984  value = lhs;
2985  }
2986 
2987  ObjectLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewObjectLiteralProperty(
2988  name_expression, value, ObjectLiteralProperty::COMPUTED, false);
2989  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, name);
2990  return result;
2991  }
2992 
2993  case ParsePropertyKind::kMethod: {
2994  // MethodDefinition
2995  // PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
2996  // '*' PropertyName '(' StrictFormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
2997 
2998  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
2999  Scanner::Location(next_loc.beg_pos, end_position()),
3000  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
3001 
3002  std::unique_ptr<BlockState> block_state;
3003  if (object_literal_scope_ != nullptr) {
3004  DCHECK_EQ(object_literal_scope_->outer_scope(), scope_);
3005  block_state.reset(new BlockState(&scope_, object_literal_scope_));
3006  }
3007  constexpr bool kIsStatic = false;
3008  FunctionKind kind = MethodKindFor(kIsStatic, function_flags);
3009 
3010  ExpressionT value = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
3011  name, scanner()->location(), kSkipFunctionNameCheck, kind,
3012  next_loc.beg_pos, FunctionSyntaxKind::kAccessorOrMethod,
3013  language_mode(), nullptr);
3014 
3015  ObjectLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewObjectLiteralProperty(
3016  name_expression, value, ObjectLiteralProperty::COMPUTED,
3017  prop_info->is_computed_name);
3018  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, name);
3019  return result;
3020  }
3021 
3022  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter:
3023  case ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorSetter: {
3024  DCHECK_EQ(function_flags, ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal);
3025  bool is_get = prop_info->kind == ParsePropertyKind::kAccessorGetter;
3026 
3027  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
3028  Scanner::Location(next_loc.beg_pos, end_position()),
3029  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
3030 
3031  if (!prop_info->is_computed_name) {
3032  // Make sure the name expression is a string since we need a Name for
3033  // Runtime_DefineAccessorPropertyUnchecked and since we can determine
3034  // this statically we can skip the extra runtime check.
3035  name_expression =
3036  factory()->NewStringLiteral(name, name_expression->position());
3037  }
3038 
3039  std::unique_ptr<BlockState> block_state;
3040  if (object_literal_scope_ != nullptr) {
3041  DCHECK_EQ(object_literal_scope_->outer_scope(), scope_);
3042  block_state.reset(new BlockState(&scope_, object_literal_scope_));
3043  }
3044 
3045  FunctionKind kind = is_get ? FunctionKind::kGetterFunction
3046  : FunctionKind::kSetterFunction;
3047 
3048  FunctionLiteralT value = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
3049  name, scanner()->location(), kSkipFunctionNameCheck, kind,
3050  next_loc.beg_pos, FunctionSyntaxKind::kAccessorOrMethod,
3051  language_mode(), nullptr);
3052 
3053  ObjectLiteralPropertyT result = factory()->NewObjectLiteralProperty(
3054  name_expression, value,
3055  is_get ? ObjectLiteralProperty::GETTER
3056  : ObjectLiteralProperty::SETTER,
3057  prop_info->is_computed_name);
3058  const AstRawString* prefix =
3059  is_get ? ast_value_factory()->get_space_string()
3060  : ast_value_factory()->set_space_string();
3061  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromPropertyName(result, name, prefix);
3062  return result;
3063  }
3064 
3065  case ParsePropertyKind::kAutoAccessorClassField:
3066  case ParsePropertyKind::kClassField:
3067  case ParsePropertyKind::kNotSet:
3068  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
3069  return impl()->NullLiteralProperty();
3070  }
3071  UNREACHABLE();
3072 }
3073 
3074 template <typename Impl>
3075 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseObjectLiteral() {
3076  // ObjectLiteral ::
3077  // '{' (PropertyDefinition (',' PropertyDefinition)* ','? )? '}'
3078 
3079  int pos = peek_position();
3080  ObjectPropertyListT properties(pointer_buffer());
3081  int number_of_boilerplate_properties = 0;
3082 
3083  bool has_computed_names = false;
3084  bool has_rest_property = false;
3085  bool has_seen_proto = false;
3086 
3087  Consume(Token::kLeftBrace);
3088  AccumulationScope accumulation_scope(expression_scope());
3089 
3090  // If methods appear inside the object literal, we'll enter this scope.
3091  Scope* block_scope = NewBlockScopeForObjectLiteral();
3092  block_scope->set_start_position(pos);
3093  BlockState object_literal_scope_state(&object_literal_scope_, block_scope);
3094 
3095  while (!Check(Token::kRightBrace)) {
3096  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
3097 
3098  ParsePropertyInfo prop_info(this, &accumulation_scope);
3099  prop_info.position = PropertyPosition::kObjectLiteral;
3100  ObjectLiteralPropertyT property =
3101  ParseObjectPropertyDefinition(&prop_info, &has_seen_proto);
3102  if (impl()->IsNull(property)) return impl()->FailureExpression();
3103 
3104  if (prop_info.is_computed_name) {
3105  has_computed_names = true;
3106  }
3107 
3108  if (prop_info.is_rest) {
3109  has_rest_property = true;
3110  }
3111 
3112  if (impl()->IsBoilerplateProperty(property) && !has_computed_names) {
3113  // Count CONSTANT or COMPUTED properties to maintain the enumeration
3114  // order.
3115  number_of_boilerplate_properties++;
3116  }
3117 
3118  properties.Add(property);
3119 
3120  if (peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
3121  Expect(Token::kComma);
3122  }
3123 
3124  fni_.Infer();
3125  }
3126 
3127  Variable* home_object = nullptr;
3128  if (block_scope->needs_home_object()) {
3129  home_object = block_scope->DeclareHomeObjectVariable(ast_value_factory());
3130  block_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
3131  } else {
3132  block_scope = block_scope->FinalizeBlockScope();
3133  DCHECK_NULL(block_scope);
3134  }
3135 
3136  // In pattern rewriter, we rewrite rest property to call out to a
3137  // runtime function passing all the other properties as arguments to
3138  // this runtime function. Here, we make sure that the number of
3139  // properties is less than number of arguments allowed for a runtime
3140  // call.
3141  if (has_rest_property && properties.length() > Code::kMaxArguments) {
3142  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(Scanner::Location(pos, position()),
3143  MessageTemplate::kTooManyArguments);
3144  }
3145 
3146  return impl()->InitializeObjectLiteral(
3147  factory()->NewObjectLiteral(properties, number_of_boilerplate_properties,
3148  pos, has_rest_property, home_object));
3149 }

3151 template <typename Impl>
3152 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseArguments(
3153  typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionListT* args, bool* has_spread,
3154  ParsingArrowHeadFlag maybe_arrow) {
3155  // Arguments ::
3156  // '(' (AssignmentExpression)*[','] ')'
3157 
3158  *has_spread = false;
3159  Consume(Token::kLeftParen);
3160  AccumulationScope accumulation_scope(expression_scope());
3161 
3162  int variable_index = 0;
3163  while (peek() != Token::kRightParen) {
3164  int start_pos = peek_position();
3165  bool is_spread = Check(Token::kEllipsis);
3166  int expr_pos = peek_position();
3167 
3168  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
3169  ExpressionT argument = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
3170 
3171  if (V8_UNLIKELY(maybe_arrow == kMaybeArrowHead)) {
3172  ClassifyArrowParameter(&accumulation_scope, expr_pos, argument);
3173  if (is_spread) {
3174  expression_scope()->RecordNonSimpleParameter();
3175  if (argument->IsAssignment()) {
3176  expression_scope()->RecordAsyncArrowParametersError(
3177  scanner()->location(), MessageTemplate::kRestDefaultInitializer);
3178  }
3179  if (peek() == Token::kComma) {
3180  expression_scope()->RecordAsyncArrowParametersError(
3181  scanner()->peek_location(), MessageTemplate::kParamAfterRest);
3182  }
3183  }
3184  }
3185  if (is_spread) {
3186  *has_spread = true;
3187  argument = factory()->NewSpread(argument, start_pos, expr_pos);
3188  }
3189  args->Add(argument);
3190 
3191  variable_index =
3192  expression_scope()->SetInitializers(variable_index, peek_position());
3193 
3194  if (!Check(Token::kComma)) break;
3195  }
3196 
3197  if (args->length() + 1 /* receiver */ > Code::kMaxArguments) {
3198  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kTooManyArguments);
3199  return;
3200  }
3201 
3202  Scanner::Location location = scanner_->location();
3203  if (!Check(Token::kRightParen)) {
3204  impl()->ReportMessageAt(location, MessageTemplate::kUnterminatedArgList);
3205  }
3206 }

3210 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseConditionalChainAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar() {

3213  // YieldExpression

3215  int lhs_beg_pos = peek_position();
3216 
3217  if (peek() == Token::kYield && is_generator()) {
3218  return ParseYieldExpression();
3219  }
3220 
3221  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
3222 
3223  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(), next_arrow_function_info_.HasInitialState());
3224 
3225  ExpressionT expression = ParseLogicalExpression();
3226 
3227  Token::Value op = peek();
3228 
3229  if (!Token::IsArrowOrAssignmentOp(op) || peek() == Token::kConditional)
3230  return expression;
3231 
3232  return ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammarContinuation(lhs_beg_pos,
3233  expression);

3246 
3247  if (peek() == Token::kYield && is_generator()) {
3248  return ParseYieldExpression();
3249  }
3250 
3251  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
3252

3254

3265 // Precedence = 2
3266 template <typename Impl>
3267 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3268 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammarContinuation(
3269  int lhs_beg_pos, ExpressionT expression) {
3270  // AssignmentExpression ::
3271  // ConditionalExpression
3272  // ArrowFunction
3273  // YieldExpression
3274  // LeftHandSideExpression AssignmentOperator AssignmentExpression
3275  Token::Value op = peek();
3276 
3277  // Arrow functions.
3278  if (V8_UNLIKELY(op == Token::kArrow)) {
3279  Scanner::Location loc(lhs_beg_pos, end_position());
3280 
3281  if (!impl()->IsIdentifier(expression) && !expression->is_parenthesized()) {
3282  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
3283  Scanner::Location(expression->position(), position()),
3284  MessageTemplate::kMalformedArrowFunParamList);
3285  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3286  }
3287 
3288  DeclarationScope* scope = next_arrow_function_info_.scope;
3289  int function_literal_id = next_arrow_function_info_.function_literal_id;
3290  scope->set_start_position(lhs_beg_pos);
3291 
3292  FormalParametersT parameters(scope);
3293  parameters.set_strict_parameter_error(
3294  next_arrow_function_info_.strict_parameter_error_location,
3295  next_arrow_function_info_.strict_parameter_error_message);
3296  parameters.is_simple = scope->has_simple_parameters();
3297  bool could_be_immediately_invoked =
3298  next_arrow_function_info_.could_be_immediately_invoked;
3299  next_arrow_function_info_.Reset();
3300 
3301  impl()->DeclareArrowFunctionFormalParameters(&parameters, expression, loc);
3302  // function_literal_id was reserved for the arrow function, but not actaully
3303  // allocated. This comparison allocates a function literal id for the arrow
3304  // function, and checks whether it's still the function id we wanted. If
3305  // not, we'll reindex the arrow function formal parameters to shift them all
3306  // 1 down to make space for the arrow function.
3307  if (function_literal_id != GetNextInfoId()) {
3308  impl()->ReindexArrowFunctionFormalParameters(&parameters);
3309  }
3310 
3311  expression = ParseArrowFunctionLiteral(parameters, function_literal_id,
3312  could_be_immediately_invoked);
3313 
3314  return expression;
3315  }
3316 
3317  if (V8_LIKELY(impl()->IsAssignableIdentifier(expression))) {
3318  if (expression->is_parenthesized()) {
3319  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
3320  Scanner::Location(lhs_beg_pos, end_position()),
3321  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
3322  }
3323  expression_scope()->MarkIdentifierAsAssigned();
3324  } else if (expression->IsProperty()) {
3325  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
3326  Scanner::Location(lhs_beg_pos, end_position()),
3327  MessageTemplate::kInvalidPropertyBindingPattern);
3328  expression_scope()->ValidateAsExpression();
3329  } else if (expression->IsPattern() && op == Token::kAssign) {
3330  // Destructuring assignmment.
3331  if (expression->is_parenthesized()) {
3332  Scanner::Location loc(lhs_beg_pos, end_position());
3333  if (expression_scope()->IsCertainlyDeclaration()) {
3334  impl()->ReportMessageAt(loc,
3335  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
3336  } else {
3337  // Syntax Error if LHS is neither object literal nor an array literal
3338  // (Parenthesized literals are
3339  // CoverParenthesizedExpressionAndArrowParameterList).
3340  // #sec-assignment-operators-static-semantics-early-errors
3341  impl()->ReportMessageAt(loc, MessageTemplate::kInvalidLhsInAssignment);
3342  }
3343  }
3344  expression_scope()->ValidateAsPattern(expression, lhs_beg_pos,
3345  end_position());
3346  } else {
3347  DCHECK(!IsValidReferenceExpression(expression));
3348  // For web compatibility reasons, throw early errors only for logical
3349  // assignment, not for regular assignment.
3350  const bool early_error = Token::IsLogicalAssignmentOp(op);
3351  expression = RewriteInvalidReferenceExpression(
3352  expression, lhs_beg_pos, end_position(),
3353  MessageTemplate::kInvalidLhsInAssignment, early_error);
3354  }
3355 
3356  Consume(op);
3357  int op_position = position();
3358 
3359  ExpressionT right = ParseAssignmentExpression();
3360 
3361  // Anonymous function name inference applies to =, ||=, &&=, and ??=.
3362  if (op == Token::kAssign || Token::IsLogicalAssignmentOp(op)) {
3363  impl()->CheckAssigningFunctionLiteralToProperty(expression, right);
3364 
3365  // Check if the right hand side is a call to avoid inferring a
3366  // name if we're dealing with "a = function(){...}();"-like
3367  // expression.
3368  if (right->IsCall() || right->IsCallNew()) {
3369  fni_.RemoveLastFunction();
3370  } else {
3371  fni_.Infer();
3372  }
3373 
3374  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromIdentifierRef(right, expression);
3375  } else {
3376  fni_.RemoveLastFunction();
3377  }
3378 
3379  if (op == Token::kAssign) {
3380  // We try to estimate the set of properties set by constructors. We define a
3381  // new property whenever there is an assignment to a property of 'this'. We
3382  // should probably only add properties if we haven't seen them before.
3383  // Otherwise we'll probably overestimate the number of properties.
3384  if (impl()->IsThisProperty(expression)) function_state_->AddProperty();
3385  } else {
3386  if (Token::IsLogicalAssignmentOp(op)) {
3387  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kLogicalAssignment);
3388  }
3389  // Only initializers (i.e. no compound assignments) are allowed in patterns.
3390  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
3391  Scanner::Location(lhs_beg_pos, end_position()),
3392  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
3393  }
3394 
3395  return factory()->NewAssignment(op, expression, right, op_position);
3396 }
3397 
3398 template <typename Impl>
3399 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3400 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseYieldExpression() {
3401  // YieldExpression ::
3402  // 'yield' ([no line terminator] '*'? AssignmentExpression)?
3403  int pos = peek_position();
3404  expression_scope()->RecordParameterInitializerError(
3405  scanner()->peek_location(), MessageTemplate::kYieldInParameter);
3406  Consume(Token::kYield);
3407  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
3408  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
3409  }
3410 
3411  CheckStackOverflow();
3412 
3413  // The following initialization is necessary.
3414  ExpressionT expression = impl()->NullExpression();
3415  bool delegating = false; // yield*
3416  if (!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext()) {
3417  if (Check(Token::kMul)) delegating = true;
3418  switch (peek()) {
3419  case Token::kEos:
3420  case Token::kSemicolon:
3421  case Token::kRightBrace:
3422  case Token::kRightBracket:
3423  case Token::kRightParen:
3424  case Token::kColon:
3425  case Token::kComma:
3426  case Token::kIn:
3427  // The above set of tokens is the complete set of tokens that can appear
3428  // after an AssignmentExpression, and none of them can start an
3429  // AssignmentExpression. This allows us to avoid looking for an RHS for
3430  // a regular yield, given only one look-ahead token.
3431  if (!delegating) break;
3432  // Delegating yields require an RHS; fall through.
3433  [[fallthrough]];
3434  default:
3435  expression = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
3436  break;
3437  }
3438  }
3439 
3440  if (delegating) {
3441  ExpressionT yieldstar = factory()->NewYieldStar(expression, pos);
3442  impl()->RecordSuspendSourceRange(yieldstar, PositionAfterSemicolon());
3443  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3444  if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(function_state_->kind())) {
3445  // return, iterator_close and delegated_iterator_output suspend ids.
3446  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3447  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3448  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3449  }
3450  return yieldstar;
3451  }
3452 
3453  // Hackily disambiguate o from o.next and o [Symbol.iterator]().
3454  // TODO(verwaest): Come up with a better solution.
3455  ExpressionT yield =
3456  factory()->NewYield(expression, pos, Suspend::kOnExceptionThrow);
3457  impl()->RecordSuspendSourceRange(yield, PositionAfterSemicolon());
3458  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3459  return yield;
3460 }

3462 // Precedence = 3
3463 template <typename Impl>
3464 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3465 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseConditionalExpression() {
3466  // ConditionalExpression ::
3467  // LogicalExpression
3468  // LogicalExpression '?' AssignmentExpression ':' AssignmentExpression
3469  //
3470  int pos = peek_position();
3471  ExpressionT expression = ParseLogicalExpression();
3472  return peek() == Token::kConditional
3473  ? ParseConditionalChainExpression(expression, pos)
3474  : expression;
3475 }

3477 template <typename Impl>
3478 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3479 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseLogicalExpression() {
3480  // LogicalExpression ::
3481  // LogicalORExpression
3482  // CoalesceExpression
3483 
3484  // Both LogicalORExpression and CoalesceExpression start with BitwiseOR.
3485  // Parse for binary expressions >= 6 (BitwiseOR);
3486  ExpressionT expression = ParseBinaryExpression(6);
3487  if (peek() == Token::kAnd || peek() == Token::kOr) {
3488  // LogicalORExpression, pickup parsing where we left off.
3489  int prec1 = Token::Precedence(peek(), accept_IN_);
3490  expression = ParseBinaryContinuation(expression, 4, prec1);
3491  } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kNullish)) {
3492  expression = ParseCoalesceExpression(expression);
3493  }
3494  return expression;
3495 }

3497 template <typename Impl>
3498 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3499 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseCoalesceExpression(ExpressionT expression) {
3500  // CoalesceExpression ::
3501  // CoalesceExpressionHead ?? BitwiseORExpression
3502  //
3503  // CoalesceExpressionHead ::
3504  // CoalesceExpression
3505  // BitwiseORExpression
3506 
3507  // We create a binary operation for the first nullish, otherwise collapse
3508  // into an nary expresion.
3509  bool first_nullish = true;
3510  while (peek() == Token::kNullish) {
3511  SourceRange right_range;
3512  int pos;
3513  ExpressionT y;
3514  {
3515  SourceRangeScope right_range_scope(scanner(), &right_range);
3516  Consume(Token::kNullish);
3517  pos = peek_position();
3518  // Parse BitwiseOR or higher.
3519  y = ParseBinaryExpression(6);
3520  }
3521  if (first_nullish) {
3522  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kNullishCoalescing);
3523  expression =
3524  factory()->NewBinaryOperation(Token::kNullish, expression, y, pos);
3525  impl()->RecordBinaryOperationSourceRange(expression, right_range);
3526  first_nullish = false;
3527  } else {
3528  impl()->CollapseNaryExpression(&expression, y, Token::kNullish, pos,
3529  right_range);
3530  }
3531  }
3532  return expression;
3533 }
3534 
3535 template <typename Impl>
3536 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3537 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseConditionalChainExpression(ExpressionT condition,
3538  int condition_pos) {
3539  // ConditionalChainExpression ::
3540  // ConditionalExpression_1 ? AssignmentExpression_1 :
3541  // ConditionalExpression_2 ? AssignmentExpression_2 :
3542  // ConditionalExpression_3 ? AssignmentExpression_3 :
3543  // ...
3544  // ConditionalExpression_n ? AssignmentExpression_n
3545 
3546  ExpressionT expr = impl()->NullExpression();
3547  ExpressionT else_expression = impl()->NullExpression();
3548  bool else_found = false;
3549  ZoneVector<int> else_ranges_beg_pos(impl()->zone());
3550  do {
3551  SourceRange then_range;
3552  ExpressionT then_expression;
3553  {
3554  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &then_range);
3555  Consume(Token::kConditional);
3556  // In parsing the first assignment expression in conditional
3557  // expressions we always accept the 'in' keyword; see ECMA-262,
3558  // section 11.12, page 58.
3559  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
3560  then_expression = ParseAssignmentExpression();
3561  }
3562 
3563  else_ranges_beg_pos.emplace_back(scanner()->peek_location().beg_pos);
3564  int condition_or_else_pos = peek_position();
3565  SourceRange condition_or_else_range = SourceRange();
3566  ExpressionT condition_or_else_expression;
3567  {
3568  SourceRangeScope condition_or_else_range_scope(scanner(),
3569  &condition_or_else_range);
3570  Expect(Token::kColon);
3571  condition_or_else_expression =
3572  ParseConditionalChainAssignmentExpression();
3573  }
3574 
3575  else_found = (peek() != Token::kConditional);
3576 
3577  if (else_found) {
3578  else_expression = condition_or_else_expression;
3579 
3580  if (impl()->IsNull(expr)) {
3581  // When we have a single conditional expression, we don't create a
3582  // conditional chain expression. Instead, we just return a conditional
3583  // expression.
3584  SourceRange else_range = condition_or_else_range;
3585  expr = factory()->NewConditional(condition, then_expression,
3586  else_expression, condition_pos);
3587  impl()->RecordConditionalSourceRange(expr, then_range, else_range);
3588  return expr;
3589  }
3590  }
3591 
3592  if (impl()->IsNull(expr)) {
3593  // For the first conditional expression, we create a conditional chain.
3594  expr = factory()->NewConditionalChain(1, condition_pos);
3595  }
3596 
3597  impl()->CollapseConditionalChain(&expr, condition, then_expression,
3598  else_expression, condition_pos,
3599  then_range);
3600 
3601  if (!else_found) {
3602  condition = condition_or_else_expression;
3603  condition_pos = condition_or_else_pos;
3604  }
3605  } while (!else_found);
3606 
3607  int end_pos = scanner()->location().end_pos;
3608  for (const auto& else_range_beg_pos : else_ranges_beg_pos) {
3609  impl()->AppendConditionalChainElse(
3610  &expr, SourceRange(else_range_beg_pos, end_pos));
3611  }
3612 
3613  return expr;
3614 }
3615 
3616 template <typename Impl>
3617 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3618 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseConditionalContinuation(ExpressionT expression,
3619  int pos) {
3620  SourceRange then_range, else_range;
3621 
3622  ExpressionT left;
3623  {
3624  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &then_range);
3625  Consume(Token::kConditional);
3626  // In parsing the first assignment expression in conditional
3627  // expressions we always accept the 'in' keyword; see ECMA-262,
3628  // section 11.12, page 58.
3629  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
3630  left = ParseAssignmentExpression();
3631  }
3632  ExpressionT right;
3633  {
3634  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &else_range);
3635  Expect(Token::kColon);
3636  right = ParseAssignmentExpression();
3637  }
3638  ExpressionT expr = factory()->NewConditional(expression, left, right, pos);
3639  impl()->RecordConditionalSourceRange(expr, then_range, else_range);
3640  return expr;
3641 }
3642 
3643 // Precedence >= 4
3644 template <typename Impl>
3645 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3646 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBinaryContinuation(ExpressionT x, int prec, int prec1) {
3647  do {
3648  // prec1 >= 4
3649  while (Token::Precedence(peek(), accept_IN_) == prec1) {
3650  SourceRange right_range;
3651  int pos = peek_position();
3652  ExpressionT y;
3653  Token::Value op;
3654  {
3655  SourceRangeScope right_range_scope(scanner(), &right_range);
3656  op = Next();
3657 
3658  const bool is_right_associative = op == Token::kExp;
3659  const int next_prec = is_right_associative ? prec1 : prec1 + 1;
3660  y = ParseBinaryExpression(next_prec);
3661  }
3662 
3663  // For now we distinguish between comparisons and other binary
3664  // operations. (We could combine the two and get rid of this
3665  // code and AST node eventually.)
3666  if (Token::IsCompareOp(op)) {
3667  // We have a comparison.
3668  Token::Value cmp = op;
3669  switch (op) {
3670  case Token::kNotEq:
3671  cmp = Token::kEq;
3672  break;
3673  case Token::kNotEqStrict:
3674  cmp = Token::kEqStrict;
3675  break;
3676  default: break;
3677  }
3678  x = factory()->NewCompareOperation(cmp, x, y, pos);
3679  if (cmp != op) {
3680  // The comparison was negated - add a kNot.
3681  x = factory()->NewUnaryOperation(Token::kNot, x, pos);
3682  }
3683  } else if (!impl()->ShortcutLiteralBinaryExpression(&x, y, op, pos) &&
3684  !impl()->CollapseNaryExpression(&x, y, op, pos, right_range)) {
3685  // We have a "normal" binary operation.
3686  x = factory()->NewBinaryOperation(op, x, y, pos);
3687  if (op == Token::kOr || op == Token::kAnd) {
3688  impl()->RecordBinaryOperationSourceRange(x, right_range);
3689  }
3690  }
3691  }
3692  --prec1;
3693  } while (prec1 >= prec);
3694 
3695  return x;
3696 }
3697 
3698 // Precedence >= 4
3699 template <typename Impl>
3700 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBinaryExpression(
3701  int prec) {
3702  DCHECK_GE(prec, 4);
3703 
3704  // "#foo in ShiftExpression" needs to be parsed separately, since private
3705  // identifiers are not valid PrimaryExpressions.
3706  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kPrivateName)) {
3707  ExpressionT x = ParsePropertyOrPrivatePropertyName();
3708  int prec1 = Token::Precedence(peek(), accept_IN_);
3709  if (peek() != Token::kIn || prec1 < prec) {
3710  ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kPrivateName);
3711  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3712  }
3713  return ParseBinaryContinuation(x, prec, prec1);
3714  }
3715 
3716  ExpressionT x = ParseUnaryExpression();
3717  int prec1 = Token::Precedence(peek(), accept_IN_);
3718  if (prec1 >= prec) {
3719  return ParseBinaryContinuation(x, prec, prec1);
3720  }
3721  return x;
3722 }
3723 
3724 template <typename Impl>
3725 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3726 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseUnaryOrPrefixExpression() {
3727  Token::Value op = Next();
3728  int pos = position();
3729 
3730  // Assume "! function ..." indicates the function is likely to be called.
3731  if (op == Token::kNot && peek() == Token::kFunction) {
3732  function_state_->set_next_function_is_likely_called();
3733  }
3734 
3735  CheckStackOverflow();
3736 
3737  int expression_position = peek_position();
3738  ExpressionT expression = ParseUnaryExpression();
3739 
3740  if (Token::IsUnaryOp(op)) {
3741  if (op == Token::kDelete) {
3742  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(expression) && is_strict(language_mode())) {
3743  // "delete identifier" is a syntax error in strict mode.
3744  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kStrictDelete);
3745  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3746  }
3747 
3748  if (impl()->IsPrivateReference(expression)) {
3749  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kDeletePrivateField);
3750  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3751  }
3752  }
3753 
3754  if (peek() == Token::kExp) {
3755  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
3756  Scanner::Location(pos, peek_end_position()),
3757  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedTokenUnaryExponentiation);
3758  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3759  }
3760 
3761  // Allow the parser's implementation to rewrite the expression.
3762  return impl()->BuildUnaryExpression(expression, op, pos);
3763  }
3764 
3765  DCHECK(Token::IsCountOp(op));
3766 
3767  if (V8_LIKELY(IsValidReferenceExpression(expression))) {
3768  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(expression)) {
3769  expression_scope()->MarkIdentifierAsAssigned();
3770  }
3771  } else {
3772  const bool early_error = false;
3773  expression = RewriteInvalidReferenceExpression(
3774  expression, expression_position, end_position(),
3775  MessageTemplate::kInvalidLhsInPrefixOp, early_error);
3776  }
3777 
3778  return factory()->NewCountOperation(op, true /* prefix */, expression,
3779  position());
3780 }
3781 
3782 template <typename Impl>
3783 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3784 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAwaitExpression() {
3785  if (IsModule(function_state_->kind())) {
3786  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kTopLevelAwait);
3787  }
3788 
3789  expression_scope()->RecordParameterInitializerError(
3790  scanner()->peek_location(),
3791  MessageTemplate::kAwaitExpressionFormalParameter);
3792  int await_pos = peek_position();
3793  Consume(Token::kAwait);
3794  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
3795  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
3796  }
3797 
3798  CheckStackOverflow();
3799 
3800  ExpressionT value = ParseUnaryExpression();
3801 
3802  // 'await' is a unary operator according to the spec, even though it's treated
3803  // specially in the parser.
3804  if (peek() == Token::kExp) {
3805  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
3806  Scanner::Location(await_pos, peek_end_position()),
3807  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedTokenUnaryExponentiation);
3808  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3809  }
3810 
3811  ExpressionT expr = factory()->NewAwait(value, await_pos);
3812  function_state_->AddSuspend();
3813  impl()->RecordSuspendSourceRange(expr, PositionAfterSemicolon());
3814  return expr;
3815 }
3816 
3817 template <typename Impl>
3818 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3819 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseUnaryExpression() {
3820  // UnaryExpression ::
3821  // PostfixExpression
3822  // 'delete' UnaryExpression
3823  // 'void' UnaryExpression
3824  // 'typeof' UnaryExpression
3825  // '++' UnaryExpression
3826  // '--' UnaryExpression
3827  // '+' UnaryExpression
3828  // '-' UnaryExpression
3829  // '~' UnaryExpression
3830  // '!' UnaryExpression
3831  // [+Await] AwaitExpression[?Yield]
3832 
3833  Token::Value op = peek();
3834  if (Token::IsUnaryOrCountOp(op)) return ParseUnaryOrPrefixExpression();
3835  if (is_await_allowed() && op == Token::kAwait) {
3836  return ParseAwaitExpression();
3837  }
3838  return ParsePostfixExpression();
3839 }
3840 
3841 template <typename Impl>
3842 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3843 ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePostfixExpression() {
3844  // PostfixExpression ::
3845  // LeftHandSideExpression ('++' | '--')?
3846 
3847  int lhs_beg_pos = peek_position();
3848  ExpressionT expression = ParseLeftHandSideExpression();
3849  if (V8_LIKELY(!Token::IsCountOp(peek()) ||
3850  scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext())) {
3851  return expression;
3852  }
3853  return ParsePostfixContinuation(expression, lhs_beg_pos);
3854 }
3855 
3856 template <typename Impl>
3857 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3858 ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePostfixContinuation(ExpressionT expression,
3859  int lhs_beg_pos) {
3860  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsValidReferenceExpression(expression))) {
3861  const bool early_error = false;
3862  expression = RewriteInvalidReferenceExpression(
3863  expression, lhs_beg_pos, end_position(),
3864  MessageTemplate::kInvalidLhsInPostfixOp, early_error);
3865  }
3866  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(expression)) {
3867  expression_scope()->MarkIdentifierAsAssigned();
3868  }
3869 
3870  Token::Value next = Next();
3871  return factory()->NewCountOperation(next, false /* postfix */, expression,
3872  position());
3873 }
3874 
3875 template <typename Impl>
3876 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3877 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseLeftHandSideExpression() {
3878  // LeftHandSideExpression ::
3879  // (NewExpression | MemberExpression) ...
3880 
3881  ExpressionT result = ParseMemberExpression();
3882  if (!Token::IsPropertyOrCall(peek())) return result;
3883  return ParseLeftHandSideContinuation(result);
3884 }
3885 
3886 template <typename Impl>
3887 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
3888 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseLeftHandSideContinuation(ExpressionT result) {
3889  DCHECK(Token::IsPropertyOrCall(peek()));
3890 
3891  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() == Token::kLeftParen && impl()->IsIdentifier(result) &&
3892  scanner()->current_token() == Token::kAsync &&
3893  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() &&
3894  !scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
3895  DCHECK(impl()->IsAsync(impl()->AsIdentifier(result)));
3896  int pos = position();
3897 
3898  ArrowHeadParsingScope maybe_arrow(impl(), FunctionKind::kAsyncArrowFunction,
3899  PeekNextInfoId());
3900  Scope::Snapshot scope_snapshot(scope());
3901 
3902  ExpressionListT args(pointer_buffer());
3903  bool has_spread;
3904  ParseArguments(&args, &has_spread, kMaybeArrowHead);
3905  if (V8_LIKELY(peek() == Token::kArrow)) {
3906  fni_.RemoveAsyncKeywordFromEnd();
3907  next_arrow_function_info_.scope = maybe_arrow.ValidateAndCreateScope();
3908  next_arrow_function_info_.function_literal_id =
3909  maybe_arrow.function_literal_id();
3910  scope_snapshot.Reparent(next_arrow_function_info_.scope);
3911  // async () => ...
3912  if (!args.length()) return factory()->NewEmptyParentheses(pos);
3913  // async ( Arguments ) => ...
3914  result = impl()->ExpressionListToExpression(args);
3915  result->mark_parenthesized();
3916  return result;
3917  }
3918 
3919  result = factory()->NewCall(result, args, pos, has_spread);
3920 
3921  maybe_arrow.ValidateExpression();
3922 
3923  fni_.RemoveLastFunction();
3924  if (!Token::IsPropertyOrCall(peek())) return result;
3925  }
3926 
3927  bool optional_chaining = false;
3928  bool is_optional = false;
3929  int optional_link_begin;
3930  do {
3931  switch (peek()) {
3932  case Token::kQuestionPeriod: {
3933  if (is_optional) {
3934  ReportUnexpectedToken(peek());
3935  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3936  }
3937  // Include the ?. in the source range position.
3938  optional_link_begin = scanner()->peek_location().beg_pos;
3939  Consume(Token::kQuestionPeriod);
3940  is_optional = true;
3941  optional_chaining = true;
3942  if (Token::IsPropertyOrCall(peek())) continue;
3943  int pos = position();
3944  ExpressionT key = ParsePropertyOrPrivatePropertyName();
3945  result = factory()->NewProperty(result, key, pos, is_optional);
3946  break;
3947  }
3948 
3949  /* Property */
3950  case Token::kLeftBracket: {
3951  Consume(Token::kLeftBracket);
3952  int pos = position();
3953  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
3954  ExpressionT index = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
3955  result = factory()->NewProperty(result, index, pos, is_optional);
3956  Expect(Token::kRightBracket);
3957  break;
3958  }
3959 
3960  /* Property */
3961  case Token::kPeriod: {
3962  if (is_optional) {
3963  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
3964  return impl()->FailureExpression();
3965  }
3966  Consume(Token::kPeriod);
3967  int pos = position();
3968  ExpressionT key = ParsePropertyOrPrivatePropertyName();
3969  result = factory()->NewProperty(result, key, pos, is_optional);
3970  break;
3971  }
3972 
3973  /* Call */
3974  case Token::kLeftParen: {
3975  int pos;
3976  if (Token::IsCallable(scanner()->current_token())) {
3977  // For call of an identifier we want to report position of
3978  // the identifier as position of the call in the stack trace.
3979  pos = position();
3980  } else {
3981  // For other kinds of calls we record position of the parenthesis as
3982  // position of the call. Note that this is extremely important for
3983  // expressions of the form function(){...}() for which call position
3984  // should not point to the closing brace otherwise it will intersect
3985  // with positions recorded for function literal and confuse debugger.
3986  pos = peek_position();
3987  // Also the trailing parenthesis are a hint that the function will
3988  // be called immediately. If we happen to have parsed a preceding
3989  // function literal eagerly, we can also compile it eagerly.
3990  if (result->IsFunctionLiteral()) {
3991  result->AsFunctionLiteral()->SetShouldEagerCompile();
3992  }
3993  }
3994  bool has_spread;
3995  ExpressionListT args(pointer_buffer());
3996  ParseArguments(&args, &has_spread);
3997 
3998  // Keep track of eval() calls since they disable all local variable
3999  // optimizations.
4000  // The calls that need special treatment are the
4001  // direct eval calls. These calls are all of the form eval(...), with
4002  // no explicit receiver.
4003  // These calls are marked as potentially direct eval calls. Whether
4004  // they are actually direct calls to eval is determined at run time.
4005  int eval_scope_info_index = 0;
4006  if (CheckPossibleEvalCall(result, is_optional, scope())) {
4007  eval_scope_info_index = GetNextInfoId();
4008  if (!Call::EvalScopeInfoIndexField::is_valid(eval_scope_info_index)) {
4009  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kTooManyEvals);
4010  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4011  }
4012  }
4013 
4014  result = factory()->NewCall(result, args, pos, has_spread,
4015  eval_scope_info_index, is_optional);
4016 
4017  fni_.RemoveLastFunction();
4018  break;
4019  }
4020 
4021  default:
4022  // Template literals in/after an Optional Chain not supported:
4023  if (optional_chaining) {
4024  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
4025  MessageTemplate::kOptionalChainingNoTemplate);
4026  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4027  }
4028  /* Tagged Template */
4029  DCHECK(Token::IsTemplate(peek()));
4030  result = ParseTemplateLiteral(result, position(), true);
4031  break;
4032  }
4033  if (is_optional) {
4034  SourceRange chain_link_range(optional_link_begin, end_position());
4035  impl()->RecordExpressionSourceRange(result, chain_link_range);
4036  is_optional = false;
4037  }
4038  } while (Token::IsPropertyOrCall(peek()));
4039  if (optional_chaining) return factory()->NewOptionalChain(result);
4040  return result;
4041 }
4042 
4043 template <typename Impl>
4044 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4045 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseMemberWithPresentNewPrefixesExpression() {
4046  // NewExpression ::
4047  // ('new')+ MemberExpression
4048  //
4049  // NewTarget ::
4050  // 'new' '.' 'target'
4051  //
4052  // ImportMeta :
4053  // import . meta
4054 
4055  // The grammar for new expressions is pretty warped. We can have several 'new'
4056  // keywords following each other, and then a MemberExpression. When we see '('
4057  // after the MemberExpression, it's associated with the rightmost unassociated
4058  // 'new' to create a NewExpression with arguments. However, a NewExpression
4059  // can also occur without arguments.
4060 
4061  // Examples of new expression:
4062  // new foo.bar().baz means (new (foo.bar)()).baz
4063  // new foo()() means (new foo())()
4064  // new new foo()() means (new (new foo())())
4065  // new new foo means new (new foo)
4066  // new new foo() means new (new foo())
4067  // new new foo().bar().baz means (new (new foo()).bar()).baz
4068  // new super.x means new (super.x)
4069  // new import.meta.foo means (new (import.meta.foo)())
4070  Consume(Token::kNew);
4071  int new_pos = position();
4072  ExpressionT result;
4073 
4074  CheckStackOverflow();
4075 
4076  if (peek() == Token::kImport) {
4077  result = ParseMemberExpression();
4078  if (result->IsImportCallExpression()) {
4079  // new import() and new import.source() are never allowed.
4080  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4081  MessageTemplate::kImportCallNotNewExpression);
4082  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4083  }
4084  } else if (peek() == Token::kPeriod) {
4085  result = ParseNewTargetExpression();
4086  return ParseMemberExpressionContinuation(result);
4087  } else {
4088  result = ParseMemberExpression();
4089  if (result->IsSuperCallReference()) {
4090  // new super() is never allowed
4091  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4092  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedSuper);
4093  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4094  }
4095  }
4096  if (peek() == Token::kLeftParen) {
4097  // NewExpression with arguments.
4098  {
4099  ExpressionListT args(pointer_buffer());
4100  bool has_spread;
4101  ParseArguments(&args, &has_spread);
4102 
4103  result = factory()->NewCallNew(result, args, new_pos, has_spread);
4104  }
4105  // The expression can still continue with . or [ after the arguments.
4106  return ParseMemberExpressionContinuation(result);
4107  }
4108 
4109  if (peek() == Token::kQuestionPeriod) {
4110  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
4111  MessageTemplate::kOptionalChainingNoNew);
4112  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4113  }
4114 
4115  // NewExpression without arguments.
4116  ExpressionListT args(pointer_buffer());
4117  return factory()->NewCallNew(result, args, new_pos, false);
4118 }
4119 
4120 template <typename Impl>
4121 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4122 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseFunctionExpression() {
4123  Consume(Token::kFunction);
4124  int function_token_position = position();
4125 
4126  FunctionKind function_kind = Check(Token::kMul)
4127  ? FunctionKind::kGeneratorFunction
4128  : FunctionKind::kNormalFunction;
4129  IdentifierT name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
4130  bool is_strict_reserved_name = Token::IsStrictReservedWord(peek());
4131  Scanner::Location function_name_location = Scanner::Location::invalid();
4132  FunctionSyntaxKind function_syntax_kind =
4133  FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression;
4134  if (impl()->ParsingDynamicFunctionDeclaration()) {
4135  // We don't want dynamic functions to actually declare their name
4136  // "anonymous". We just want that name in the toString().
4137  Consume(Token::kIdentifier);
4138  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(),
4139  scanner()->CurrentSymbol(ast_value_factory()) ==
4140  ast_value_factory()->anonymous_string());
4141  } else if (peek_any_identifier()) {
4142  name = ParseIdentifier(function_kind);
4143  function_name_location = scanner()->location();
4144  function_syntax_kind = FunctionSyntaxKind::kNamedExpression;
4145  }
4146  FunctionLiteralT result = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
4147  name, function_name_location,
4148  is_strict_reserved_name ? kFunctionNameIsStrictReserved
4149  : kFunctionNameValidityUnknown,
4150  function_kind, function_token_position, function_syntax_kind,
4151  language_mode(), nullptr);
4152  // TODO(verwaest): FailureFunctionLiteral?
4153  if (impl()->IsNull(result)) return impl()->FailureExpression();
4154  return result;
4155 }
4156 
4157 template <typename Impl>
4158 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4159 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseMemberExpression() {
4160  // MemberExpression ::
4161  // (PrimaryExpression | FunctionLiteral | ClassLiteral)
4162  // ('[' Expression ']' | '.' Identifier | Arguments | TemplateLiteral)*
4163  //
4164  // CallExpression ::
4165  // (SuperCall | ImportCall)
4166  // ('[' Expression ']' | '.' Identifier | Arguments | TemplateLiteral)*
4167  //
4168  // The '[' Expression ']' and '.' Identifier parts are parsed by
4169  // ParseMemberExpressionContinuation, and everything preceeding it is merged
4170  // into ParsePrimaryExpression.
4171 
4172  // Parse the initial primary or function expression.
4173  ExpressionT result = ParsePrimaryExpression();
4174  return ParseMemberExpressionContinuation(result);
4175 }
4176 
4177 template <typename Impl>
4178 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4179 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseImportExpressions() {
4180  // ImportCall[Yield, Await] :
4181  // import ( AssignmentExpression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await] )
4182  // import . source ( AssignmentExpression[+In, ?Yield, ?Await] )
4183  //
4184  // ImportMeta : import . meta
4185 
4186  Consume(Token::kImport);
4187  int pos = position();
4188 
4189  ModuleImportPhase phase = ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation;
4190 
4191  // Distinguish import meta and import phase calls.
4192  if (Check(Token::kPeriod)) {
4193  if (v8_flags.js_source_phase_imports &&
4194  CheckContextualKeyword(ast_value_factory()->source_string())) {
4195  phase = ModuleImportPhase::kSource;
4196  } else {
4197  ExpectContextualKeyword(ast_value_factory()->meta_string(), "import.meta",
4198  pos);
4199  if (!flags().is_module() && !IsParsingWhileDebugging()) {
4200  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4201  MessageTemplate::kImportMetaOutsideModule);
4202  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4203  }
4204  return impl()->ImportMetaExpression(pos);
4205  }
4206  }
4207 
4208  if (V8_UNLIKELY(peek() != Token::kLeftParen)) {
4209  if (!flags().is_module()) {
4210  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4211  MessageTemplate::kImportOutsideModule);
4212  } else {
4213  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
4214  }
4215  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4216  }
4217 
4218  Consume(Token::kLeftParen);
4219  if (peek() == Token::kRightParen) {
4220  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4221  MessageTemplate::kImportMissingSpecifier);
4222  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4223  }
4224 
4225  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
4226  ExpressionT specifier = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
4227 
4228  DCHECK_IMPLIES(phase == ModuleImportPhase::kSource,
4229  v8_flags.js_source_phase_imports);
4230  // TODO(42204365): Enable import attributes with source phase import once
4231  // specified.
4232  if (v8_flags.harmony_import_attributes &&
4233  phase == ModuleImportPhase::kEvaluation && Check(Token::kComma)) {
4234  if (Check(Token::kRightParen)) {
4235  // A trailing comma allowed after the specifier.
4236  return factory()->NewImportCallExpression(specifier, phase, pos);
4237  } else {
4238  ExpressionT import_options = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
4239  Check(Token::kComma); // A trailing comma is allowed after the import
4240  // attributes.
4241  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
4242  return factory()->NewImportCallExpression(specifier, phase,
4243  import_options, pos);
4244  }
4245  }
4246 
4247  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
4248  return factory()->NewImportCallExpression(specifier, phase, pos);
4249 }
4250 
4251 template <typename Impl>
4252 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4253 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseSuperExpression() {
4254  Consume(Token::kSuper);
4255  int pos = position();
4256 
4257  DeclarationScope* scope = GetReceiverScope();
4258  FunctionKind kind = scope->function_kind();
4259  if (IsConciseMethod(kind) || IsAccessorFunction(kind) ||
4260  IsClassConstructor(kind)) {
4261  if (Token::IsProperty(peek())) {
4262  if (peek() == Token::kPeriod && PeekAhead() == Token::kPrivateName) {
4263  Consume(Token::kPeriod);
4264  Consume(Token::kPrivateName);
4265 
4266  impl()->ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedPrivateField);
4267  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4268  }
4269  if (peek() == Token::kQuestionPeriod) {
4270  Consume(Token::kQuestionPeriod);
4271  impl()->ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kOptionalChainingNoSuper);
4272  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4273  }
4274  scope->RecordSuperPropertyUsage();
4275  UseThis();
4276  return impl()->NewSuperPropertyReference(pos);
4277  }
4278  // super() is only allowed in derived constructor. new super() is never
4279  // allowed; it's reported as an error by
4280  // ParseMemberWithPresentNewPrefixesExpression.
4281  if (peek() == Token::kLeftParen && IsDerivedConstructor(kind)) {
4282  // TODO(rossberg): This might not be the correct FunctionState for the
4283  // method here.
4284  expression_scope()->RecordThisUse();
4285  UseThis();
4286  return impl()->NewSuperCallReference(pos);
4287  }
4288  }
4289 
4290  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4291  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedSuper);
4292  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4293 }
4294 
4295 template <typename Impl>
4296 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4297 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseNewTargetExpression() {
4298  int pos = position();
4299  Consume(Token::kPeriod);
4300  ExpectContextualKeyword(ast_value_factory()->target_string(), "new.target",
4301  pos);
4302 
4303  if (!GetReceiverScope()->is_function_scope()) {
4304  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4305  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedNewTarget);
4306  return impl()->FailureExpression();
4307  }
4308 
4309  return impl()->NewTargetExpression(pos);
4310 }
