4312 template <typename Impl>
4313 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
4314 ParserBase<Impl>::DoParseMemberExpressionContinuation(ExpressionT expression) {
4315  DCHECK(Token::IsMember(peek()));
4316  // Parses this part of MemberExpression:
4317  // ('[' Expression ']' | '.' Identifier | TemplateLiteral)*
4318  do {
4319  switch (peek()) {
4320  case Token::kLeftBracket: {
4321  Consume(Token::kLeftBracket);
4322  int pos = position();
4323  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
4324  ExpressionT index = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
4325  expression = factory()->NewProperty(expression, index, pos);
4326  impl()->PushPropertyName(index);
4327  Expect(Token::kRightBracket);
4328  break;
4329  }
4330  case Token::kPeriod: {
4331  Consume(Token::kPeriod);
4332  int pos = peek_position();
4333  ExpressionT key = ParsePropertyOrPrivatePropertyName();
4334  expression = factory()->NewProperty(expression, key, pos);
4335  break;
4336  }
4337  default: {
4338  DCHECK(Token::IsTemplate(peek()));
4339  int pos;
4340  if (scanner()->current_token() == Token::kIdentifier) {
4341  pos = position();
4342  } else {
4343  pos = peek_position();
4344  if (expression->IsFunctionLiteral()) {
4345  // If the tag function looks like an IIFE, set_parenthesized() to
4346  // force eager compilation.
4347  expression->AsFunctionLiteral()->SetShouldEagerCompile();
4348  }
4349  }
4350  expression = ParseTemplateLiteral(expression, pos, true);
4351  break;
4352  }
4353  }
4354  } while (Token::IsMember(peek()));
4355  return expression;
4356 }
4357 
4358 template <typename Impl>
4359 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseFormalParameter(FormalParametersT* parameters) {
4360  // FormalParameter[Yield,GeneratorParameter] :
4361  // BindingElement[?Yield, ?GeneratorParameter]
4362  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
4363  int pos = peek_position();
4364  auto declaration_it = scope()->declarations()->end();
4365  ExpressionT pattern = ParseBindingPattern();
4366  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(pattern)) {
4367  ClassifyParameter(impl()->AsIdentifier(pattern), pos, end_position());
4368  } else {
4369  parameters->is_simple = false;
4370  }
4371 
4372  ExpressionT initializer = impl()->NullExpression();
4373  if (Check(Token::kAssign)) {
4374  parameters->is_simple = false;
4375 
4376  if (parameters->has_rest) {
4377  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kRestDefaultInitializer);
4378  return;
4379  }
4380 
4381  AcceptINScope accept_in_scope(this, true);
4382  initializer = ParseAssignmentExpression();
4383  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromIdentifierRef(initializer, pattern);
4384  }
4385 
4386  auto declaration_end = scope()->declarations()->end();
4387  int initializer_end = end_position();
4388  for (; declaration_it != declaration_end; ++declaration_it) {
4389  Variable* var = declaration_it->var();
4390 
4391  // The first time a variable is initialized (i.e. when the initializer
4392  // position is unset), clear its maybe_assigned flag as it is not a true
4393  // assignment. Since this is done directly on the Variable objects, it has
4394  // no effect on VariableProxy objects appearing on the left-hand side of
4395  // true assignments, so x will be still be marked as maybe_assigned for:
4396  // (x = 1, y = (x = 2)) => {}
4397  // and even:
4398  // (x = (x = 2)) => {}.
4399  if (var->initializer_position() == kNoSourcePosition)
4400  var->clear_maybe_assigned();
4401  var->set_initializer_position(initializer_end);
4402  }
4403 
4404  impl()->AddFormalParameter(parameters, pattern, initializer, end_position(),
4405  parameters->has_rest);
4406 }
4407 
4408 template <typename Impl>
4409 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseFormalParameterList(FormalParametersT* parameters) {
4410  // FormalParameters[Yield] :
4411  // [empty]
4412  // FunctionRestParameter[?Yield]
4413  // FormalParameterList[?Yield]
4414  // FormalParameterList[?Yield] ,
4415  // FormalParameterList[?Yield] , FunctionRestParameter[?Yield]
4416  //
4417  // FormalParameterList[Yield] :
4418  // FormalParameter[?Yield]
4419  // FormalParameterList[?Yield] , FormalParameter[?Yield]
4420  ParameterParsingScope scope(impl(), parameters);
4421 
4422  DCHECK_EQ(0, parameters->arity);
4423 
4424  if (peek() != Token::kRightParen) {
4425  while (true) {
4426  parameters->has_rest = Check(Token::kEllipsis);
4427  ParseFormalParameter(parameters);
4428 
4429  if (parameters->has_rest) {
4430  parameters->is_simple = false;
4431  if (peek() == Token::kComma) {
4432  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
4433  MessageTemplate::kParamAfterRest);
4434  return;
4435  }
4436  break;
4437  }
4438  if (!Check(Token::kComma)) break;
4439  if (peek() == Token::kRightParen) {
4440  // allow the trailing comma
4441  break;
4442  }
4443  }
4444  }
4445 
4446  if (parameters->arity + 1 /* receiver */ > Code::kMaxArguments) {
4447  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kTooManyParameters);
4448  return;
4449  }
4450 
4451  impl()->DeclareFormalParameters(parameters);
4452 }
4453 
4454 template <typename Impl>
4455 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseVariableDeclarations(
4456  VariableDeclarationContext var_context,
4457  DeclarationParsingResult* parsing_result,
4458  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names) {
4459  // VariableDeclarations ::
4460  // ('var' | 'const' | 'let' | 'using' | 'await using') (Identifier ('='
4461  // AssignmentExpression)?)+[',']
4462  //
4463  // ES6:
4464  // FIXME(marja, nikolaos): Add an up-to-date comment about ES6 variable
4465  // declaration syntax.
4466 
4467  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(parsing_result);
4468  parsing_result->descriptor.kind = NORMAL_VARIABLE;
4469  parsing_result->descriptor.declaration_pos = peek_position();
4470  parsing_result->descriptor.initialization_pos = peek_position();
4471 
4472  Scope* target_scope = scope();
4473 
4474  switch (peek()) {
4475  case Token::kVar:
4476  parsing_result->descriptor.mode = VariableMode::kVar;
4477  target_scope = scope()->GetDeclarationScope();
4478  Consume(Token::kVar);
4479  break;
4480  case Token::kConst:
4481  Consume(Token::kConst);
4482  DCHECK_NE(var_context, kStatement);
4483  parsing_result->descriptor.mode = VariableMode::kConst;
4484  break;
4485  case Token::kLet:
4486  Consume(Token::kLet);
4487  DCHECK_NE(var_context, kStatement);
4488  parsing_result->descriptor.mode = VariableMode::kLet;
4489  break;
4490  case Token::kUsing:
4491  // using [no LineTerminator here] BindingList[?In, ?Yield, ?Await,
4492  // ~Pattern] ;
4493  Consume(Token::kUsing);
4494  DCHECK(v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management);
4495  DCHECK_NE(var_context, kStatement);
4496  DCHECK(is_using_allowed());
4497  DCHECK(!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext());
4498  DCHECK(peek() != Token::kLeftBracket && peek() != Token::kLeftBrace);
4499  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kExplicitResourceManagement);
4500  parsing_result->descriptor.mode = VariableMode::kUsing;
4501  break;
4502  case Token::kAwait:
4503  // CoverAwaitExpressionAndAwaitUsingDeclarationHead[?Yield] [no
4504  // LineTerminator here] BindingList[?In, ?Yield, +Await, ~Pattern];
4505  Consume(Token::kAwait);
4506  DCHECK(v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management);
4507  DCHECK_NE(var_context, kStatement);
4508  DCHECK(is_using_allowed());
4509  DCHECK(is_await_allowed());
4510  Consume(Token::kUsing);
4511  DCHECK(!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext());
4512  DCHECK(peek() != Token::kLeftBracket && peek() != Token::kLeftBrace);
4513  impl()->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kExplicitResourceManagement);
4514  parsing_result->descriptor.mode = VariableMode::kAwaitUsing;
4515  if (!target_scope->has_await_using_declaration()) {
4516  function_state_->AddSuspend();
4517  }
4518  break;
4519  default:
4520  UNREACHABLE(); // by current callers
4521  break;
4522  }
4523 
4524  VariableDeclarationParsingScope declaration(
4525  impl(), parsing_result->descriptor.mode, names);
4526 
4527  auto declaration_it = target_scope->declarations()->end();
4528 
4529  int bindings_start = peek_position();
4530  do {
4531  // Parse binding pattern.
4532  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
4533 
4534  int decl_pos = peek_position();
4535 
4536  IdentifierT name;
4537  ExpressionT pattern;
4538  // Check for an identifier first, so that we can elide the pattern in cases
4539  // where there is no initializer (and so no proxy needs to be created).
4540  if (V8_LIKELY(Token::IsAnyIdentifier(peek()))) {
4541  name = ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(Next());
4542  if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_strict(language_mode()) &&
4543  impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(name))) {
4544  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
4545  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
4546  return;
4547  }
4548  if (peek() == Token::kAssign ||
4549  (var_context == kForStatement && PeekInOrOf()) ||
4550  parsing_result->descriptor.mode == VariableMode::kLet) {
4551  // Assignments need the variable expression for the assignment LHS, and
4552  // for of/in will need it later, so create the expression now.
4553  pattern = impl()->ExpressionFromIdentifier(name, decl_pos);
4554  } else {
4555  // Otherwise, elide the variable expression and just declare it.
4556  impl()->DeclareIdentifier(name, decl_pos);
4557  pattern = impl()->NullExpression();
4558  }
4559  } else if (parsing_result->descriptor.mode != VariableMode::kUsing &&
4560  parsing_result->descriptor.mode != VariableMode::kAwaitUsing) {
4561  name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
4562  pattern = ParseBindingPattern();
4563  DCHECK(!impl()->IsIdentifier(pattern));
4564  } else {
4565  // `using` declarations should have an identifier.
4566  impl()->ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(decl_pos, end_position()),
4567  MessageTemplate::kDeclarationMissingInitializer,
4568  "using");
4569  return;
4570  }
4571 
4572  Scanner::Location variable_loc = scanner()->location();
4573 
4574  ExpressionT value = impl()->NullExpression();
4575  int value_beg_pos = kNoSourcePosition;
4576  if (Check(Token::kAssign)) {
4577  DCHECK(!impl()->IsNull(pattern));
4578  {
4579  value_beg_pos = peek_position();
4580  AcceptINScope scope(this, var_context != kForStatement);
4581  value = ParseAssignmentExpression();
4582  }
4583  variable_loc.end_pos = end_position();
4584 
4585  if (!parsing_result->first_initializer_loc.IsValid()) {
4586  parsing_result->first_initializer_loc = variable_loc;
4587  }
4588 
4589  // Don't infer if it is "a = function(){...}();"-like expression.
4590  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(pattern)) {
4591  if (!value->IsCall() && !value->IsCallNew()) {
4592  fni_.Infer();
4593  } else {
4594  fni_.RemoveLastFunction();
4595  }
4596  }
4597 
4598  impl()->SetFunctionNameFromIdentifierRef(value, pattern);
4599  } else {
4600 #ifdef DEBUG
4601  // We can fall through into here on error paths, so don't DCHECK those.
4602  if (!has_error()) {
4603  // We should never get identifier patterns for the non-initializer path,
4604  // as those expressions should be elided.
4605  DCHECK_EQ(!impl()->IsNull(name),
4606  Token::IsAnyIdentifier(scanner()->current_token()));
4607  DCHECK_IMPLIES(impl()->IsNull(pattern), !impl()->IsNull(name));
4608  // The only times we have a non-null pattern are:
4609  // 1. This is a destructuring declaration (with no initializer, which
4610  // is immediately an error),
4611  // 2. This is a declaration in a for in/of loop, or
4612  // 3. This is a let (which has an implicit undefined initializer)
4613  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
4614  !impl()->IsNull(pattern),
4615  !impl()->IsIdentifier(pattern) ||
4616  (var_context == kForStatement && PeekInOrOf()) ||
4617  parsing_result->descriptor.mode == VariableMode::kLet);
4618  }
4619 #endif
4620 
4621  if (var_context != kForStatement || !PeekInOrOf()) {
4622  // ES6 'const' and binding patterns require initializers.
4623  if (IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(parsing_result->descriptor.mode) ||
4624  impl()->IsNull(name)) {
4625  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
4626  Scanner::Location(decl_pos, end_position()),
4627  MessageTemplate::kDeclarationMissingInitializer,
4628  impl()->IsNull(name) ? "destructuring"
4629  : ImmutableLexicalVariableModeToString(
4630  parsing_result->descriptor.mode));
4631  return;
4632  }
4633  // 'let x' initializes 'x' to undefined.
4634  if (parsing_result->descriptor.mode == VariableMode::kLet) {
4635  value = factory()->NewUndefinedLiteral(position());
4636  }
4637  }
4638  }
4639 
4640  int initializer_position = end_position();
4641  auto declaration_end = target_scope->declarations()->end();
4642  for (; declaration_it != declaration_end; ++declaration_it) {
4643  declaration_it->var()->set_initializer_position(initializer_position);
4644  }
4645 
4646  // Patterns should be elided iff. they don't have an initializer.
4647  DCHECK_IMPLIES(impl()->IsNull(pattern),
4648  impl()->IsNull(value) ||
4649  (var_context == kForStatement && PeekInOrOf()));
4650 
4651  typename DeclarationParsingResult::Declaration decl(pattern, value);
4652  decl.value_beg_pos = value_beg_pos;
4653 
4654  parsing_result->declarations.push_back(decl);
4655  } while (Check(Token::kComma));
4656 
4657  parsing_result->bindings_loc =
4658  Scanner::Location(bindings_start, end_position());
4659 }
4660 
4661 template <typename Impl>
4662 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
4663 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseFunctionDeclaration() {
4664  Consume(Token::kFunction);
4665 
4666  int pos = position();
4667  ParseFunctionFlags flags = ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal;
4668  if (Check(Token::kMul)) {
4669  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
4670  scanner()->location(),
4671  MessageTemplate::kGeneratorInSingleStatementContext);
4672  return impl()->NullStatement();
4673  }
4674  return ParseHoistableDeclaration(pos, flags, nullptr, false);
4675 }
4676 
4677 template <typename Impl>
4678 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
4679 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseHoistableDeclaration(
4680  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names, bool default_export) {
4681  Consume(Token::kFunction);
4682 
4683  int pos = position();
4684  ParseFunctionFlags flags = ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal;
4685  if (Check(Token::kMul)) {
4686  flags |= ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator;
4687  }
4688  return ParseHoistableDeclaration(pos, flags, names, default_export);
4689 }
4690 
4691 template <typename Impl>
4692 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
4693 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseHoistableDeclaration(
4694  int pos, ParseFunctionFlags flags, ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names,
4695  bool default_export) {
4696  CheckStackOverflow();
4697 
4698  // FunctionDeclaration ::
4699  // 'function' Identifier '(' FormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
4700  // 'function' '(' FormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
4701  // GeneratorDeclaration ::
4702  // 'function' '*' Identifier '(' FormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
4703  // 'function' '*' '(' FormalParameters ')' '{' FunctionBody '}'
4704  //
4705  // The anonymous forms are allowed iff [default_export] is true.
4706  //
4707  // 'function' and '*' (if present) have been consumed by the caller.
4708 
4709  DCHECK_IMPLIES((flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync) != 0,
4710  (flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator) == 0);
4711 
4712  if ((flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync) != 0 && Check(Token::kMul)) {
4713  // Async generator
4714  flags |= ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator;
4715  }
4716 
4717  IdentifierT name;
4718  FunctionNameValidity name_validity;
4719  IdentifierT variable_name;
4720  if (peek() == Token::kLeftParen) {
4721  if (default_export) {
4722  impl()->GetDefaultStrings(&name, &variable_name);
4723  name_validity = kSkipFunctionNameCheck;
4724  } else {
4725  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kMissingFunctionName);
4726  return impl()->NullStatement();
4727  }
4728  } else {
4729  bool is_strict_reserved = Token::IsStrictReservedWord(peek());
4730  name = ParseIdentifier();
4731  name_validity = is_strict_reserved ? kFunctionNameIsStrictReserved
4732  : kFunctionNameValidityUnknown;
4733  variable_name = name;
4734  }
4735 
4736  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
4737  impl()->PushEnclosingName(name);
4738 
4739  FunctionKind function_kind = FunctionKindFor(flags);
4740 
4741  FunctionLiteralT function = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
4742  name, scanner()->location(), name_validity, function_kind, pos,
4743  FunctionSyntaxKind::kDeclaration, language_mode(), nullptr);
4744 
4745  // In ES6, a function behaves as a lexical binding, except in
4746  // a script scope, or the initial scope of eval or another function.
4747  VariableMode mode =
4748  (!scope()->is_declaration_scope() || scope()->is_module_scope())
4749  ? VariableMode::kLet
4750  : VariableMode::kVar;
4751  // Async functions don't undergo sloppy mode block scoped hoisting, and don't
4752  // allow duplicates in a block. Both are represented by the
4753  // sloppy_block_functions_. Don't add them to the map for async functions.
4754  // Generators are also supposed to be prohibited; currently doing this behind
4755  // a flag and UseCounting violations to assess web compatibility.
4756  VariableKind kind = is_sloppy(language_mode()) &&
4757  !scope()->is_declaration_scope() &&
4758  flags == ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal
4759  ? SLOPPY_BLOCK_FUNCTION_VARIABLE
4760  : NORMAL_VARIABLE;
4761 
4762  return impl()->DeclareFunction(variable_name, function, mode, kind, pos,
4763  end_position(), names);
4764 }
4765 
4766 template <typename Impl>
4767 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassDeclaration(
4768  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names, bool default_export) {
4769  // ClassDeclaration ::
4770  // 'class' Identifier ('extends' LeftHandExpression)? '{' ClassBody '}'
4771  // 'class' ('extends' LeftHandExpression)? '{' ClassBody '}'
4772  //
4773  // The anonymous form is allowed iff [default_export] is true.
4774  //
4775  // 'class' is expected to be consumed by the caller.
4776  //
4777  // A ClassDeclaration
4778  //
4779  // class C { ... }
4780  //
4781  // has the same semantics as:
4782  //
4783  // let C = class C { ... };
4784  //
4785  // so rewrite it as such.
4786 
4787  int class_token_pos = position();
4788  IdentifierT name = impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
4789  bool is_strict_reserved = Token::IsStrictReservedWord(peek());
4790  IdentifierT variable_name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
4791  if (default_export &&
4792  (peek() == Token::kExtends || peek() == Token::kLeftBrace)) {
4793  impl()->GetDefaultStrings(&name, &variable_name);
4794  } else {
4795  name = ParseIdentifier();
4796  variable_name = name;
4797  }
4798 
4799  ExpressionParsingScope no_expression_scope(impl());
4800  ExpressionT value = ParseClassLiteral(scope(), name, scanner()->location(),
4801  is_strict_reserved, class_token_pos);
4802  no_expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
4803  int end_pos = position();
4804  return impl()->DeclareClass(variable_name, value, names, class_token_pos,
4805  end_pos);
4806 }
4807 
4808 // Language extension which is only enabled for source files loaded
4809 // through the API's extension mechanism. A native function
4810 // declaration is resolved by looking up the function through a
4811 // callback provided by the extension.
4812 template <typename Impl>
4813 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
4814 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseNativeDeclaration() {
4815  function_state_->DisableOptimization(BailoutReason::kNativeFunctionLiteral);
4816 
4817  int pos = peek_position();
4818  Consume(Token::kFunction);
4819  // Allow "eval" or "arguments" for backward compatibility.
4820  IdentifierT name = ParseIdentifier();
4821  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
4822  if (peek() != Token::kRightParen) {
4823  do {
4824  ParseIdentifier();
4825  } while (Check(Token::kComma));
4826  }
4827  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
4828  Expect(Token::kSemicolon);
4829  return impl()->DeclareNative(name, pos);
4830 }
4831 
4832 template <typename Impl>
4833 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
4834 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAsyncFunctionDeclaration(
4835  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names, bool default_export) {
4836  // AsyncFunctionDeclaration ::
4837  // async [no LineTerminator here] function BindingIdentifier[Await]
4838  // ( FormalParameters[Await] ) { AsyncFunctionBody }
4839  DCHECK_EQ(scanner()->current_token(), Token::kAsync);
4840  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
4841  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
4842  }
4843  int pos = position();
4844  DCHECK(!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext());
4845  Consume(Token::kFunction);
4846  ParseFunctionFlags flags = ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync;
4847  return ParseHoistableDeclaration(pos, flags, names, default_export);
4848 }
4849 
4850 template <typename Impl>
4851 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseFunctionBody(
4852  StatementListT* body, IdentifierT function_name, int pos,
4853  const FormalParametersT& parameters, FunctionKind kind,
4854  FunctionSyntaxKind function_syntax_kind, FunctionBodyType body_type) {
4855  CheckStackOverflow();
4856 
4857  if (IsResumableFunction(kind)) impl()->PrepareGeneratorVariables();
4858 
4859  DeclarationScope* function_scope = parameters.scope;
4860  DeclarationScope* inner_scope = function_scope;
4861 
4862  // Building the parameter initialization block declares the parameters.
4863  // TODO(verwaest): Rely on ArrowHeadParsingScope instead.
4864  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!parameters.is_simple)) {
4865  if (has_error()) return;
4866  body->Add(impl()->BuildParameterInitializationBlock(parameters));
4867  if (has_error()) return;
4868 
4869  inner_scope = NewVarblockScope();
4870  inner_scope->set_start_position(position());
4871  }
4872 
4873  StatementListT inner_body(pointer_buffer());
4874 
4875  {
4876  BlockState block_state(&scope_, inner_scope);
4877 
4878  if (body_type == FunctionBodyType::kExpression) {
4879  ExpressionT expression = ParseAssignmentExpression();
4880  inner_body.Add(BuildReturnStatement(expression, expression->position()));
4881  } else {
4882  DCHECK(accept_IN_);
4883  DCHECK_EQ(FunctionBodyType::kBlock, body_type);
4884  // If we are parsing the source as if it is wrapped in a function, the
4885  // source ends without a closing brace.
4886  Token::Value closing_token =
4887  function_syntax_kind == FunctionSyntaxKind::kWrapped
4888  ? Token::kEos
4889  : Token::kRightBrace;
4890 
4891  if (IsAsyncGeneratorFunction(kind)) {
4892  impl()->ParseAsyncGeneratorFunctionBody(pos, kind, &inner_body);
4893  } else if (IsGeneratorFunction(kind)) {
4894  impl()->ParseGeneratorFunctionBody(pos, kind, &inner_body);
4895  } else {
4896  ParseStatementList(&inner_body, closing_token);
4897  if (IsAsyncFunction(kind)) {
4898  inner_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
4899  }
4900  }
4901  if (IsDerivedConstructor(kind)) {
4902  // Derived constructors are implemented by returning `this` when the
4903  // original return value is undefined, so always use `this`.
4904  ExpressionParsingScope expression_scope(impl());
4905  UseThis();
4906  expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
4907  }
4908  Expect(closing_token);
4909  }
4910  }
4911 
4912  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
4913 
4914  bool allow_duplicate_parameters = false;
4915 
4916  CheckConflictingVarDeclarations(inner_scope);
4917 
4918  if (V8_LIKELY(parameters.is_simple)) {
4919  DCHECK_EQ(inner_scope, function_scope);
4920  if (is_sloppy(function_scope->language_mode())) {
4921  impl()->InsertSloppyBlockFunctionVarBindings(function_scope);
4922  }
4923  allow_duplicate_parameters =
4924  is_sloppy(function_scope->language_mode()) && !IsConciseMethod(kind);
4925  } else {
4926  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(inner_scope);
4927  DCHECK_EQ(function_scope, scope());
4928  DCHECK_EQ(function_scope, inner_scope->outer_scope());
4929  impl()->SetLanguageMode(function_scope, inner_scope->language_mode());
4930 
4931  if (is_sloppy(inner_scope->language_mode())) {
4932  impl()->InsertSloppyBlockFunctionVarBindings(inner_scope);
4933  }
4934 
4935  inner_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
4936  if (inner_scope->FinalizeBlockScope() != nullptr) {
4937  BlockT inner_block = factory()->NewBlock(true, inner_body);
4938  inner_body.Rewind();
4939  inner_body.Add(inner_block);
4940  inner_block->set_scope(inner_scope);
4941  impl()->RecordBlockSourceRange(inner_block, scope()->end_position());
4942  if (!impl()->HasCheckedSyntax()) {
4943  const AstRawString* conflict = inner_scope->FindVariableDeclaredIn(
4944  function_scope, VariableMode::kLastLexicalVariableMode);
4945  if (conflict != nullptr) {
4946  impl()->ReportVarRedeclarationIn(conflict, inner_scope);
4947  }
4948  }
4949 
4950  // According to ES#sec-functiondeclarationinstantiation step 27,28
4951  // when hasParameterExpressions is true, we need bind var declared
4952  // arguments to "arguments exotic object", so we here first declare
4953  // "arguments exotic object", then var declared arguments will be
4954  // initialized with "arguments exotic object"
4955  if (!IsArrowFunction(kind)) {
4956  function_scope->DeclareArguments(ast_value_factory());
4957  }
4958 
4959  impl()->InsertShadowingVarBindingInitializers(inner_block);
4960  }
4961  }
4962 
4963  ValidateFormalParameters(language_mode(), parameters,
4964  allow_duplicate_parameters);
4965 
4966  if (!IsArrowFunction(kind)) {
4967  function_scope->DeclareArguments(ast_value_factory());
4968  }
4969 
4970  impl()->DeclareFunctionNameVar(function_name, function_syntax_kind,
4971  function_scope);
4972 
4973  inner_body.MergeInto(body);
4974 }
4975 
4976 template <typename Impl>
4977 void ParserBase<Impl>::CheckArityRestrictions(int param_count,
4978  FunctionKind function_kind,
4979  bool has_rest,
4980  int formals_start_pos,
4981  int formals_end_pos) {
4982  if (impl()->HasCheckedSyntax()) return;
4983  if (IsGetterFunction(function_kind)) {
4984  if (param_count != 0) {
4985  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
4986  Scanner::Location(formals_start_pos, formals_end_pos),
4987  MessageTemplate::kBadGetterArity);
4988  }
4989  } else if (IsSetterFunction(function_kind)) {
4990  if (param_count != 1) {
4991  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
4992  Scanner::Location(formals_start_pos, formals_end_pos),
4993  MessageTemplate::kBadSetterArity);
4994  }
4995  if (has_rest) {
4996  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
4997  Scanner::Location(formals_start_pos, formals_end_pos),
4998  MessageTemplate::kBadSetterRestParameter);
4999  }
5000  }
5001 }
5002 
5003 template <typename Impl>
5004 bool ParserBase<Impl>::IsNextLetKeyword() {
5005  DCHECK_EQ(Token::kLet, peek());
5006  Token::Value next_next = PeekAhead();
5007  switch (next_next) {
5008  case Token::kLeftBrace:
5009  case Token::kLeftBracket:
5010  case Token::kIdentifier:
5011  case Token::kStatic:
5012  case Token::kLet: // `let let;` is disallowed by static semantics, but the
5013  // token must be first interpreted as a keyword in order
5014  // for those semantics to apply. This ensures that ASI is
5015  // not honored when a LineTerminator separates the
5016  // tokens.
5017  case Token::kYield:
5018  case Token::kAwait:
5019  case Token::kGet:
5020  case Token::kSet:
5021  case Token::kOf:
5022  case Token::kUsing:
5023  case Token::kAccessor:
5024  case Token::kAsync:
5025  return true;
5026  case Token::kFutureStrictReservedWord:
5027  case Token::kEscapedStrictReservedWord:
5028  // The early error rule for future reserved keywords
5029  // (ES#sec-identifiers-static-semantics-early-errors) uses the static
5030  // semantics StringValue of IdentifierName, which normalizes escape
5031  // sequences. So, both escaped and unescaped future reserved keywords are
5032  // allowed as identifiers in sloppy mode.
5033  return is_sloppy(language_mode());
5034  default:
5035  return false;
5036  }
5037 }

5039 template <typename Impl>
5040 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
5041 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseArrowFunctionLiteral(
5042  const FormalParametersT& formal_parameters, int function_literal_id,
5043  bool could_be_immediately_invoked) {
5044  RCS_SCOPE(runtime_call_stats_,
5045  Impl::IsPreParser()
5046  ? RuntimeCallCounterId::kPreParseArrowFunctionLiteral
5047  : RuntimeCallCounterId::kParseArrowFunctionLiteral,
5048  RuntimeCallStats::kThreadSpecific);
5049  base::ElapsedTimer timer;
5050  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.log_function_events)) timer.Start();
5051 
5052  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(), peek() == Token::kArrow);
5053  if (!impl()->HasCheckedSyntax() && scanner_->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext()) {
5054  // No line terminator allowed between the parameters and the arrow:
5055  // ArrowFunction[In, Yield, Await] :
5056  // ArrowParameters[?Yield, ?Await] [no LineTerminator here] =>
5057  // ConciseBody[?In]
5058  // If the next token is not `=>`, it's a syntax error anyway.
5059  impl()->ReportUnexpectedTokenAt(scanner_->peek_location(), Token::kArrow);
5060  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5061  }
5062 
5063  int expected_property_count = 0;
5064  int suspend_count = 0;
5065 
5066  FunctionKind kind = formal_parameters.scope->function_kind();
5067  int compile_hint_position = formal_parameters.scope->start_position();
5068  FunctionLiteral::EagerCompileHint eager_compile_hint =
5069  could_be_immediately_invoked ||
5070  (compile_hints_magic_enabled_ &&
5071  scanner_->SawMagicCommentCompileHintsAll()) ||
5072  (compile_hints_per_function_magic_enabled_ &&
5073  scanner_->HasPerFunctionCompileHint(compile_hint_position))
5074  ? FunctionLiteral::kShouldEagerCompile
5075  : default_eager_compile_hint_;
5076 
5077  eager_compile_hint =
5078  impl()->GetEmbedderCompileHint(eager_compile_hint, compile_hint_position);
5079 
5080  bool can_preparse = impl()->parse_lazily() &&
5081  eager_compile_hint == FunctionLiteral::kShouldLazyCompile;
5082  // TODO(marja): consider lazy-parsing inner arrow functions too. is_this
5083  // handling in Scope::ResolveVariable needs to change.
5084  bool is_lazy_top_level_function =
5085  can_preparse && impl()->AllowsLazyParsingWithoutUnresolvedVariables();
5086  bool has_braces = true;
5087  ProducedPreparseData* produced_preparse_data = nullptr;
5088  StatementListT body(pointer_buffer());
5089  {
5090  FunctionState function_state(&function_state_, &scope_,
5091  formal_parameters.scope);
5092 
5093  Consume(Token::kArrow);
5094 
5095  if (peek() == Token::kLeftBrace) {
5096  // Multiple statement body
5097  DCHECK_EQ(scope(), formal_parameters.scope);
5098 
5099  if (is_lazy_top_level_function) {
5100  // FIXME(marja): Arrow function parameters will be parsed even if the
5101  // body is preparsed; move relevant parts of parameter handling to
5102  // simulate consistent parameter handling.
5103 
5104  // Building the parameter initialization block declares the parameters.
5105  // TODO(verwaest): Rely on ArrowHeadParsingScope instead.
5106  if (!formal_parameters.is_simple) {
5107  impl()->BuildParameterInitializationBlock(formal_parameters);
5108  if (has_error()) return impl()->FailureExpression();
5109  }
5110 
5111  // For arrow functions, we don't need to retrieve data about function
5112  // parameters.
5113  int dummy_num_parameters = -1;
5114  int dummy_function_length = -1;
5115  DCHECK(IsArrowFunction(kind));
5116  bool did_preparse_successfully = impl()->SkipFunction(
5117  nullptr, kind, FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression,
5118  formal_parameters.scope, &dummy_num_parameters,
5119  &dummy_function_length, &produced_preparse_data);
5120 
5121  DCHECK_NULL(produced_preparse_data);
5122 
5123  if (did_preparse_successfully) {
5124  // Validate parameter names. We can do this only after preparsing the
5125  // function, since the function can declare itself strict.
5126  ValidateFormalParameters(language_mode(), formal_parameters, false);
5127  } else {
5128  // In case we did not sucessfully preparse the function because of an
5129  // unidentified error we do a full reparse to return the error.
5130  // Parse again in the outer scope, since the language mode may change.
5131  BlockState block_state(&scope_, scope()->outer_scope());
5132  ExpressionT expression = ParseConditionalExpression();
5133  // Reparsing the head may have caused a stack overflow.
5134  if (has_error()) return impl()->FailureExpression();
5135 
5136  DeclarationScope* function_scope = next_arrow_function_info_.scope;
5137  FunctionState inner_function_state(&function_state_, &scope_,
5138  function_scope);
5139  Scanner::Location loc(function_scope->start_position(),
5140  end_position());
5141  FormalParametersT parameters(function_scope);
5142  parameters.is_simple = function_scope->has_simple_parameters();
5143  impl()->DeclareArrowFunctionFormalParameters(&parameters, expression,
5144  loc);
5145  next_arrow_function_info_.Reset();
5146 
5147  Consume(Token::kArrow);
5148  Consume(Token::kLeftBrace);
5149 
5150  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
5151  FunctionParsingScope body_parsing_scope(impl());
5152  ParseFunctionBody(&body, impl()->NullIdentifier(), kNoSourcePosition,
5153  parameters, kind,
5154  FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression,
5155  FunctionBodyType::kBlock);
5156  CHECK(has_error());
5157  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5158  }
5159  } else {
5160  Consume(Token::kLeftBrace);
5161  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
5162  FunctionParsingScope body_parsing_scope(impl());
5163  ParseFunctionBody(&body, impl()->NullIdentifier(), kNoSourcePosition,
5164  formal_parameters, kind,
5165  FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression,
5166  FunctionBodyType::kBlock);
5167  expected_property_count = function_state.expected_property_count();
5168  }
5169  } else {
5170  // Single-expression body
5171  has_braces = false;
5172  FunctionParsingScope body_parsing_scope(impl());
5173  ParseFunctionBody(&body, impl()->NullIdentifier(), kNoSourcePosition,
5174  formal_parameters, kind,
5175  FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression,
5176  FunctionBodyType::kExpression);
5177  expected_property_count = function_state.expected_property_count();
5178  }
5179 
5180  formal_parameters.scope->set_end_position(end_position());
5181 
5182  // Validate strict mode.
5183  if (is_strict(language_mode())) {
5184  CheckStrictOctalLiteral(formal_parameters.scope->start_position(),
5185  end_position());
5186  }
5187  suspend_count = function_state.suspend_count();
5188  }
5189 
5190  FunctionLiteralT function_literal = factory()->NewFunctionLiteral(
5191  impl()->EmptyIdentifierString(), formal_parameters.scope, body,
5192  expected_property_count, formal_parameters.num_parameters(),
5193  formal_parameters.function_length,
5194  FunctionLiteral::kNoDuplicateParameters,
5195  FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression, eager_compile_hint,
5196  formal_parameters.scope->start_position(), has_braces,
5197  function_literal_id, produced_preparse_data);
5198 
5199  function_literal->set_suspend_count(suspend_count);
5200  function_literal->set_function_token_position(
5201  formal_parameters.scope->start_position());
5202 
5203  impl()->RecordFunctionLiteralSourceRange(function_literal);
5204  impl()->AddFunctionForNameInference(function_literal);
5205 
5206  if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.log_function_events)) {
5207  Scope* scope = formal_parameters.scope;
5208  double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();
5209  const char* event_name =
5210  is_lazy_top_level_function ? "preparse-no-resolution" : "parse";
5211  const char* name = "arrow function";
5212  v8_file_logger_->FunctionEvent(event_name, flags().script_id(), ms,
5213  scope->start_position(),
5214  scope->end_position(), name, strlen(name));
5215  }
5216 
5217  return function_literal;
5218 }

5220 template <typename Impl>
5221 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassExpression(
5222  Scope* outer_scope) {
5223  Consume(Token::kClass);
5224  int class_token_pos = position();
5225  IdentifierT name = impl()->EmptyIdentifierString();
5226  bool is_strict_reserved_name = false;
5227  Scanner::Location class_name_location = Scanner::Location::invalid();
5228  if (peek_any_identifier()) {
5229  name = ParseAndClassifyIdentifier(Next());
5230  class_name_location = scanner()->location();
5231  is_strict_reserved_name =
5232  Token::IsStrictReservedWord(scanner()->current_token());
5233  }
5234  return ParseClassLiteral(outer_scope, name, class_name_location,
5235  is_strict_reserved_name, class_token_pos);
5236 }
5237 
5238 template <typename Impl>
5239 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassLiteral(
5240  Scope* outer_scope, IdentifierT name, Scanner::Location class_name_location,
5241  bool name_is_strict_reserved, int class_token_pos) {
5242  bool is_anonymous = impl()->IsEmptyIdentifier(name);
5243 
5244  // All parts of a ClassDeclaration and ClassExpression are strict code.
5245  if (!impl()->HasCheckedSyntax() && !is_anonymous) {
5246  if (name_is_strict_reserved) {
5247  impl()->ReportMessageAt(class_name_location,
5248  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedStrictReserved);
5249  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5250  }
5251  if (impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(name)) {
5252  impl()->ReportMessageAt(class_name_location,
5253  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
5254  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5255  }
5256  }
5257 
5258  ClassScope* class_scope = NewClassScope(outer_scope, is_anonymous);
5259  BlockState block_state(&scope_, class_scope);
5260  RaiseLanguageMode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
5261 
5262  BlockState object_literal_scope_state(&object_literal_scope_, nullptr);
5263 
5264  ClassInfo class_info(this);
5265  class_info.is_anonymous = is_anonymous;
5266 
5267  scope()->set_start_position(class_token_pos);
5268  if (Check(Token::kExtends)) {
5269  ClassScope::HeritageParsingScope heritage(class_scope);
5270  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
5271  ExpressionParsingScope scope(impl());
5272  class_info.extends = ParseLeftHandSideExpression();
5273  scope.ValidateExpression();
5274  }
5275 
5276  Expect(Token::kLeftBrace);
5277 
5278  ParseClassLiteralBody(class_info, name, class_token_pos, Token::kRightBrace);
5279 
5280  CheckStrictOctalLiteral(scope()->start_position(), scope()->end_position());
5281 
5282  VariableProxy* unresolvable = class_scope->ResolvePrivateNamesPartially();
5283  if (unresolvable != nullptr) {
5284  impl()->ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(unresolvable->position(),
5285  unresolvable->position() + 1),
5286  MessageTemplate::kInvalidPrivateFieldResolution,
5287  unresolvable->raw_name());
5288  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5289  }
5290 
5291  if (class_info.requires_brand) {
5292  class_scope->DeclareBrandVariable(
5293  ast_value_factory(), IsStaticFlag::kNotStatic, kNoSourcePosition);
5294  }
5295 
5296  if (class_scope->needs_home_object()) {
5297  class_info.home_object_variable =
5298  class_scope->DeclareHomeObjectVariable(ast_value_factory());
5299  class_info.static_home_object_variable =
5300  class_scope->DeclareStaticHomeObjectVariable(ast_value_factory());
5301  }
5302 
5303  bool should_save_class_variable = class_scope->should_save_class_variable();
5304  if (!class_info.is_anonymous || should_save_class_variable) {
5305  impl()->DeclareClassVariable(class_scope, name, &class_info,
5306  class_token_pos);
5307  if (should_save_class_variable) {
5308  class_scope->class_variable()->set_is_used();
5309  class_scope->class_variable()->ForceContextAllocation();
5310  }
5311  }
5312 
5313  return impl()->RewriteClassLiteral(class_scope, name, &class_info,
5314  class_token_pos);
5315 }
5316 
5317 template <typename Impl>
5318 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseClassLiteralBody(ClassInfo& class_info,
5319  IdentifierT name,
5320  int class_token_pos,
5321  Token::Value end_token) {
5322  bool has_extends = !impl()->IsNull(class_info.extends);
5323 
5324  while (peek() != end_token) {
5325  if (Check(Token::kSemicolon)) continue;
5326 
5327  // Either we're parsing a `static { }` initialization block or a property.
5328  if (peek() == Token::kStatic && PeekAhead() == Token::kLeftBrace) {
5329  BlockT static_block = ParseClassStaticBlock(&class_info);
5330  impl()->AddClassStaticBlock(static_block, &class_info);
5331  continue;
5332  }
5333 
5334  FuncNameInferrerState fni_state(&fni_);
5335  // If we haven't seen the constructor yet, it potentially is the next
5336  // property.
5337  bool is_constructor = !class_info.has_seen_constructor;
5338  ParsePropertyInfo prop_info(this);
5339  prop_info.position = PropertyPosition::kClassLiteral;
5340 
5341  ClassLiteralPropertyT property =
5342  ParseClassPropertyDefinition(&class_info, &prop_info, has_extends);
5343 
5344  if (has_error()) return;
5345 
5346  ClassLiteralProperty::Kind property_kind =
5347  ClassPropertyKindFor(prop_info.kind);
5348 
5349  if (!class_info.has_static_computed_names && prop_info.is_static &&
5350  prop_info.is_computed_name) {
5351  class_info.has_static_computed_names = true;
5352  }
5353  is_constructor &= class_info.has_seen_constructor;
5354 
5355  bool is_field = property_kind == ClassLiteralProperty::FIELD;
5356 
5357  if (V8_UNLIKELY(prop_info.is_private)) {
5358  DCHECK(!is_constructor);
5359  class_info.requires_brand |= (!is_field && !prop_info.is_static);
5360  class_info.has_static_private_methods_or_accessors |=
5361  (prop_info.is_static && !is_field);
5362 
5363  impl()->DeclarePrivateClassMember(scope()->AsClassScope(), prop_info.name,
5364  property, property_kind,
5365  prop_info.is_static, &class_info);
5366  impl()->InferFunctionName();
5367  continue;
5368  }
5369 
5370  if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_field)) {
5371  DCHECK(!prop_info.is_private);
5372  // If we're reparsing, we might not have a class scope. We only need a
5373  // class scope if we have a computed name though, and in that case we're
5374  // certain that the current scope must be a class scope.
5375  ClassScope* class_scope = nullptr;
5376  if (prop_info.is_computed_name) {
5377  class_info.computed_field_count++;
5378  class_scope = scope()->AsClassScope();
5379  }
5380 
5381  impl()->DeclarePublicClassField(class_scope, property,
5382  prop_info.is_static,
5383  prop_info.is_computed_name, &class_info);
5384  impl()->InferFunctionName();
5385  continue;
5386  }
5387 
5388  if (property_kind == ClassLiteralProperty::Kind::AUTO_ACCESSOR) {
5389  // Private auto-accessors are handled above with the other private
5390  // properties.
5391  DCHECK(!prop_info.is_private);
5392  impl()->AddInstanceFieldOrStaticElement(property, &class_info,
5393  prop_info.is_static);
5394  }
5395 
5396  impl()->DeclarePublicClassMethod(name, property, is_constructor,
5397  &class_info);
5398  impl()->InferFunctionName();
5399  }
5400 
5401  Expect(end_token);
5402  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
5403 }
5404 
5405 template <typename Impl>
5406 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
5407 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseAsyncFunctionLiteral() {
5408  // AsyncFunctionLiteral ::
5409  // async [no LineTerminator here] function ( FormalParameters[Await] )
5410  // { AsyncFunctionBody }
5411  //
5412  // async [no LineTerminator here] function BindingIdentifier[Await]
5413  // ( FormalParameters[Await] ) { AsyncFunctionBody }
5414  DCHECK_EQ(scanner()->current_token(), Token::kAsync);
5415  if (V8_UNLIKELY(scanner()->literal_contains_escapes())) {
5416  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(Token::kEscapedKeyword);
5417  }
5418  int pos = position();
5419  Consume(Token::kFunction);
5420  IdentifierT name = impl()->NullIdentifier();
5421  FunctionSyntaxKind syntax_kind = FunctionSyntaxKind::kAnonymousExpression;
5422 
5423  ParseFunctionFlags flags = ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync;
5424  if (Check(Token::kMul)) flags |= ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator;
5425  const FunctionKind kind = FunctionKindFor(flags);
5426  bool is_strict_reserved = Token::IsStrictReservedWord(peek());
5427 
5428  if (impl()->ParsingDynamicFunctionDeclaration()) {
5429  // We don't want dynamic functions to actually declare their name
5430  // "anonymous". We just want that name in the toString().
5431 
5432  // Consuming token we did not peek yet, which could lead to a kIllegal token
5433  // in the case of a stackoverflow.
5434  Consume(Token::kIdentifier);
5435  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(),
5436  scanner()->CurrentSymbol(ast_value_factory()) ==
5437  ast_value_factory()->anonymous_string());
5438  } else if (peek_any_identifier()) {
5439  syntax_kind = FunctionSyntaxKind::kNamedExpression;
5440  name = ParseIdentifier(kind);
5441  }
5442  FunctionLiteralT result = impl()->ParseFunctionLiteral(
5443  name, scanner()->location(),
5444  is_strict_reserved ? kFunctionNameIsStrictReserved
5445  : kFunctionNameValidityUnknown,
5446  kind, pos, syntax_kind, language_mode(), nullptr);
5447  if (impl()->IsNull(result)) return impl()->FailureExpression();
5448  return result;
5449 }
5450 
5451 template <typename Impl>
5452 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseTemplateLiteral(
5453  ExpressionT tag, int start, bool tagged) {
5454  // A TemplateLiteral is made up of 0 or more kTemplateSpan tokens (literal
5455  // text followed by a substitution expression), finalized by a single
5456  // kTemplateTail.
5457  //
5458  // In terms of draft language, kTemplateSpan may be either the TemplateHead or
5459  // TemplateMiddle productions, while kTemplateTail is either TemplateTail, or
5460  // NoSubstitutionTemplate.
5461  //
5462  // When parsing a TemplateLiteral, we must have scanned either an initial
5463  // kTemplateSpan, or a kTemplateTail.
5464  DCHECK(peek() == Token::kTemplateSpan || peek() == Token::kTemplateTail);
5465 
5466  if (tagged) {
5467  // TaggedTemplate expressions prevent the eval compilation cache from being
5468  // used. This flag is only used if an eval is being parsed.
5469  set_allow_eval_cache(false);
5470  }
5471 
5472  bool forbid_illegal_escapes = !tagged;
5473 
5474  // If we reach a kTemplateTail first, we are parsing a NoSubstitutionTemplate.
5475  // In this case we may simply consume the token and build a template with a
5476  // single kTemplateSpan and no expressions.
5477  if (peek() == Token::kTemplateTail) {
5478  Consume(Token::kTemplateTail);
5479  int pos = position();
5480  typename Impl::TemplateLiteralState ts = impl()->OpenTemplateLiteral(pos);
5481  bool is_valid = CheckTemplateEscapes(forbid_illegal_escapes);
5482  impl()->AddTemplateSpan(&ts, is_valid, true);
5483  return impl()->CloseTemplateLiteral(&ts, start, tag);
5484  }
5485 
5486  Consume(Token::kTemplateSpan);
5487  int pos = position();
5488  typename Impl::TemplateLiteralState ts = impl()->OpenTemplateLiteral(pos);
5489  bool is_valid = CheckTemplateEscapes(forbid_illegal_escapes);
5490  impl()->AddTemplateSpan(&ts, is_valid, false);
5491  Token::Value next;
5492 
5493  // If we open with a kTemplateSpan, we must scan the subsequent expression,
5494  // and repeat if the following token is a kTemplateSpan as well (in this
5495  // case, representing a TemplateMiddle).
5496 
5497  do {
5498  next = peek();
5499 
5500  int expr_pos = peek_position();
5501  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
5502  ExpressionT expression = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
5503  impl()->AddTemplateExpression(&ts, expression);
5504 
5505  if (peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
5506  impl()->ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(expr_pos, peek_position()),
5507  MessageTemplate::kUnterminatedTemplateExpr);
5508  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5509  }
5510 
5511  // If we didn't die parsing that expression, our next token should be a
5512  // kTemplateSpan or kTemplateTail.
5513  next = scanner()->ScanTemplateContinuation();
5514  Next();
5515  pos = position();
5516 
5517  is_valid = CheckTemplateEscapes(forbid_illegal_escapes);
5518  impl()->AddTemplateSpan(&ts, is_valid, next == Token::kTemplateTail);
5519  } while (next == Token::kTemplateSpan);
5520 
5521  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_error(), next == Token::kTemplateTail);
5522  // Once we've reached a kTemplateTail, we can close the TemplateLiteral.
5523  return impl()->CloseTemplateLiteral(&ts, start, tag);
5524 }
5525 
5526 template <typename Impl>
5527 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
5528 ParserBase<Impl>::RewriteInvalidReferenceExpression(ExpressionT expression,
5529  int beg_pos, int end_pos,
5530  MessageTemplate message,
5531  bool early_error) {
5532  DCHECK(!IsValidReferenceExpression(expression));
5533  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(expression)) {
5534  DCHECK(is_strict(language_mode()));
5535  DCHECK(impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(impl()->AsIdentifier(expression)));
5536 
5537  ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(beg_pos, end_pos),
5538  MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
5539  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5540  }
5541  if (expression->IsCall() && !expression->AsCall()->is_tagged_template() &&
5542  !early_error) {
5543  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
5544  Scanner::Location(beg_pos, end_pos),
5545  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
5546  // If it is a call, make it a runtime error for legacy web compatibility.
5547  // Bug: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/v8/issues/detail?id=4480
5548  // Rewrite `expr' to `expr[throw ReferenceError]'.
5549  impl()->CountUsage(
5550  is_strict(language_mode())
5551  ? v8::Isolate::kAssigmentExpressionLHSIsCallInStrict
5552  : v8::Isolate::kAssigmentExpressionLHSIsCallInSloppy);
5553  ExpressionT error = impl()->NewThrowReferenceError(message, beg_pos);
5554  return factory()->NewProperty(expression, error, beg_pos);
5555  }
5556  // Tagged templates and other modern language features (which pass early_error
5557  // = true) are exempt from the web compatibility hack. Throw a regular early
5558  // error.
5559  ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(beg_pos, end_pos), message);
5560  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5561 }
5562 
5563 template <typename Impl>
5564 void ParserBase<Impl>::ClassifyParameter(IdentifierT parameter, int begin,
5565  int end) {
5566  if (impl()->IsEvalOrArguments(parameter)) {
5567  expression_scope()->RecordStrictModeParameterError(
5568  Scanner::Location(begin, end), MessageTemplate::kStrictEvalArguments);
5569  }
5570 }
5571 
5572 template <typename Impl>
5573 void ParserBase<Impl>::ClassifyArrowParameter(
5574  AccumulationScope* accumulation_scope, int position,
5575  ExpressionT parameter) {
5576  accumulation_scope->Accumulate();
5577  if (parameter->is_parenthesized() ||
5578  !(impl()->IsIdentifier(parameter) || parameter->IsPattern() ||
5579  parameter->IsAssignment())) {
5580  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
5581  Scanner::Location(position, end_position()),
5582  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
5583  } else if (impl()->IsIdentifier(parameter)) {
5584  ClassifyParameter(impl()->AsIdentifier(parameter), position,
5585  end_position());
5586  } else {
5587  expression_scope()->RecordNonSimpleParameter();
5588  }
5589 }
5590 
5591 template <typename Impl>
5592 bool ParserBase<Impl>::IsValidReferenceExpression(ExpressionT expression) {
5593  return IsAssignableIdentifier(expression) || expression->IsProperty();
5594 }
5595 
5596 template <typename Impl>
5597 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT
5598 ParserBase<Impl>::ParsePossibleDestructuringSubPattern(
5599  AccumulationScope* scope) {
5600  if (scope) scope->Accumulate();
5601  int begin = peek_position();
5602  ExpressionT result = ParseAssignmentExpressionCoverGrammar();
5603 
5604  if (IsValidReferenceExpression(result)) {
5605  // Parenthesized identifiers and property references are allowed as part of
5606  // a larger assignment pattern, even though parenthesized patterns
5607  // themselves are not allowed, e.g., "[(x)] = []". Only accumulate
5608  // assignment pattern errors if the parsed expression is more complex.
5609  if (impl()->IsIdentifier(result)) {
5610  if (result->is_parenthesized()) {
5611  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
5612  Scanner::Location(begin, end_position()),
5613  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
5614  }
5615  IdentifierT identifier = impl()->AsIdentifier(result);
5616  ClassifyParameter(identifier, begin, end_position());
5617  } else {
5618  DCHECK(result->IsProperty());
5619  expression_scope()->RecordDeclarationError(
5620  Scanner::Location(begin, end_position()),
5621  MessageTemplate::kInvalidPropertyBindingPattern);
5622  if (scope != nullptr) scope->ValidateExpression();
5623  }
5624  } else if (result->is_parenthesized() ||
5625  (!result->IsPattern() && !result->IsAssignment())) {
5626  expression_scope()->RecordPatternError(
5627  Scanner::Location(begin, end_position()),
5628  MessageTemplate::kInvalidDestructuringTarget);
5629  }
5630 
5631  return result;
5632 }
5633 
5634 template <typename Impl>
5635 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ExpressionT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseV8Intrinsic() {
5636  // CallRuntime ::
5637  // '%' Identifier Arguments
5638 
5639  int pos = peek_position();
5640  Consume(Token::kMod);
5641  // Allow "eval" or "arguments" for backward compatibility.
5642  IdentifierT name = ParseIdentifier();
5643  if (peek() != Token::kLeftParen) {
5644  impl()->ReportUnexpectedToken(peek());
5645  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5646  }
5647  bool has_spread;
5648  ExpressionListT args(pointer_buffer());
5649  ParseArguments(&args, &has_spread);
5650 
5651  if (has_spread) {
5652  ReportMessageAt(Scanner::Location(pos, position()),
5653  MessageTemplate::kIntrinsicWithSpread);
5654  return impl()->FailureExpression();
5655  }
5656 
5657  return impl()->NewV8Intrinsic(name, args, pos);
5658 }
5659 
5660 template <typename Impl>
5661 void ParserBase<Impl>::ParseStatementList(StatementListT* body,
5662  Token::Value end_token) {
5663  // StatementList ::
5664  // (StatementListItem)* <end_token>
5665  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(body);
5666 
5667  while (peek() == Token::kString) {
5668  bool use_strict = false;
5669 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5670  bool use_asm = false;
5671 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5672 
5673  Scanner::Location token_loc = scanner()->peek_location();
5674 
5675  if (scanner()->NextLiteralExactlyEquals("use strict")) {
5676  use_strict = true;
5677 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5678  } else if (scanner()->NextLiteralExactlyEquals("use asm")) {
5679  use_asm = true;
5680 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5681  }
5682 
5683  StatementT stat = ParseStatementListItem();
5684  if (impl()->IsNull(stat)) return;
5685 
5686  body->Add(stat);
5687 
5688  if (!impl()->IsStringLiteral(stat)) break;
5689 
5690  if (use_strict) {
5691  // Directive "use strict" (ES5 14.1).
5692  RaiseLanguageMode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
5693  if (!scope()->HasSimpleParameters()) {
5694  // TC39 deemed "use strict" directives to be an error when occurring
5695  // in the body of a function with non-simple parameter list, on
5696  // 29/7/2015. See:
5697  // https://github.com/tc39/notes/blob/main/meetings/2015-07/july-29.md#conclusionresolution
5698  impl()->ReportMessageAt(token_loc,
5699  MessageTemplate::kIllegalLanguageModeDirective,
5700  "use strict");
5701  return;
5702  }
5703 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5704  } else if (use_asm) {
5705  // Directive "use asm".
5706  impl()->SetAsmModule();
5707 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5708  } else {
5709  // Possibly an unknown directive.
5710  // Should not change mode, but will increment usage counters
5711  // as appropriate. Ditto usages below.
5712  RaiseLanguageMode(LanguageMode::kSloppy);
5713  }
5714  }
5715 
5716  while (peek() != end_token) {
5717  StatementT stat = ParseStatementListItem();
5718  if (impl()->IsNull(stat)) return;
5719  if (stat->IsEmptyStatement()) continue;
5720  body->Add(stat);
5721  }
5722 }
5723 
5724 template <typename Impl>
5725 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
5726 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseStatementListItem() {
5727  // ECMA 262 6th Edition
5728  // StatementListItem[Yield, Return] :
5729  // Statement[?Yield, ?Return]
5730  // Declaration[?Yield]
5731  //
5732  // Declaration[Yield] :
5733  // HoistableDeclaration[?Yield]
5734  // ClassDeclaration[?Yield]
5735  // LexicalDeclaration[In, ?Yield]
5736  //
5737  // HoistableDeclaration[Yield, Default] :
5738  // FunctionDeclaration[?Yield, ?Default]
5739  // GeneratorDeclaration[?Yield, ?Default]
5740  //
5741  // LexicalDeclaration[In, Yield, Await] :
5742  // LetOrConst BindingList[?In, ?Yield, ?Await, +Pattern] ;
5743  // UsingDeclaration[?In, ?Yield, ?Await, ~Pattern];
5744  // [+Await] AwaitUsingDeclaration[?In, ?Yield];
5745 
5746  switch (peek()) {
5747  case Token::kFunction:
5748  return ParseHoistableDeclaration(nullptr, false);
5749  case Token::kClass:
5750  Consume(Token::kClass);
5751  return ParseClassDeclaration(nullptr, false);
5752  case Token::kVar:
5753  case Token::kConst:
5754  return ParseVariableStatement(kStatementListItem, nullptr);
5755  case Token::kLet:
5756  if (IsNextLetKeyword()) {
5757  return ParseVariableStatement(kStatementListItem, nullptr);
5758  }
5759  break;
5760  case Token::kUsing:
5761  if (!v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management) break;
5762  if (!is_using_allowed()) break;
5763  if (!(scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext()) &&
5764  Token::IsAnyIdentifier(PeekAhead())) {
5765  return ParseVariableStatement(kStatementListItem, nullptr);
5766  }
5767  break;
5768  case Token::kAwait:
5769  if (!v8_flags.js_explicit_resource_management) break;
5770  if (!is_await_allowed()) break;
5771  if (!is_using_allowed()) break;
5772  if (!(scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext()) &&
5773  PeekAhead() == Token::kUsing &&
5774  !(scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNextNext()) &&
5775  Token::IsAnyIdentifier(PeekAheadAhead())) {
5776  return ParseVariableStatement(kStatementListItem, nullptr);
5777  }
5778  break;
5779  case Token::kAsync:
5780  if (PeekAhead() == Token::kFunction &&
5781  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext()) {
5782  Consume(Token::kAsync);
5783  return ParseAsyncFunctionDeclaration(nullptr, false);
5784  }
5785  break;
5786  default:
5787  break;
5788  }
5789  return ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr, kAllowLabelledFunctionStatement);
5790 }
5791 
5792 template <typename Impl>
5793 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseStatement(
5794  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
5795  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels,
5796  AllowLabelledFunctionStatement allow_function) {
5797  // Statement ::
5798  // Block
5799  // VariableStatement
5800  // EmptyStatement
5801  // ExpressionStatement
5802  // IfStatement
5803  // IterationStatement
5804  // ContinueStatement
5805  // BreakStatement
5806  // ReturnStatement
5807  // WithStatement
5808  // LabelledStatement
5809  // SwitchStatement
5810  // ThrowStatement
5811  // TryStatement
5812  // DebuggerStatement
5813 
5814  // {own_labels} is always a subset of {labels}.
5815  DCHECK_IMPLIES(labels == nullptr, own_labels == nullptr);
5816 
5817  // Note: Since labels can only be used by 'break' and 'continue'
5818  // statements, which themselves are only valid within blocks,
5819  // iterations or 'switch' statements (i.e., BreakableStatements),
5820  // labels can be simply ignored in all other cases; except for
5821  // trivial labeled break statements 'label: break label' which is
5822  // parsed into an empty statement.
5823  switch (peek()) {
5824  case Token::kLeftBrace:
5825  return ParseBlock(labels);
5826  case Token::kSemicolon:
5827  Next();
5828  return factory()->EmptyStatement();
5829  case Token::kIf:
5830  return ParseIfStatement(labels);
5831  case Token::kDo:
5832  return ParseDoWhileStatement(labels, own_labels);
5833  case Token::kWhile:
5834  return ParseWhileStatement(labels, own_labels);
5835  case Token::kFor:
5836  if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_await_allowed() && PeekAhead() == Token::kAwait)) {
5837  return ParseForAwaitStatement(labels, own_labels);
5838  }
5839  return ParseForStatement(labels, own_labels);
5840  case Token::kContinue:
5841  return ParseContinueStatement();
5842  case Token::kBreak:
5843  return ParseBreakStatement(labels);
5844  case Token::kReturn:
5845  return ParseReturnStatement();
5846  case Token::kThrow:
5847  return ParseThrowStatement();
5848  case Token::kTry: {
5849  // It is somewhat complicated to have labels on try-statements.
5850  // When breaking out of a try-finally statement, one must take
5851  // great care not to treat it as a fall-through. It is much easier
5852  // just to wrap the entire try-statement in a statement block and
5853  // put the labels there.
5854  if (labels == nullptr) return ParseTryStatement();
5855  StatementListT statements(pointer_buffer());
5856  BlockT result = factory()->NewBlock(false, true);
5857  Target target(this, result, labels, nullptr,
5858  Target::TARGET_FOR_NAMED_ONLY);
5859  StatementT statement = ParseTryStatement();
5860  statements.Add(statement);
5861  result->InitializeStatements(statements, zone());
5862  return result;
5863  }
5864  case Token::kWith:
5865  return ParseWithStatement(labels);
5866  case Token::kSwitch:
5867  return ParseSwitchStatement(labels);
5868  case Token::kFunction:
5869  // FunctionDeclaration only allowed as a StatementListItem, not in
5870  // an arbitrary Statement position. Exceptions such as
5871  // ES#sec-functiondeclarations-in-ifstatement-statement-clauses
5872  // are handled by calling ParseScopedStatement rather than
5873  // ParseStatement directly.
5874  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
5875  is_strict(language_mode())
5876  ? MessageTemplate::kStrictFunction
5877  : MessageTemplate::kSloppyFunction);
5878  return impl()->NullStatement();
5879  case Token::kDebugger:
5880  return ParseDebuggerStatement();
5881  case Token::kVar:
5882  return ParseVariableStatement(kStatement, nullptr);
5883  case Token::kAsync:
5884  if (!impl()->HasCheckedSyntax() &&
5885  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext() &&
5886  PeekAhead() == Token::kFunction) {
5887  impl()->ReportMessageAt(
5888  scanner()->peek_location(),
5889  MessageTemplate::kAsyncFunctionInSingleStatementContext);
5890  return impl()->NullStatement();
5891  }
5892  [[fallthrough]];
5893  default:
5894  return ParseExpressionOrLabelledStatement(labels, own_labels,
5895  allow_function);
5896  }
5897 }
5898 
5899 template <typename Impl>
5900 typename ParserBase<Impl>::BlockT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBlock(
5901  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels, Scope* block_scope) {
5902  // Block ::
5903  // '{' StatementList '}'
5904 
5905  // Parse the statements and collect escaping labels.
5906  BlockT body = factory()->NewBlock(false, labels != nullptr);
5907  StatementListT statements(pointer_buffer());
5908 
5909  CheckStackOverflow();
5910 
5911  {
5912  BlockState block_state(&scope_, block_scope);
5913  scope()->set_start_position(peek_position());
5914  Target target(this, body, labels, nullptr, Target::TARGET_FOR_NAMED_ONLY);
5915 
5916  Expect(Token::kLeftBrace);
5917 
5918  while (peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
5919  StatementT stat = ParseStatementListItem();
5920  if (impl()->IsNull(stat)) return body;
5921  if (stat->IsEmptyStatement()) continue;
5922  statements.Add(stat);
5923  }
5924 
5925  Expect(Token::kRightBrace);
5926 
5927  int end_pos = end_position();
5928  scope()->set_end_position(end_pos);
5929 
5930  impl()->RecordBlockSourceRange(body, end_pos);
5931  body->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
5932  }
5933 
5934  body->InitializeStatements(statements, zone());
5935  return body;
5936 }
5937 
5938 template <typename Impl>
5939 typename ParserBase<Impl>::BlockT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBlock(
5940  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
5941  return ParseBlock(labels, NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE));
5942 }
5943 
5944 template <typename Impl>
5945 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseScopedStatement(
5946  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
5947  if (is_strict(language_mode()) || peek() != Token::kFunction) {
5948  return ParseStatement(labels, nullptr);
5949  } else {
5950  // Make a block around the statement for a lexical binding
5951  // is introduced by a FunctionDeclaration.
5952  BlockState block_state(zone(), &scope_);
5953  scope()->set_start_position(scanner()->location().beg_pos);
5954  BlockT block = factory()->NewBlock(1, false);
5955  StatementT body = ParseFunctionDeclaration();
5956  block->statements()->Add(body, zone());
5957  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
5958  block->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
5959  return block;
5960  }
5961 }
5962 
5963 template <typename Impl>
5964 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseVariableStatement(
5965  VariableDeclarationContext var_context,
5966  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* names) {
5967  // VariableStatement ::
5968  // VariableDeclarations ';'
5969 
5970  // The scope of a var declared variable anywhere inside a function
5971  // is the entire function (ECMA-262, 3rd, 10.1.3, and 12.2). Thus we can
5972  // transform a source-level var declaration into a (Function) Scope
5973  // declaration, and rewrite the source-level initialization into an assignment
5974  // statement. We use a block to collect multiple assignments.
5975  //
5976  // We mark the block as initializer block because we don't want the
5977  // rewriter to add a '.result' assignment to such a block (to get compliant
5978  // behavior for code such as print(eval('var x = 7')), and for cosmetic
5979  // reasons when pretty-printing. Also, unless an assignment (initialization)
5980  // is inside an initializer block, it is ignored.
5981 
5982  DeclarationParsingResult parsing_result;
5983  ParseVariableDeclarations(var_context, &parsing_result, names);
5984  ExpectSemicolon();
5985  return impl()->BuildInitializationBlock(&parsing_result);
5986 }
5987 
5988 template <typename Impl>
5989 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
5990 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseDebuggerStatement() {
5991  // In ECMA-262 'debugger' is defined as a reserved keyword. In some browser
5992  // contexts this is used as a statement which invokes the debugger as i a
5993  // break point is present.
5994  // DebuggerStatement ::
5995  // 'debugger' ';'
5996 
5997  int pos = peek_position();
5998  Consume(Token::kDebugger);
5999  ExpectSemicolon();
6000  return factory()->NewDebuggerStatement(pos);
6001 }
6002 
6003 template <typename Impl>
6004 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
6005 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseExpressionOrLabelledStatement(
6006  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6007  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels,
6008  AllowLabelledFunctionStatement allow_function) {
6009  // ExpressionStatement | LabelledStatement ::
6010  // Expression ';'
6011  // Identifier ':' Statement
6012  //
6013  // ExpressionStatement[Yield] :
6014  // [lookahead notin {{, function, class, let [}] Expression[In, ?Yield] ;
6015 
6016  int pos = peek_position();
6017 
6018  switch (peek()) {
6019  case Token::kFunction:
6020  case Token::kLeftBrace:
6021  UNREACHABLE(); // Always handled by the callers.
6022  case Token::kClass:
6023  ReportUnexpectedToken(Next());
6024  return impl()->NullStatement();
6025  case Token::kLet: {
6026  Token::Value next_next = PeekAhead();
6027  // "let" followed by either "[", "{" or an identifier means a lexical
6028  // declaration, which should not appear here.
6029  // However, ASI may insert a line break before an identifier or a brace.
6030  if (next_next != Token::kLeftBracket &&
6031  ((next_next != Token::kLeftBrace &&
6032  next_next != Token::kIdentifier) ||
6033  scanner_->HasLineTerminatorAfterNext())) {
6034  break;
6035  }
6036  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
6037  MessageTemplate::kUnexpectedLexicalDeclaration);
6038  return impl()->NullStatement();
6039  }
6040  default:
6041  break;
6042  }
6043 
6044  bool starts_with_identifier = peek_any_identifier();
6045 
6046  ExpressionT expr;
6047  {
6048  // Effectively inlines ParseExpression, so potential labels can be extracted
6049  // from expression_scope.
6050  ExpressionParsingScope expression_scope(impl());
6051  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
6052  expr = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
6053  expression_scope.ValidateExpression();
6054 
6055  if (peek() == Token::kColon && starts_with_identifier &&
6056  impl()->IsIdentifier(expr)) {
6057  // The whole expression was a single identifier, and not, e.g.,
6058  // something starting with an identifier or a parenthesized identifier.
6059  DCHECK_EQ(expression_scope.variable_list()->length(), 1);
6060  VariableProxy* label = expression_scope.variable_list()->at(0).first;
6061  impl()->DeclareLabel(&labels, &own_labels, label->raw_name());
6062 
6063  // Remove the "ghost" variable that turned out to be a label from the top
6064  // scope. This way, we don't try to resolve it during the scope
6065  // processing.
6066  this->scope()->DeleteUnresolved(label);
6067 
6068  Consume(Token::kColon);
6069  // ES#sec-labelled-function-declarations Labelled Function Declarations
6070  if (peek() == Token::kFunction && is_sloppy(language_mode()) &&
6071  allow_function == kAllowLabelledFunctionStatement) {
6072  return ParseFunctionDeclaration();
6073  }
6074  return ParseStatement(labels, own_labels, allow_function);
6075  }
6076  }
6077 
6078  // We allow a native function declaration if we're parsing the source for an
6079  // extension. A native function declaration starts with "native function"
6080  // with no line-terminator between the two words.
6081  if (impl()->ParsingExtension() && peek() == Token::kFunction &&
6082  !scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() && impl()->IsNative(expr) &&
6083  !scanner()->literal_contains_escapes()) {
6084  return ParseNativeDeclaration();
6085  }
6086 
6087  // Parsed expression statement, followed by semicolon.
6088  ExpectSemicolon();
6089  if (expr->IsFailureExpression()) return impl()->NullStatement();
6090  return factory()->NewExpressionStatement(expr, pos);
6091 }
6092 
6093 template <typename Impl>
6094 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseIfStatement(
6095  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
6096  // IfStatement ::
6097  // 'if' '(' Expression ')' Statement ('else' Statement)?
6098 
6099  int pos = peek_position();
6100  Consume(Token::kIf);
6101  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6102  ExpressionT condition = ParseExpression();
6103  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6104 
6105  SourceRange then_range, else_range;
6106  StatementT then_statement = impl()->NullStatement();
6107  {
6108  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &then_range);
6109  // Make a copy of {labels} to avoid conflicts with any
6110  // labels that may be applied to the else clause below.
6111  auto labels_copy =
6112  labels == nullptr
6113  ? labels
6114  : zone()->template New<ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>>(*labels,
6115  zone());
6116  then_statement = ParseScopedStatement(labels_copy);
6117  }
6118 
6119  StatementT else_statement = impl()->NullStatement();
6120  if (Check(Token::kElse)) {
6121  else_statement = ParseScopedStatement(labels);
6122  else_range = SourceRange::ContinuationOf(then_range, end_position());
6123  } else {
6124  else_statement = factory()->EmptyStatement();
6125  }
6126  StatementT stmt =
6127  factory()->NewIfStatement(condition, then_statement, else_statement, pos);
6128  impl()->RecordIfStatementSourceRange(stmt, then_range, else_range);
6129  return stmt;
6130 }
6131 
6132 template <typename Impl>
6133 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
6134 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseContinueStatement() {
6135  // ContinueStatement ::
6136  // 'continue' Identifier? ';'
6137 
6138  int pos = peek_position();
6139  Consume(Token::kContinue);
6140  IdentifierT label = impl()->NullIdentifier();
6141  Token::Value tok = peek();
6142  if (!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() &&
6143  !Token::IsAutoSemicolon(tok)) {
6144  // ECMA allows "eval" or "arguments" as labels even in strict mode.
6145  label = ParseIdentifier();
6146  }
6147  IterationStatementT target = LookupContinueTarget(label);
6148  if (impl()->IsNull(target)) {
6149  // Illegal continue statement.
6150  MessageTemplate message = MessageTemplate::kIllegalContinue;
6151  BreakableStatementT breakable_target = LookupBreakTarget(label);
6152  if (impl()->IsNull(label)) {
6153  message = MessageTemplate::kNoIterationStatement;
6154  } else if (impl()->IsNull(breakable_target)) {
6155  message = MessageTemplate::kUnknownLabel;
6156  }
6157  ReportMessage(message, label);
6158  return impl()->NullStatement();
6159  }
6160  ExpectSemicolon();
6161  StatementT stmt = factory()->NewContinueStatement(target, pos);
6162  impl()->RecordJumpStatementSourceRange(stmt, end_position());
6163  return stmt;
6164 }
6165 
6166 template <typename Impl>
6167 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseBreakStatement(
6168  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
6169  // BreakStatement ::
6170  // 'break' Identifier? ';'
6171 
6172  int pos = peek_position();
6173  Consume(Token::kBreak);
6174  IdentifierT label = impl()->NullIdentifier();
6175  Token::Value tok = peek();
6176  if (!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() &&
6177  !Token::IsAutoSemicolon(tok)) {
6178  // ECMA allows "eval" or "arguments" as labels even in strict mode.
6179  label = ParseIdentifier();
6180  }
6181  // Parse labeled break statements that target themselves into
6182  // empty statements, e.g. 'l1: l2: l3: break l2;'
6183  if (!impl()->IsNull(label) &&
6184  impl()->ContainsLabel(labels, impl()->GetRawNameFromIdentifier(label))) {
6185  ExpectSemicolon();
6186  return factory()->EmptyStatement();
6187  }
6188  BreakableStatementT target = LookupBreakTarget(label);
6189  if (impl()->IsNull(target)) {
6190  // Illegal break statement.
6191  MessageTemplate message = MessageTemplate::kIllegalBreak;
6192  if (!impl()->IsNull(label)) {
6193  message = MessageTemplate::kUnknownLabel;
6194  }
6195  ReportMessage(message, label);
6196  return impl()->NullStatement();
6197  }
6198  ExpectSemicolon();
6199  StatementT stmt = factory()->NewBreakStatement(target, pos);
6200  impl()->RecordJumpStatementSourceRange(stmt, end_position());
6201  return stmt;
6202 }
6203 
6204 template <typename Impl>
6205 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseReturnStatement() {
6206  // ReturnStatement ::
6207  // 'return' [no line terminator] Expression? ';'
6208 
6209  // Consume the return token. It is necessary to do that before
6210  // reporting any errors on it, because of the way errors are
6211  // reported (underlining).
6212  Consume(Token::kReturn);
6213  Scanner::Location loc = scanner()->location();
6214 
6215  switch (GetDeclarationScope()->scope_type()) {
6216  case SCRIPT_SCOPE:
6217  case REPL_MODE_SCOPE:
6218  case EVAL_SCOPE:
6219  case MODULE_SCOPE:
6220  impl()->ReportMessageAt(loc, MessageTemplate::kIllegalReturn);
6221  return impl()->NullStatement();
6222  case BLOCK_SCOPE:
6223  // Class static blocks disallow return. They are their own var scopes and
6224  // have a varblock scope.
6225  if (function_state_->kind() ==
6226  FunctionKind::kClassStaticInitializerFunction) {
6227  impl()->ReportMessageAt(loc, MessageTemplate::kIllegalReturn);
6228  return impl()->NullStatement();
6229  }
6230  break;
6231  default:
6232  break;
6233  }
6234 
6235  Token::Value tok = peek();
6236  ExpressionT return_value = impl()->NullExpression();
6237  if (!scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext() &&
6238  !Token::IsAutoSemicolon(tok)) {
6239  return_value = ParseExpression();
6240  }
6241  ExpectSemicolon();
6242 
6243  int continuation_pos = end_position();
6244  StatementT stmt =
6245  BuildReturnStatement(return_value, loc.beg_pos, continuation_pos);
6246  impl()->RecordJumpStatementSourceRange(stmt, end_position());
6247  return stmt;
6248 }
6249 
6250 template <typename Impl>
6251 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseWithStatement(
6252  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
6253  // WithStatement ::
6254  // 'with' '(' Expression ')' Statement
6255 
6256  Consume(Token::kWith);
6257  int pos = position();
6258 
6259  if (is_strict(language_mode())) {
6260  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kStrictWith);
6261  return impl()->NullStatement();
6262  }
6263 
6264  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6265  ExpressionT expr = ParseExpression();
6266  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6267 
6268  Scope* with_scope = NewScope(WITH_SCOPE);
6269  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6270  {
6271  BlockState block_state(&scope_, with_scope);
6272  with_scope->set_start_position(position());
6273  body = ParseStatement(labels, nullptr);
6274  with_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
6275  }
6276  return factory()->NewWithStatement(with_scope, expr, body, pos);
6277 }
6278 
6279 template <typename Impl>
6280 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseDoWhileStatement(
6281  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6282  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6283  // DoStatement ::
6284  // 'do' Statement 'while' '(' Expression ')' ';'
6285  typename FunctionState::LoopScope loop_scope(function_state_);
6286 
6287  auto loop = factory()->NewDoWhileStatement(peek_position());
6288  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6289 
6290  SourceRange body_range;
6291  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6292 
6293  Consume(Token::kDo);
6294 
6295  CheckStackOverflow();
6296  {
6297  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
6298  body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
6299  }
6300  Expect(Token::kWhile);
6301  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6302 
6303  ExpressionT cond = ParseExpression();
6304  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6305 
6306  // Allow do-statements to be terminated with and without
6307  // semi-colons. This allows code such as 'do;while(0)return' to
6308  // parse, which would not be the case if we had used the
6309  // ExpectSemicolon() functionality here.
6310  Check(Token::kSemicolon);
6311 
6312  loop->Initialize(cond, body);
6313  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
6314 
6315  return loop;
6316 }
6317 
6318 template <typename Impl>
6319 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseWhileStatement(
6320  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6321  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6322  // WhileStatement ::
6323  // 'while' '(' Expression ')' Statement
6324  typename FunctionState::LoopScope loop_scope(function_state_);
6325 
6326  auto loop = factory()->NewWhileStatement(peek_position());
6327  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6328 
6329  SourceRange body_range;
6330  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6331 
6332  Consume(Token::kWhile);
6333  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6334  ExpressionT cond = ParseExpression();
6335  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6336  {
6337  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
6338  body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
6339  }
6340 
6341  loop->Initialize(cond, body);
6342  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
6343 
6344  return loop;
6345 }
