6347 template <typename Impl>
6348 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseThrowStatement() {
6349  // ThrowStatement ::
6350  // 'throw' Expression ';'
6351 
6352  Consume(Token::kThrow);
6353  int pos = position();
6354  if (scanner()->HasLineTerminatorBeforeNext()) {
6355  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kNewlineAfterThrow);
6356  return impl()->NullStatement();
6357  }
6358  ExpressionT exception = ParseExpression();
6359  ExpectSemicolon();
6360 
6361  StatementT stmt = impl()->NewThrowStatement(exception, pos);
6362  impl()->RecordThrowSourceRange(stmt, end_position());
6363 
6364  return stmt;
6365 }
6366 
6367 template <typename Impl>
6368 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseSwitchStatement(
6369  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels) {
6370  // SwitchStatement ::
6371  // 'switch' '(' Expression ')' '{' CaseClause* '}'
6372  // CaseClause ::
6373  // 'case' Expression ':' StatementList
6374  // 'default' ':' StatementList
6375  int switch_pos = peek_position();
6376 
6377  Consume(Token::kSwitch);
6378  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6379  ExpressionT tag = ParseExpression();
6380  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6381 
6382  auto switch_statement = factory()->NewSwitchStatement(tag, switch_pos);
6383 
6384  {
6385  BlockState cases_block_state(zone(), &scope_);
6386  scope()->set_start_position(switch_pos);
6387  scope()->SetNonlinear();
6388  Target target(this, switch_statement, labels, nullptr,
6389  Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6390 
6391  bool default_seen = false;
6392  Expect(Token::kLeftBrace);
6393  while (peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
6394  // An empty label indicates the default case.
6395  ExpressionT label = impl()->NullExpression();
6396  StatementListT statements(pointer_buffer());
6397  SourceRange clause_range;
6398  {
6399  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &clause_range);
6400  if (Check(Token::kCase)) {
6401  label = ParseExpression();
6402  } else {
6403  Expect(Token::kDefault);
6404  if (default_seen) {
6405  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kMultipleDefaultsInSwitch);
6406  return impl()->NullStatement();
6407  }
6408  default_seen = true;
6409  }
6410  Expect(Token::kColon);
6411  while (peek() != Token::kCase && peek() != Token::kDefault &&
6412  peek() != Token::kRightBrace) {
6413  StatementT stat = ParseStatementListItem();
6414  if (impl()->IsNull(stat)) return stat;
6415  if (stat->IsEmptyStatement()) continue;
6416  statements.Add(stat);
6417  }
6418  }
6419  auto clause = factory()->NewCaseClause(label, statements);
6420  impl()->RecordCaseClauseSourceRange(clause, clause_range);
6421  switch_statement->cases()->Add(clause, zone());
6422  }
6423  Expect(Token::kRightBrace);
6424 
6425  int end_pos = end_position();
6426  scope()->set_end_position(end_pos);
6427  impl()->RecordSwitchStatementSourceRange(switch_statement, end_pos);
6428  Scope* switch_scope = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
6429  if (switch_scope != nullptr) {
6430  return impl()->RewriteSwitchStatement(switch_statement, switch_scope);
6431  }
6432  return switch_statement;
6433  }
6434 }
6435 
6436 template <typename Impl>
6437 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseTryStatement() {
6438  // TryStatement ::
6439  // 'try' Block Catch
6440  // 'try' Block Finally
6441  // 'try' Block Catch Finally
6442  //
6443  // Catch ::
6444  // 'catch' '(' Identifier ')' Block
6445  //
6446  // Finally ::
6447  // 'finally' Block
6448 
6449  Consume(Token::kTry);
6450  int pos = position();
6451 
6452  BlockT try_block = ParseBlock(nullptr);
6453 
6454  CatchInfo catch_info(this);
6455 
6456  if (peek() != Token::kCatch && peek() != Token::kFinally) {
6457  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kNoCatchOrFinally);
6458  return impl()->NullStatement();
6459  }
6460 
6461  SourceRange catch_range, finally_range;
6462 
6463  BlockT catch_block = impl()->NullBlock();
6464  {
6465  SourceRangeScope catch_range_scope(scanner(), &catch_range);
6466  if (Check(Token::kCatch)) {
6467  bool has_binding;
6468  has_binding = Check(Token::kLeftParen);
6469 
6470  if (has_binding) {
6471  catch_info.scope = NewScope(CATCH_SCOPE);
6472  catch_info.scope->set_start_position(position());
6473 
6474  {
6475  BlockState catch_block_state(&scope_, catch_info.scope);
6476  StatementListT catch_statements(pointer_buffer());
6477 
6478  // Create a block scope to hold any lexical declarations created
6479  // as part of destructuring the catch parameter.
6480  {
6481  BlockState catch_variable_block_state(zone(), &scope_);
6482  scope()->set_start_position(peek_position());
6483 
6484  if (peek_any_identifier()) {
6485  IdentifierT identifier = ParseNonRestrictedIdentifier();
6486  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6487  catch_info.variable = impl()->DeclareCatchVariableName(
6488  catch_info.scope, identifier);
6489  } else {
6490  catch_info.variable = catch_info.scope->DeclareCatchVariableName(
6491  ast_value_factory()->dot_catch_string());
6492 
6493  auto declaration_it = scope()->declarations()->end();
6494 
6495  VariableDeclarationParsingScope destructuring(
6496  impl(), VariableMode::kLet, nullptr);
6497  catch_info.pattern = ParseBindingPattern();
6498 
6499  int initializer_position = end_position();
6500  auto declaration_end = scope()->declarations()->end();
6501  for (; declaration_it != declaration_end; ++declaration_it) {
6502  declaration_it->var()->set_initializer_position(
6503  initializer_position);
6504  }
6505 
6506  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6507  catch_statements.Add(impl()->RewriteCatchPattern(&catch_info));
6508  }
6509 
6510  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6511 
6512  BlockT inner_block = ParseBlock(nullptr);
6513  catch_statements.Add(inner_block);
6514 
6515  // Check for `catch(e) { let e; }` and similar errors.
6516  if (!impl()->HasCheckedSyntax()) {
6517  Scope* inner_scope = inner_block->scope();
6518  if (inner_scope != nullptr) {
6519  const AstRawString* conflict = nullptr;
6520  if (impl()->IsNull(catch_info.pattern)) {
6521  const AstRawString* name = catch_info.variable->raw_name();
6522  if (inner_scope->LookupLocal(name)) conflict = name;
6523  } else {
6524  conflict = inner_scope->FindVariableDeclaredIn(
6525  scope(), VariableMode::kVar);
6526  }
6527  if (conflict != nullptr) {
6528  impl()->ReportVarRedeclarationIn(conflict, inner_scope);
6529  }
6530  }
6531  }
6532 
6533  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
6534  catch_block = factory()->NewBlock(false, catch_statements);
6535  catch_block->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
6536  }
6537  }
6538 
6539  catch_info.scope->set_end_position(end_position());
6540  } else {
6541  catch_block = ParseBlock(nullptr);
6542  }
6543  }
6544  }
6545 
6546  BlockT finally_block = impl()->NullBlock();
6547  DCHECK(has_error() || peek() == Token::kFinally ||
6548  !impl()->IsNull(catch_block));
6549  {
6550  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &finally_range);
6551  if (Check(Token::kFinally)) {
6552  finally_block = ParseBlock(nullptr);
6553  }
6554  }
6555 
6556  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6557  return impl()->RewriteTryStatement(try_block, catch_block, catch_range,
6558  finally_block, finally_range, catch_info,
6559  pos);
6560 }
6561 
6562 template <typename Impl>
6563 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseForStatement(
6564  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6565  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6566  // Either a standard for loop
6567  // for (<init>; <cond>; <next>) { ... }
6568  // or a for-each loop
6569  // for (<each> of|in <iterable>) { ... }
6570  //
6571  // We parse a declaration/expression after the 'for (' and then read the first
6572  // expression/declaration before we know if this is a for or a for-each.
6573  typename FunctionState::LoopScope loop_scope(function_state_);
6574 
6575  int stmt_pos = peek_position();
6576  ForInfo for_info(this);
6577 
6578  Consume(Token::kFor);
6579  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6580 
6581  bool starts_with_let = peek() == Token::kLet;
6582  bool starts_with_using_or_await_using_keyword =
6583  IfStartsWithUsingOrAwaitUsingKeyword();
6584  if (peek() == Token::kConst || (starts_with_let && IsNextLetKeyword()) ||
6585  starts_with_using_or_await_using_keyword) {
6586  // The initializer contains lexical declarations,
6587  // so create an in-between scope.
6588  BlockState for_state(zone(), &scope_);
6589  scope()->set_start_position(position());
6590 
6591  // Also record whether inner functions or evals are found inside
6592  // this loop, as this information is used to simplify the desugaring
6593  // if none are found.
6594  typename FunctionState::FunctionOrEvalRecordingScope recording_scope(
6595  function_state_);
6596 
6597  // Create an inner block scope which will be the parent scope of scopes
6598  // possibly created by ParseVariableDeclarations.
6599  Scope* inner_block_scope = NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE);
6600  inner_block_scope->set_start_position(end_position());
6601  {
6602  BlockState inner_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
6603  ParseVariableDeclarations(kForStatement, &for_info.parsing_result,
6604  &for_info.bound_names);
6605  }
6606  DCHECK(IsLexicalVariableMode(for_info.parsing_result.descriptor.mode));
6607  for_info.position = position();
6608 
6609  if (CheckInOrOf(&for_info.mode)) {
6610  scope()->set_is_hidden();
6611  if (starts_with_using_or_await_using_keyword &&
6612  for_info.mode == ForEachStatement::ENUMERATE) {
6613  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->location(),
6614  MessageTemplate::kInvalidUsingInForInLoop);
6615  }
6616  return ParseForEachStatementWithDeclarations(
6617  stmt_pos, &for_info, labels, own_labels, inner_block_scope);
6618  }
6619 
6620  Expect(Token::kSemicolon);
6621 
6622  // Parse the remaining code in the inner block scope since the declaration
6623  // above was parsed there. We'll finalize the unnecessary outer block scope
6624  // after parsing the rest of the loop.
6625  StatementT result = impl()->NullStatement();
6626  {
6627  BlockState inner_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
6628  StatementT init =
6629  impl()->BuildInitializationBlock(&for_info.parsing_result);
6630 
6631  result = ParseStandardForLoopWithLexicalDeclarations(
6632  stmt_pos, init, &for_info, labels, own_labels);
6633  }
6634  Scope* finalized = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
6635  DCHECK_NULL(finalized);
6636  USE(finalized);
6637  return result;
6638  }
6639 
6640  StatementT init = impl()->NullStatement();
6641  if (peek() == Token::kVar) {
6642  ParseVariableDeclarations(kForStatement, &for_info.parsing_result,
6643  &for_info.bound_names);
6644  DCHECK_EQ(for_info.parsing_result.descriptor.mode, VariableMode::kVar);
6645  for_info.position = position();
6646 
6647  if (CheckInOrOf(&for_info.mode)) {
6648  return ParseForEachStatementWithDeclarations(stmt_pos, &for_info, labels,
6649  own_labels, scope());
6650  }
6651 
6652  init = impl()->BuildInitializationBlock(&for_info.parsing_result);
6653  } else if (peek() != Token::kSemicolon) {
6654  // The initializer does not contain declarations.
6655  Scanner::Location next_loc = scanner()->peek_location();
6656  int lhs_beg_pos = next_loc.beg_pos;
6657  int lhs_end_pos;
6658  bool is_for_each;
6659  ExpressionT expression;
6660 
6661  {
6662  ExpressionParsingScope parsing_scope(impl());
6663  AcceptINScope scope(this, false);
6664  expression = ParseExpressionCoverGrammar();
6665  // `for (async of` is disallowed but `for (async.x of` is allowed, so
6666  // check if the token is kAsync after parsing the expression.
6667  bool expression_is_async = scanner()->current_token() == Token::kAsync &&
6668  !scanner()->literal_contains_escapes();
6669  // Initializer is reference followed by in/of.
6670  lhs_end_pos = end_position();
6671  is_for_each = CheckInOrOf(&for_info.mode);
6672  if (is_for_each) {
6673  if ((starts_with_let || expression_is_async) &&
6674  for_info.mode == ForEachStatement::ITERATE) {
6675  impl()->ReportMessageAt(next_loc, starts_with_let
6676  ? MessageTemplate::kForOfLet
6677  : MessageTemplate::kForOfAsync);
6678  return impl()->NullStatement();
6679  }
6680  if (expression->IsPattern()) {
6681  parsing_scope.ValidatePattern(expression, lhs_beg_pos, lhs_end_pos);
6682  } else {
6683  expression = parsing_scope.ValidateAndRewriteReference(
6684  expression, lhs_beg_pos, lhs_end_pos);
6685  }
6686  } else {
6687  parsing_scope.ValidateExpression();
6688  }
6689  }
6690 
6691  if (is_for_each) {
6692  return ParseForEachStatementWithoutDeclarations(
6693  stmt_pos, expression, lhs_beg_pos, lhs_end_pos, &for_info, labels,
6694  own_labels);
6695  }
6696  // Initializer is just an expression.
6697  init = factory()->NewExpressionStatement(expression, lhs_beg_pos);
6698  }
6699 
6700  Expect(Token::kSemicolon);
6701 
6702  // Standard 'for' loop, we have parsed the initializer at this point.
6703  ExpressionT cond = impl()->NullExpression();
6704  StatementT next = impl()->NullStatement();
6705  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6706  ForStatementT loop =
6707  ParseStandardForLoop(stmt_pos, labels, own_labels, &cond, &next, &body);
6708  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6709  loop->Initialize(init, cond, next, body);
6710  return loop;
6711 }
6712 
6713 template <typename Impl>
6714 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
6715 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseForEachStatementWithDeclarations(
6716  int stmt_pos, ForInfo* for_info, ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6717  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels, Scope* inner_block_scope) {
6718  // Just one declaration followed by in/of.
6719  if (for_info->parsing_result.declarations.size() != 1) {
6720  impl()->ReportMessageAt(for_info->parsing_result.bindings_loc,
6721  MessageTemplate::kForInOfLoopMultiBindings,
6722  ForEachStatement::VisitModeString(for_info->mode));
6723  return impl()->NullStatement();
6724  }
6725  if (for_info->parsing_result.first_initializer_loc.IsValid() &&
6726  (is_strict(language_mode()) ||
6727  for_info->mode == ForEachStatement::ITERATE ||
6728  IsLexicalVariableMode(for_info->parsing_result.descriptor.mode) ||
6729  !impl()->IsIdentifier(
6730  for_info->parsing_result.declarations[0].pattern))) {
6731  impl()->ReportMessageAt(for_info->parsing_result.first_initializer_loc,
6732  MessageTemplate::kForInOfLoopInitializer,
6733  ForEachStatement::VisitModeString(for_info->mode));
6734  return impl()->NullStatement();
6735  }
6736 
6737  BlockT init_block = impl()->RewriteForVarInLegacy(*for_info);
6738 
6739  auto loop = factory()->NewForEachStatement(for_info->mode, stmt_pos);
6740  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6741 
6742  Scope* enumerable_block_scope = NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE);
6743  enumerable_block_scope->set_start_position(position());
6744  enumerable_block_scope->set_is_hidden();
6745  ExpressionT enumerable = impl()->NullExpression();
6746  {
6747  BlockState block_state(&scope_, enumerable_block_scope);
6748 
6749  if (for_info->mode == ForEachStatement::ITERATE) {
6750  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
6751  enumerable = ParseAssignmentExpression();
6752  } else {
6753  enumerable = ParseExpression();
6754  }
6755  }
6756  enumerable_block_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
6757 
6758  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6759 
6760  ExpressionT each_variable = impl()->NullExpression();
6761  BlockT body_block = impl()->NullBlock();
6762  {
6763  BlockState block_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
6764 
6765  SourceRange body_range;
6766  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6767  {
6768  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
6769  body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
6770  }
6771  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
6772 
6773  impl()->DesugarBindingInForEachStatement(for_info, &body_block,
6774  &each_variable);
6775  body_block->statements()->Add(body, zone());
6776 
6777  if (IsLexicalVariableMode(for_info->parsing_result.descriptor.mode)) {
6778  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
6779  body_block->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
6780  }
6781  }
6782 
6783  loop->Initialize(each_variable, enumerable, body_block,
6784  enumerable_block_scope);
6785 
6786  init_block = impl()->CreateForEachStatementTDZ(init_block, *for_info);
6787 
6788  // Parsed for-in loop w/ variable declarations.
6789  if (!impl()->IsNull(init_block)) {
6790  init_block->statements()->Add(loop, zone());
6791  if (IsLexicalVariableMode(for_info->parsing_result.descriptor.mode)) {
6792  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
6793  init_block->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
6794  }
6795  return init_block;
6796  }
6797 
6798  return loop;
6799 }

6801 template <typename Impl>
6802 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
6803 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseForEachStatementWithoutDeclarations(
6804  int stmt_pos, ExpressionT expression, int lhs_beg_pos, int lhs_end_pos,
6805  ForInfo* for_info, ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6806  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6807  auto loop = factory()->NewForEachStatement(for_info->mode, stmt_pos);
6808  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6809 
6810  ExpressionT enumerable = impl()->NullExpression();
6811  if (for_info->mode == ForEachStatement::ITERATE) {
6812  AcceptINScope scope(this, true);
6813  enumerable = ParseAssignmentExpression();
6814  } else {
6815  enumerable = ParseExpression();
6816  }
6817 
6818  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6819 
6820  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6821  SourceRange body_range;
6822  {
6823  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
6824  body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
6825  }
6826  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
6827  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6828  loop->Initialize(expression, enumerable, body, nullptr);
6829  return loop;
6830 }

6832 template <typename Impl>
6833 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT
6834 ParserBase<Impl>::ParseStandardForLoopWithLexicalDeclarations(
6835  int stmt_pos, StatementT init, ForInfo* for_info,
6836  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6837  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6838  // The condition and the next statement of the for loop must be parsed
6839  // in a new scope.
6840  Scope* inner_scope = NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE);
6841  ForStatementT loop = impl()->NullStatement();
6842  ExpressionT cond = impl()->NullExpression();
6843  StatementT next = impl()->NullStatement();
6844  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
6845  {
6846  BlockState block_state(&scope_, inner_scope);
6847  scope()->set_start_position(scanner()->location().beg_pos);
6848  loop =
6849  ParseStandardForLoop(stmt_pos, labels, own_labels, &cond, &next, &body);
6850  RETURN_IF_PARSE_ERROR;
6851  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
6852  }
6853 
6854  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
6855  if (for_info->bound_names.length() > 0 &&
6856  function_state_->contains_function_or_eval()) {
6857  scope()->set_is_hidden();
6858  return impl()->DesugarLexicalBindingsInForStatement(
6859  loop, init, cond, next, body, inner_scope, *for_info);
6860  } else {
6861  inner_scope = inner_scope->FinalizeBlockScope();
6862  DCHECK_NULL(inner_scope);
6863  USE(inner_scope);
6864  }
6865 
6866  Scope* for_scope = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
6867  if (for_scope != nullptr) {
6868  // Rewrite a for statement of the form
6869  // for (const x = i; c; n) b
6870  //
6871  // into
6872  //
6873  // {
6874  // const x = i;
6875  // for (; c; n) b
6876  // }
6877  //
6878  DCHECK(!impl()->IsNull(init));
6879  BlockT block = factory()->NewBlock(2, false);
6880  block->statements()->Add(init, zone());
6881  block->statements()->Add(loop, zone());
6882  block->set_scope(for_scope);
6883  loop->Initialize(impl()->NullStatement(), cond, next, body);
6884  return block;
6885  }
6886 
6887  loop->Initialize(init, cond, next, body);
6888  return loop;
6889 }
6890 
6891 template <typename Impl>
6892 typename ParserBase<Impl>::ForStatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseStandardForLoop(
6893  int stmt_pos, ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6894  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels, ExpressionT* cond,
6895  StatementT* next, StatementT* body) {
6896  CheckStackOverflow();
6897  ForStatementT loop = factory()->NewForStatement(stmt_pos);
6898  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6899 
6900  if (peek() != Token::kSemicolon) {
6901  *cond = ParseExpression();
6902  }
6903  Expect(Token::kSemicolon);
6904 
6905  if (peek() != Token::kRightParen) {
6906  ExpressionT exp = ParseExpression();
6907  *next = factory()->NewExpressionStatement(exp, exp->position());
6908  }
6909  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
6910 
6911  SourceRange body_range;
6912  {
6913  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
6914  *body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
6915  }
6916  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
6917 
6918  return loop;
6919 }
6920 
6921 template <typename Impl>
6922 typename ParserBase<Impl>::StatementT ParserBase<Impl>::ParseForAwaitStatement(
6923  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* labels,
6924  ZonePtrList<const AstRawString>* own_labels) {
6925  // for await '(' ForDeclaration of AssignmentExpression ')'
6926  DCHECK(is_await_allowed());
6927  typename FunctionState::LoopScope loop_scope(function_state_);
6928 
6929  int stmt_pos = peek_position();
6930 
6931  ForInfo for_info(this);
6932  for_info.mode = ForEachStatement::ITERATE;
6933 
6934  // Create an in-between scope for let-bound iteration variables.
6935  BlockState for_state(zone(), &scope_);
6936  Expect(Token::kFor);
6937  Expect(Token::kAwait);
6938  Expect(Token::kLeftParen);
6939  scope()->set_start_position(position());
6940  scope()->set_is_hidden();
6941 
6942  auto loop = factory()->NewForOfStatement(stmt_pos, IteratorType::kAsync);
6943  // Two suspends: one for next() and one for return()
6944  function_state_->AddSuspend();
6945  function_state_->AddSuspend();
6946 
6947  Target target(this, loop, labels, own_labels, Target::TARGET_FOR_ANONYMOUS);
6948 
6949  ExpressionT each_variable = impl()->NullExpression();
6950 
6951  bool has_declarations = false;
6952  Scope* inner_block_scope = NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE);
6953  inner_block_scope->set_start_position(peek_position());
6954 
6955  bool starts_with_let = peek() == Token::kLet;
6956  if (peek() == Token::kVar || peek() == Token::kConst ||
6957  (starts_with_let && IsNextLetKeyword()) ||
6958  IfStartsWithUsingOrAwaitUsingKeyword()) {
6959  // The initializer contains declarations
6960  // 'for' 'await' '(' ForDeclaration 'of' AssignmentExpression ')'
6961  // Statement
6962  // 'for' 'await' '(' 'var' ForBinding 'of' AssignmentExpression ')'
6963  // Statement
6964  has_declarations = true;
6965 
6966  {
6967  BlockState inner_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
6968  ParseVariableDeclarations(kForStatement, &for_info.parsing_result,
6969  &for_info.bound_names);
6970  }
6971  for_info.position = position();
6972 
6973  // Only a single declaration is allowed in for-await-of loops
6974  if (for_info.parsing_result.declarations.size() != 1) {
6975  impl()->ReportMessageAt(for_info.parsing_result.bindings_loc,
6976  MessageTemplate::kForInOfLoopMultiBindings,
6977  "for-await-of");
6978  return impl()->NullStatement();
6979  }
6980 
6981  // for-await-of's declarations do not permit initializers.
6982  if (for_info.parsing_result.first_initializer_loc.IsValid()) {
6983  impl()->ReportMessageAt(for_info.parsing_result.first_initializer_loc,
6984  MessageTemplate::kForInOfLoopInitializer,
6985  "for-await-of");
6986  return impl()->NullStatement();
6987  }
6988  } else {
6989  // The initializer does not contain declarations.
6990  // 'for' 'await' '(' LeftHandSideExpression 'of' AssignmentExpression ')'
6991  // Statement
6992  if (starts_with_let) {
6993  impl()->ReportMessageAt(scanner()->peek_location(),
6994  MessageTemplate::kForOfLet);
6995  return impl()->NullStatement();
6996  }
6997  int lhs_beg_pos = peek_position();
6998  BlockState inner_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
6999  ExpressionParsingScope parsing_scope(impl());
7000  ExpressionT lhs = each_variable = ParseLeftHandSideExpression();
7001  int lhs_end_pos = end_position();
7002 
7003  if (lhs->IsPattern()) {
7004  parsing_scope.ValidatePattern(lhs, lhs_beg_pos, lhs_end_pos);
7005  } else {
7006  each_variable = parsing_scope.ValidateAndRewriteReference(
7007  lhs, lhs_beg_pos, lhs_end_pos);
7008  }
7009  }
7010 
7011  ExpectContextualKeyword(Token::kOf);
7012 
7013  const bool kAllowIn = true;
7014  ExpressionT iterable = impl()->NullExpression();
7015  Scope* iterable_block_scope = NewScope(BLOCK_SCOPE);
7016  iterable_block_scope->set_start_position(position());
7017  iterable_block_scope->set_is_hidden();
7018 
7019  {
7020  BlockState block_state(&scope_, iterable_block_scope);
7021  AcceptINScope scope(this, kAllowIn);
7022  iterable = ParseAssignmentExpression();
7023  }
7024  iterable_block_scope->set_end_position(end_position());
7025 
7026  Expect(Token::kRightParen);
7027 
7028  StatementT body = impl()->NullStatement();
7029  {
7030  BlockState block_state(&scope_, inner_block_scope);
7031 
7032  SourceRange body_range;
7033  {
7034  SourceRangeScope range_scope(scanner(), &body_range);
7035  body = ParseStatement(nullptr, nullptr);
7036  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
7037  }
7038  impl()->RecordIterationStatementSourceRange(loop, body_range);
7039 
7040  if (has_declarations) {
7041  BlockT body_block = impl()->NullBlock();
7042  impl()->DesugarBindingInForEachStatement(&for_info, &body_block,
7043  &each_variable);
7044  body_block->statements()->Add(body, zone());
7045  body_block->set_scope(scope()->FinalizeBlockScope());
7046  body = body_block;
7047  } else {
7048  Scope* block_scope = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
7049  DCHECK_NULL(block_scope);
7050  USE(block_scope);
7051  }
7052  }
7053 
7054  loop->Initialize(each_variable, iterable, body, iterable_block_scope);
7055 
7056  if (!has_declarations) {
7057  Scope* for_scope = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
7058  DCHECK_NULL(for_scope);
7059  USE(for_scope);
7060  return loop;
7061  }
7062 
7063  BlockT init_block =
7064  impl()->CreateForEachStatementTDZ(impl()->NullBlock(), for_info);
7065 
7066  scope()->set_end_position(end_position());
7067  Scope* for_scope = scope()->FinalizeBlockScope();
7068  // Parsed for-in loop w/ variable declarations.
7069  if (!impl()->IsNull(init_block)) {
7070  init_block->statements()->Add(loop, zone());
7071  init_block->set_scope(for_scope);
7072  return init_block;
7073  }
7074  DCHECK_NULL(for_scope);
7075  return loop;
7076 }
7077 
7078 template <typename Impl>
7079 void ParserBase<Impl>::CheckClassMethodName(IdentifierT name,
7080  ParsePropertyKind type,
7081  ParseFunctionFlags flags,
7082  bool is_static,
7083  bool* has_seen_constructor) {
7084  DCHECK(type == ParsePropertyKind::kMethod || IsAccessor(type));
7085 
7086  AstValueFactory* avf = ast_value_factory();
7087 
7088  if (impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->private_constructor_string())) {
7089  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kConstructorIsPrivate);
7090  return;
7091  } else if (is_static) {
7092  if (impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->prototype_string())) {
7093  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kStaticPrototype);
7094  return;
7095  }
7096  } else if (impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->constructor_string())) {
7097  if (flags != ParseFunctionFlag::kIsNormal || IsAccessor(type)) {
7098  MessageTemplate msg = (flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsGenerator) != 0
7099  ? MessageTemplate::kConstructorIsGenerator
7100  : (flags & ParseFunctionFlag::kIsAsync) != 0
7101  ? MessageTemplate::kConstructorIsAsync
7102  : MessageTemplate::kConstructorIsAccessor;
7103  ReportMessage(msg);
7104  return;
7105  }
7106  if (*has_seen_constructor) {
7107  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kDuplicateConstructor);
7108  return;
7109  }
7110  *has_seen_constructor = true;
7111  return;
7112  }
7113 }
7114 
7115 template <typename Impl>
7116 void ParserBase<Impl>::CheckClassFieldName(IdentifierT name, bool is_static) {
7117  AstValueFactory* avf = ast_value_factory();
7118  if (is_static && impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->prototype_string())) {
7119  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kStaticPrototype);
7120  return;
7121  }
7122 
7123  if (impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->constructor_string()) ||
7124  impl()->IdentifierEquals(name, avf->private_constructor_string())) {
7125  ReportMessage(MessageTemplate::kConstructorClassField);
7126  return;
7127  }
7128 }
